{"term": "1965", "caseName": "Walker Process Equipment, Inc. v. Food Machinery & Chemical Corporation", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/1965/13", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - October 12, 1965", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren13/oral_argument_audio/15025", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Number 13, Walker Process Equipment Incorporated, Petitioner, versus Food Machinery and Chemical Corporation.", "start": 0, "stop": 11.456, "duration": 11.46, "cleanText": [["number", "walker", "process", "equipment", "incorporate", "petitioner", "versus", "food", "machinery", "and", "chemical", "corporation"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Merriam.", "start": 11.456, "stop": 12.967, "duration": 1.51, "cleanText": [["mr", "merriam"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice and members of the Court.", "start": 12.967, "stop": 16.206, "duration": 3.24, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "member", "of", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "This case comes here on petition for certiorari to the Seventh Circuit for affirming an opinion of the District Court on two different aspects.", "start": 16.206, "stop": 26.729, "duration": 10.52, "cleanText": [["this", "case", "come", "here", "on", "petition", "for", "certiorari", "to", "the", "seventh", "circuit", "for", "affirm", "an", "opinion", "of", "the", "district", "court", "on", "two", "different", "aspect"]]}, {"text": "The first was the dismissal of the original complaint for patent infringement on the latter patent which I will go into, after it had become apparent that the patent had been obtained by fraud upon the Patent Office and without an opportunity to obtain findings of facts with respect to that fraud, and also, without awarding as requested attorney's fees in connection with the dismissal.", "start": 26.729, "stop": 56.042, "duration": 29.31, "cleanText": [["the", "first", "be", "the", "dismissal", "of", "the", "original", "complaint", "for", "patent", "infringement", "on", "the", "latter", "patent", "which", "i", "will", "go", "into", "after", "it", "have", "become", "apparent", "that", "the", "patent", "have", "be", "obtain", "by", "fraud", "upon", "the", "patent", "office", "and", "without", "an", "opportunity", "to", "obtain", "finding", "of", "fact", "with", "respect", "to", "that", "fraud", "and", "also", "without", "award", "as", "request", "attorney", "s", "fee", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "dismissal"]]}, {"text": "The second point of time, perhaps more important here was the dismissal of Walkers' counterclaim -- or rather second amended counterclaim which setup a cause of action, allegedly, based upon the fact that the plaintiff FMC had obtained its patent by a fraud from the Patent Office and failing to point out to the Patent Office, and in filing a false oath with respect to the absence of prior use more than a year before the patent was filed.", "start": 56.042, "stop": 92.333, "duration": 36.29, "cleanText": [["the", "second", "point", "of", "time", "perhaps", "more", "important", "here", "be", "the", "dismissal", "of", "walker", "counterclaim", "or", "rather", "second", "amend", "counterclaim", "which", "setup", "a", "because", "of", "action", "allegedly", "base", "upon", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "plaintiff", "fmc", "have", "obtain", "its", "patent", "by", "a", "fraud", "from", "the", "patent", "office", "and", "fail", "to", "point", "out", "to", "the", "patent", "office", "and", "in", "file", "a", "false", "oath", "with", "respect", "to", "the", "absence", "of", "prior", "use", "more", "than", "a", "year", "before", "the", "patent", "be", "file"]]}, {"text": "That was dismissed on the ground that a plaintiff in a declaratory judgment action which was -- the counterclaim was taken to be cannot raise the issue of fraud because that would in effect be invalidating the patent which it could only be done by the Patent Office, it distinguished from cases where a fraud was setup in defense.", "start": 92.333, "stop": 118.208, "duration": 25.88, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "dismiss", "on", "the", "ground", "that", "a", "plaintiff", "in", "a", "declaratory", "judgment", "action", "which", "be", "the", "counterclaim", "be", "take", "to", "be", "can", "not", "raise", "the", "issue", "of", "fraud", "because", "that", "would", "in", "effect", "be", "invalidate", "the", "patent", "which", "it", "could", "only", "be", "do", "by", "the", "patent", "office", "it", "distinguish", "from", "case", "where", "a", "fraud", "be", "setup", "in", "defense"]]}, {"text": "The latter patent relates to the treatment of sewage and it is in the class of what you call aerations equipment and where long pipes, perforated pipes or tube are put into the bottom of the incoming sewage vessels and a stream of air is passed through that sewage.", "start": 118.208, "stop": 140.263, "duration": 22.06, "cleanText": [["the", "latter", "patent", "relate", "to", "the", "treatment", "of", "sewage", "and", "it", "be", "in", "the", "class", "of", "what", "you", "call", "aeration", "equipment", "and", "where", "long", "pipe", "perforate", "pipe", "or", "tube", "be", "put", "into", "the", "bottom", "of", "the", "incoming", "sewage", "vessel", "and", "a", "stream", "of", "air", "be", "pass", "through", "that", "sewage"]]}, {"text": "These pipes, if left by themselves in the old days, clog and the only remedy was to drain the tanks and go down and clean off the pipes, which was not exactly an appealing job.", "start": 140.263, "stop": 159.243, "duration": 18.98, "cleanText": [["these", "pipe", "if", "leave", "by", "themselves", "in", "the", "old", "day", "clog", "and", "the", "only", "remedy", "be", "to", "drain", "the", "tank", "and", "go", "down", "and", "clean", "off", "the", "pipe", "which", "be", "not", "exactly", "an", "appeal", "job"]]}, {"text": "And eventually, the Chicago Pump Company which is a division of FMC, developed a so-called swing diffuser in which the pipes were mounted on a swing apparatus which would swing them up so they could be cleaned out of the tank.", "start": 159.243, "stop": 177.406, "duration": 18.16, "cleanText": [["and", "eventually", "the", "chicago", "pump", "company", "which", "be", "a", "division", "of", "fmc", "develop", "a", "so", "called", "swing", "diffuser", "in", "which", "the", "pipe", "we", "be", "mount", "on", "a", "swing", "apparatus", "which", "would", "swing", "them", "up", "so", "they", "could", "be", "clean", "out", "of", "the", "tank"]]}, {"text": "That involves some difficulties because of the long arm of the -- it was necessary to swing them out and it involve a considerable torque and -- so the present invention came along, a so-called invention, in which the -- instead of a rigid arm, they need action or hinged arm to put in so that the torque was left, you could left this that's almost straight up.", "start": 177.406, "stop": 201.653, "duration": 24.25, "cleanText": [["that", "involve", "some", "difficulty", "because", "of", "the", "long", "arm", "of", "the", "it", "be", "necessary", "to", "swing", "them", "out", "and", "it", "involve", "a", "considerable", "torque", "and", "so", "the", "present", "invention", "come", "along", "a", "so", "called", "invention", "in", "which", "the", "instead", "of", "a", "rigid", "arm", "they", "need", "action", "or", "hinge", "arm", "to", "put", "in", "so", "that", "the", "torque", "be", "leave", "you", "could", "leave", "this", "that", "be", "almost", "straight", "up"]]}, {"text": "In spite of the fact that the only improvement was in the lifter arm, the patent covers the entire assembly including the tanks of which the end diffuser pipes, which the villagers and Municipalities themselves ordinarily installed.", "start": 201.653, "stop": 217.336, "duration": 15.68, "cleanText": [["in", "spite", "of", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "only", "improvement", "be", "in", "the", "lifter", "arm", "the", "patent", "cover", "the", "entire", "assembly", "include", "the", "tank", "of", "which", "the", "end", "diffuser", "pipe", "which", "the", "villager", "and", "municipality", "themselves", "ordinarily", "instal"]]}, {"text": "This -- the result of the patent however, was to permit the Chicago Pump Company and later FMC, which took it over, to have a complete monopoly on swing diffusers and a substantially complete monopoly on diffuser equipment itself.", "start": 217.336, "stop": 238.858, "duration": 21.52, "cleanText": [["this", "the", "result", "of", "the", "patent", "however", "be", "to", "permit", "the", "chicago", "pump", "company", "and", "later", "fmc", "which", "take", "it", "over", "to", "have", "a", "complete", "monopoly", "on", "swing", "diffuser", "and", "a", "substantially", "complete", "monopoly", "on", "diffuser", "equipment", "itself"]]}, {"text": "The -- Mr. Forest who represented FMC himself admitted at page 50 that they had had practically no competition in the diffuser field.", "start": 238.858, "stop": 249.835, "duration": 10.98, "cleanText": [["the", "mr", "forest", "who", "represent", "fmc", "himself", "admit", "at", "page", "that", "they", "have", "have", "practically", "no", "competition", "in", "the", "diffuser", "field"]]}, {"text": "And at 55, which is a motion filed for dismissal by FMC, they confessed that they had only been able to find one single instance of infringement up to a time or after the patent had expired.", "start": 249.835, "stop": 267.944, "duration": 18.11, "cleanText": [["and", "at", "which", "be", "a", "motion", "file", "for", "dismissal", "by", "fmc", "they", "confess", "that", "they", "have", "only", "be", "able", "to", "find", "one", "single", "instance", "of", "infringement", "up", "to", "a", "time", "or", "after", "the", "patent", "have", "expire"]]}, {"text": "What happened commercially was that the Walker people got into this business much later than FMC.", "start": 267.944, "stop": 275.846, "duration": 7.9, "cleanText": [["what", "happen", "commercially", "be", "that", "the", "walker", "people", "get", "into", "this", "business", "much", "later", "than", "fmc"]]}, {"text": "By 1954, they had developed what they called sparger and this appears at page 74 of the record, which used a -- what they believed to be a non-clogging type of diffuser.", "start": 275.846, "stop": 289.113, "duration": 13.27, "cleanText": [["by", "they", "have", "develop", "what", "they", "call", "sparger", "and", "this", "appear", "at", "page", "of", "the", "record", "which", "use", "a", "what", "they", "believe", "to", "be", "a", "non", "clog", "type", "of", "diffuser"]]}, {"text": "So that it did not have to be cleaned and therefore it did not have to be lifted out.", "start": 289.113, "stop": 293.417, "duration": 4.3, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "it", "do", "not", "have", "to", "be", "clean", "and", "therefore", "it", "do", "not", "have", "to", "be", "lift", "out"]]}, {"text": "But they were not able to convince the municipalities of this and after all, there are some reasons for that because you have to convince somebody that five years from now, he's not going to have to clean something that he wants to be convinced about.", "start": 293.417, "stop": 307.34, "duration": 13.92, "cleanText": [["but", "they", "we", "be", "not", "able", "to", "convince", "the", "municipality", "of", "this", "and", "after", "all", "there", "be", "some", "reason", "for", "that", "because", "you", "have", "to", "convince", "somebody", "that", "five", "year", "from", "now", "he", "be", "not", "go", "to", "have", "to", "clean", "something", "that", "he", "want", "to", "be", "convince", "about"]]}, {"text": "And the -- at any rate, Walker was unable to make much of the penetration into the field because of the lifting -- this -- the action lifter.", "start": 307.34, "stop": 319.361, "duration": 12.02, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "at", "any", "rate", "walker", "be", "unable", "to", "make", "much", "of", "the", "penetration", "into", "the", "field", "because", "of", "the", "lifting", "this", "the", "action", "lifter"]]}, {"text": "However, about 1956, the Walker people, who remains not described in the record and I don't know what it was, got a wind of the fact that there might have been a prior public use.", "start": 319.361, "stop": 335.439, "duration": 16.08, "cleanText": [["however", "about", "the", "walker", "people", "who", "remain", "not", "describe", "in", "the", "record", "and", "i", "do", "not", "know", "what", "it", "be", "get", "a", "wind", "of", "the", "fact", "that", "there", "might", "have", "be", "a", "prior", "public", "use"]]}, {"text": "And the patent was applied for on February 2nd, 1942 and they've got wind of an earlier device more than a year before, sold by the plaintiff but no actual information.", "start": 335.439, "stop": 350.332, "duration": 14.89, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "patent", "be", "apply", "for", "on", "february", "nd", "and", "they", "have", "get", "wind", "of", "an", "early", "device", "more", "than", "a", "year", "before", "sell", "by", "the", "plaintiff", "but", "no", "actual", "information"]]}, {"text": "But they wrote frankly, a letter to FMC which appears in page 16 of the record, pointing out that they had heard this and asking them to investigate.", "start": 350.332, "stop": 364.148, "duration": 13.82, "cleanText": [["but", "they", "write", "frankly", "a", "letter", "to", "fmc", "which", "appear", "in", "page", "of", "the", "record", "point", "out", "that", "they", "have", "hear", "this", "and", "ask", "them", "to", "investigate"]]}, {"text": "FMC replied, the reply is not in the record but at page 62 in the pleadings, it appears that they simply denied any responsibility in looking into the matter and they didn't.", "start": 364.148, "stop": 375.412, "duration": 11.26, "cleanText": [["fmc", "reply", "the", "reply", "be", "not", "in", "the", "record", "but", "at", "page", "in", "the", "pleading", "it", "appear", "that", "they", "simply", "deny", "any", "responsibility", "in", "look", "into", "the", "matter", "and", "they", "do", "not"]]}, {"text": "However, Walker got some courage up and sold an infringing device to the City of Houston, in 19 -- in or about 1960.", "start": 375.412, "stop": 386.53, "duration": 11.12, "cleanText": [["however", "walker", "get", "some", "courage", "up", "and", "sell", "an", "infringing", "device", "to", "the", "city", "of", "houston", "in", "in", "or", "about"]]}, {"text": "And in June of 1960, the suit from which this arises was brought against Walker and Chicago alleging infringement.", "start": 386.53, "stop": 397.546, "duration": 11.02, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "june", "of", "the", "suit", "from", "which", "this", "arise", "be", "bring", "against", "walker", "and", "chicago", "allege", "infringement"]]}, {"text": "Now, that was only two and a half months before the patent expired.", "start": 397.546, "stop": 402.59, "duration": 5.04, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "be", "only", "two", "and", "a", "half", "month", "before", "the", "patent", "expire"]]}, {"text": "The process of discovering followed, and it was not until the winter of 1962, that we obtained from the plaintiff, the documents which are in the record at page 21 to 27 which showed that prior to February 2nd, 1941, there was an operation at the Hunter Airbase in Savannah, Georgia an aeration system involving these lifter arms.", "start": 402.59, "stop": 434.917, "duration": 32.33, "cleanText": [["the", "process", "of", "discover", "follow", "and", "it", "be", "not", "until", "the", "winter", "of", "that", "we", "obtain", "from", "the", "plaintiff", "the", "document", "which", "be", "in", "the", "record", "at", "page", "to", "which", "show", "that", "prior", "to", "february", "nd", "there", "be", "an", "operation", "at", "the", "hunter", "airbase", "in", "savannah", "georgia", "an", "aeration", "system", "involve", "these", "lifter", "arm"]]}, {"text": "That came hard and I'm not going to go into great details of what happened but there was a great deal of evasive answering of interrogatories until these documents came out.", "start": 434.917, "stop": 446.155, "duration": 11.24, "cleanText": [["that", "come", "hard", "and", "I", "be", "not", "go", "to", "go", "into", "great", "detail", "of", "what", "happen", "but", "there", "be", "a", "great", "deal", "of", "evasive", "answering", "of", "interrogatory", "until", "these", "document", "come", "out"]]}, {"text": "And even then, it was maintained by FMC that was not a prior use because the claims of most of them call for these presence of some means of pulling out the diffuser tube, because they had supplied the crane, although at page 40 of the record, they admitted that the cranes were there and ready for use and at page 62 in the amended complaint, it was alleged that the -- they were there and that was admitted by the motion to strike.", "start": 446.155, "stop": 477.127, "duration": 30.97, "cleanText": [["and", "even", "then", "it", "be", "maintain", "by", "fmc", "that", "be", "not", "a", "prior", "use", "because", "the", "claim", "of", "most", "of", "them", "call", "for", "these", "presence", "of", "some", "mean", "of", "pull", "out", "the", "diffuser", "tube", "because", "they", "have", "supply", "the", "crane", "although", "at", "page", "of", "the", "record", "they", "admit", "that", "the", "crane", "we", "be", "there", "and", "ready", "for", "use", "and", "at", "page", "in", "the", "amended", "complaint", "it", "be", "allege", "that", "the", "they", "we", "be", "there", "and", "that", "be", "admit", "by", "the", "motion", "to", "strike"]]}, {"text": "Now, that was followed in September of 1962 by a motion for summary judgment on the part of defendant, alleging that there was a prior public use, and asking that the complaint be dismissed for that.", "start": 477.127, "stop": 496.84, "duration": 19.71, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "be", "follow", "in", "september", "of", "by", "a", "motion", "for", "summary", "judgment", "on", "the", "part", "of", "defendant", "allege", "that", "there", "be", "a", "prior", "public", "use", "and", "ask", "that", "the", "complaint", "be", "dismiss", "for", "that"]]}, {"text": "In view of the fact that there was a good deal of -- well, on October 5th of that year, a month later, the plaintiff filed an affidavit purporting to answer the question of prior public use and as a result on October 18th, these dates have some importance to the sequence and that's why I'm going into them.", "start": 496.84, "stop": 517.846, "duration": 21.01, "cleanText": [["in", "view", "of", "the", "fact", "that", "there", "be", "a", "good", "deal", "of", "well", "on", "october", "th", "of", "that", "year", "a", "month", "later", "the", "plaintiff", "file", "an", "affidavit", "purport", "to", "answer", "the", "question", "of", "prior", "public", "use", "and", "as", "a", "result", "on", "october", "th", "these", "date", "have", "some", "importance", "to", "the", "sequence", "and", "that", "be", "why", "I", "be", "go", "into", "them"]]}, {"text": "The depositions were taken and at the beginning of the deposition, the plaintiff announced that they were going to move to dismiss their complaint with prejudice and would we want to take the depositions anyway.", "start": 517.846, "stop": 529.386, "duration": 11.54, "cleanText": [["the", "deposition", "we", "be", "take", "and", "at", "the", "beginning", "of", "the", "deposition", "the", "plaintiff", "announce", "that", "they", "we", "be", "go", "to", "move", "to", "dismiss", "their", "complaint", "with", "prejudice", "and", "would", "we", "want", "to", "take", "the", "deposition", "anyway"]]}, {"text": "Well the depositions were taken, they confirmed what I have said to the court, and the -- then the plaintiff did moved to dismiss and that motion was granted in February of 1963, at which time our motion for attorney's fees was denied and our motion to file in the amended counterclaim was granted which was done, that counterclaim appears at page 71 of the record.", "start": 529.386, "stop": 557.557, "duration": 28.17, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "deposition", "we", "be", "take", "they", "confirm", "what", "i", "have", "say", "to", "the", "court", "and", "the", "then", "the", "plaintiff", "do", "move", "to", "dismiss", "and", "that", "motion", "be", "grant", "in", "february", "of", "at", "which", "time", "our", "motion", "for", "attorney", "s", "fee", "be", "deny", "and", "our", "motion", "to", "file", "in", "the", "amended", "counterclaim", "be", "grant", "which", "be", "do", "that", "counterclaim", "appear", "at", "page", "of", "the", "record"]]}, {"text": "Later in June, a second amended counterclaim was filed and it was -- it was a motion to dismiss and that motion was granted in October.", "start": 557.557, "stop": 566.036, "duration": 8.48, "cleanText": [["later", "in", "june", "a", "second", "amended", "counterclaim", "be", "file", "and", "it", "be", "it", "be", "a", "motion", "to", "dismiss", "and", "that", "motion", "be", "grant", "in", "october"]]}, {"text": "Now, so far as the law on the antitrust aspects of this case are concerned, I'm going to touch fairly lightly because I think Mr. Friedman will cover it in more detail and I don't want to trespass or overlap.", "start": 566.036, "stop": 583.599, "duration": 17.56, "cleanText": [["now", "so", "far", "as", "the", "law", "on", "the", "antitrust", "aspect", "of", "this", "case", "be", "concern", "I", "be", "go", "to", "touch", "fairly", "lightly", "because", "i", "think", "mr", "friedman", "will", "cover", "it", "in", "more", "detail", "and", "i", "do", "not", "want", "to", "trespass", "or", "overlap"]]}, {"text": "But I will say this much, the -- it's very strange that the Court of Appeals decided this case against us on the basis of several cases, none of which is cited in this Court by our opponents which is relied upon.", "start": 583.599, "stop": 601.75, "duration": 18.15, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "will", "say", "this", "much", "the", "it", "be", "very", "strange", "that", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "decide", "this", "case", "against", "us", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "several", "case", "none", "of", "which", "be", "cite", "in", "this", "court", "by", "our", "opponent", "which", "be", "rely", "upon"]]}, {"text": "The thrust of the argument of respondents is that no relief can be had here.", "start": 601.75, "stop": 610.668, "duration": 8.92, "cleanText": [["the", "thrust", "of", "the", "argument", "of", "respondent", "be", "that", "no", "relief", "can", "be", "have", "here"]]}, {"text": "Because of now for the first time, the question of relevant market is raised, which was not raised on motion, it was not raised as a special pleading and it is raised here for the first time.", "start": 610.668, "stop": 626.384, "duration": 15.72, "cleanText": [["because", "of", "now", "for", "the", "first", "time", "the", "question", "of", "relevant", "market", "be", "raise", "which", "be", "not", "raise", "on", "motion", "it", "be", "not", "raise", "as", "a", "special", "pleading", "and", "it", "be", "raise", "here", "for", "the", "first", "time"]]}, {"text": "The basis of our understanding of the counterclaim is that this Court in the Hazel Atlas - Hartford-Empire case, on the basis of a fraud far less serious than the one here because it involved only an article which was in fact true, although represented to have been written on a different way than it was written.", "start": 626.384, "stop": 652.447, "duration": 26.06, "cleanText": [["the", "basis", "of", "our", "understanding", "of", "the", "counterclaim", "be", "that", "this", "court", "in", "the", "hazel", "atlas", "hartford", "empire", "case", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "a", "fraud", "far", "less", "serious", "than", "the", "one", "here", "because", "it", "involve", "only", "an", "article", "which", "be", "in", "fact", "true", "although", "represent", "to", "have", "be", "write", "on", "a", "different", "way", "than", "it", "be", "write"]]}, {"text": "Not only held that patent invalid, but permitted a reopening of cases which had been decided years before.", "start": 652.447, "stop": 662.041, "duration": 9.59, "cleanText": [["not", "only", "hold", "that", "patent", "invalid", "but", "permit", "a", "reopening", "of", "case", "which", "have", "be", "decide", "year", "before"]]}, {"text": "And in the Shawkee case, which is also in our brief, directed that recovery should be had on account of this improper use of the patent, which recovery was in the Hartford against Shawkee case in 163 F.2d actually granted, including attorney's fees.", "start": 662.041, "stop": 684.283, "duration": 22.24, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "the", "shawkee", "case", "which", "be", "also", "in", "our", "brief", "direct", "that", "recovery", "should", "be", "have", "on", "account", "of", "this", "improper", "use", "of", "the", "patent", "which", "recovery", "be", "in", "the", "hartford", "against", "shawkee", "case", "in", "fd", "actually", "grant", "include", "attorney", "s", "fee"]]}, {"text": "In that case, lost business was not covered because they said that the proof on it was too conjectory.", "start": 684.283, "stop": 693.3, "duration": 9.02, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "case", "lose", "business", "be", "not", "cover", "because", "they", "say", "that", "the", "proof", "on", "it", "be", "too", "conjectory"]]}, {"text": "Now, what our opponents really come down to in this case is, that they assert that we are seeking to have the patent -- at least, this is what the Court of Appeals held on their request, that we are seeking to have a patent thrown out to an adjudication in rem rather in persona which is the ordinary remedy on a patent infringement suit.", "start": 693.3, "stop": 722.41, "duration": 29.11, "cleanText": [["now", "what", "our", "opponent", "really", "come", "down", "to", "in", "this", "case", "be", "that", "they", "assert", "that", "we", "be", "seek", "to", "have", "the", "patent", "at", "least", "this", "be", "what", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "hold", "on", "their", "request", "that", "we", "be", "seek", "to", "have", "a", "patent", "throw", "out", "to", "an", "adjudication", "in", "rem", "rather", "in", "persona", "which", "be", "the", "ordinary", "remedy", "on", "a", "patent", "infringement", "suit"]]}, {"text": "Actually, nothing of the kind was involved here, the patent expired several years before the judge dismissed our counterclaim.", "start": 722.41, "stop": 733.176, "duration": 10.77, "cleanText": [["actually", "nothing", "of", "the", "kind", "be", "involve", "here", "the", "patent", "expire", "several", "year", "before", "the", "judge", "dismiss", "our", "counterclaim"]]}, {"text": "And why -- anybody should think that it was necessary to throw out or have declared invalid the patent which had already expired, we don't know and they have not explained.", "start": 733.176, "stop": 748.595, "duration": 15.42, "cleanText": [["and", "why", "anybody", "should", "think", "that", "it", "be", "necessary", "to", "throw", "out", "or", "have", "declare", "invalid", "the", "patent", "which", "have", "already", "expire", "we", "do", "not", "know", "and", "they", "have", "not", "explain"]]}, {"text": "The -- what did they effectively ask is that if this case had gone along, they concede that if we had gone along as in the Hazel-Atlas case and the patent had been found invalid as we had a right to defend against it in the complaint.", "start": 748.595, "stop": 768.73, "duration": 20.13, "cleanText": [["the", "what", "do", "they", "effectively", "ask", "be", "that", "if", "this", "case", "have", "go", "along", "they", "concede", "that", "if", "we", "have", "go", "along", "as", "in", "the", "hazel", "atlas", "case", "and", "the", "patent", "have", "be", "find", "invalid", "as", "we", "have", "a", "right", "to", "defend", "against", "it", "in", "the", "complaint"]]}, {"text": "But then, all of these remedy would have followed.", "start": 768.73, "stop": 771.632, "duration": 2.9, "cleanText": [["but", "then", "all", "of", "these", "remedy", "would", "have", "follow"]]}, {"text": "But since they were permitted over -- in acquisition to our counterclaim to dismiss their complaint that there should be a different rule of law, either no reason is given for such a different rule of law, we don't see any.", "start": 771.632, "stop": 786.8, "duration": 15.17, "cleanText": [["but", "since", "they", "we", "be", "permit", "over", "in", "acquisition", "to", "our", "counterclaim", "to", "dismiss", "their", "complaint", "that", "there", "should", "be", "a", "different", "rule", "of", "law", "either", "no", "reason", "be", "give", "for", "such", "a", "different", "rule", "of", "law", "we", "do", "not", "see", "any"]]}, {"text": "All we ask is that here is somebody who has taken a patent which was improperly obtained from the Government and that is admitted of course in the motion to strike and used it to the detriment of our client.", "start": 786.8, "stop": 804.074, "duration": 17.27, "cleanText": [["all", "we", "ask", "be", "that", "here", "be", "somebody", "who", "have", "take", "a", "patent", "which", "be", "improperly", "obtain", "from", "the", "government", "and", "that", "be", "admit", "of", "course", "in", "the", "motion", "to", "strike", "and", "use", "it", "to", "the", "detriment", "of", "our", "client"]]}, {"text": "And the detriment of the client had clearly shown in the pleadings, four lost jobs are shown and a possible fifth, involving enormous amount of that -- up in that -- scores a thousand of dollars, there's also a showing that other business was probably lost because of the denial of the right to make the action lifters, all of which is a definite damage and all of which accrued solely because plaintiff had in its possession a patent which if the facts had been told to the Patent Office, if there had not been a false oath that was filed, namely that there had been no prior public use, we would not have been faced to it and we would have been able to compete.", "start": 804.074, "stop": 851.281, "duration": 47.21, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "detriment", "of", "the", "client", "have", "clearly", "show", "in", "the", "pleading", "four", "lose", "job", "be", "show", "and", "a", "possible", "fifth", "involve", "enormous", "amount", "of", "that", "up", "in", "that", "score", "a", "thousand", "of", "dollar", "there", "be", "also", "a", "showing", "that", "other", "business", "be", "probably", "lose", "because", "of", "the", "denial", "of", "the", "right", "to", "make", "the", "action", "lifter", "all", "of", "which", "be", "a", "definite", "damage", "and", "all", "of", "which", "accrue", "solely", "because", "plaintiff", "have", "in", "its", "possession", "a", "patent", "which", "if", "the", "fact", "have", "be", "tell", "to", "the", "patent", "office", "if", "there", "have", "not", "be", "a", "false", "oath", "that", "be", "file", "namely", "that", "there", "have", "be", "no", "prior", "public", "use", "we", "would", "not", "have", "be", "face", "to", "it", "and", "we", "would", "have", "be", "able", "to", "compete"]]}, {"text": "There's actually allegations on the -- there are actually allegations on the record showing losses of up in the -- or excess profits to the plaintiff up around $12 million or more, because of this cloning of a patent which they knew or should have known because the acts were there, was invalid.", "start": 851.281, "stop": 871.06, "duration": 19.78, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "actually", "allegation", "on", "the", "there", "be", "actually", "allegation", "on", "the", "record", "showing", "loss", "of", "up", "in", "the", "or", "excess", "profit", "to", "the", "plaintiff", "up", "around", "million", "or", "more", "because", "of", "this", "cloning", "of", "a", "patent", "which", "they", "know", "or", "should", "have", "know", "because", "the", "act", "we", "be", "there", "be", "invalid"]]}, {"text": "No, I'm not going to talk a great length about the matter of relevant market because I think that also comes in Mr. Friedman's area, but I will say this.", "start": 871.06, "stop": 883.994, "duration": 12.93, "cleanText": [["no", "I", "be", "not", "go", "to", "talk", "a", "great", "length", "about", "the", "matter", "of", "relevant", "market", "because", "i", "think", "that", "also", "come", "in", "mr", "friedman", "s", "area", "but", "i", "will", "say", "this"]]}, {"text": "The respondents do not appear to question the fact that wherever there has been any kind of a tying agreement involving a patent, that that is per se a violation of the antitrust law.", "start": 883.994, "stop": 900.508, "duration": 16.51, "cleanText": [["the", "respondent", "do", "not", "appear", "to", "question", "the", "fact", "that", "wherever", "there", "have", "be", "any", "kind", "of", "a", "tying", "agreement", "involve", "a", "patent", "that", "that", "be", "per", "se", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "They say this is not a tying case and I suppose in the classical sense, it is not a tying case because this was a 100% tie where there's -- everything here was unpatented but it was tied to a patent as if it were patented.", "start": 900.508, "stop": 917.252, "duration": 16.74, "cleanText": [["they", "say", "this", "be", "not", "a", "tying", "case", "and", "i", "suppose", "in", "the", "classical", "sense", "it", "be", "not", "a", "tying", "case", "because", "this", "be", "a", "tie", "where", "there", "be", "everything", "here", "be", "unpatented", "but", "it", "be", "tie", "to", "a", "patent", "as", "if", "it", "we", "be", "patent"]]}, {"text": "And why there should be a less severe rule in the case where everything that was sold was really should have been outside of the patent laws, then a case where the -- only a part of what was sold was outside of the patent laws, I don't know.", "start": 917.252, "stop": 933.272, "duration": 16.02, "cleanText": [["and", "why", "there", "should", "be", "a", "less", "severe", "rule", "in", "the", "case", "where", "everything", "that", "be", "sell", "be", "really", "should", "have", "be", "outside", "of", "the", "patent", "law", "then", "a", "case", "where", "the", "only", "a", "part", "of", "what", "be", "sell", "be", "outside", "of", "the", "patent", "law", "i", "do", "not", "know"]]}, {"text": "I also say although the question is not clearly delaminated in the pleadings because while it is the diversity is shown of the two parties, it is not shown where the primary office of the FMC is, although actually it's in California.", "start": 933.272, "stop": 949.826, "duration": 16.55, "cleanText": [["i", "also", "say", "although", "the", "question", "be", "not", "clearly", "delaminated", "in", "the", "pleading", "because", "while", "it", "be", "the", "diversity", "be", "show", "of", "the", "two", "party", "it", "be", "not", "show", "where", "the", "primary", "office", "of", "the", "fmc", "be", "although", "actually", "it", "be", "in", "california"]]}, {"text": "I think there would have been a common law diversity action here for fraud because we were harmed by their fraud.", "start": 949.826, "stop": 955.91, "duration": 6.08, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "there", "would", "have", "be", "a", "common", "law", "diversity", "action", "here", "for", "fraud", "because", "we", "we", "be", "harm", "by", "their", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "However, I don't think that question necessarily has to be considered on diversity which has been pleaded.", "start": 955.91, "stop": 961.961, "duration": 6.05, "cleanText": [["however", "i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "question", "necessarily", "have", "to", "be", "consider", "on", "diversity", "which", "have", "be", "plead"]]}, {"text": "I think that the counterclaim certainly drew out in the transaction pleaded in the original complaint, mainly here was a patent.", "start": 961.961, "stop": 969.527, "duration": 7.57, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "the", "counterclaim", "certainly", "draw", "out", "in", "the", "transaction", "plead", "in", "the", "original", "complaint", "mainly", "here", "be", "a", "patent"]]}, {"text": "They were sued on because of the patent.", "start": 969.527, "stop": 972.501, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["they", "we", "be", "sue", "on", "because", "of", "the", "patent"]]}, {"text": "We were harmed and I think the two transactions are relevant in that respect.", "start": 972.501, "stop": 979.05, "duration": 6.55, "cleanText": [["we", "we", "be", "harm", "and", "i", "think", "the", "two", "transaction", "be", "relevant", "in", "that", "respect"]]}, {"text": "So far as the matter of attorney's fees is concerned, the law of course is clear, the Court may and has discretion to award attorney's fees in an extraordinary case.", "start": 979.05, "stop": 993.279, "duration": 14.23, "cleanText": [["so", "far", "as", "the", "matter", "of", "attorney", "s", "fee", "be", "concern", "the", "law", "of", "course", "be", "clear", "the", "court", "may", "and", "have", "discretion", "to", "award", "attorney", "s", "fee", "in", "an", "extraordinary", "case"]]}, {"text": "I think beyond any question, this is an extraordinary case, the fact that the Court did not let it go to a final proof either on the complaint or on the counterclaim to show that there was actually fraud, to make findings of fact as to fraud.", "start": 993.279, "stop": 1010.023, "duration": 16.74, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "beyond", "any", "question", "this", "be", "an", "extraordinary", "case", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "court", "do", "not", "let", "it", "go", "to", "a", "final", "proof", "either", "on", "the", "complaint", "or", "on", "the", "counterclaim", "to", "show", "that", "there", "be", "actually", "fraud", "to", "make", "finding", "of", "fact", "as", "to", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "I think, there should be no excuse and rather should be in our favor and instead of the Court.", "start": 1010.023, "stop": 1015.817, "duration": 5.79, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "there", "should", "be", "no", "excuse", "and", "rather", "should", "be", "in", "our", "favor", "and", "instead", "of", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "I think you do the discretion, although I think that in view of the Shawkee case, the 163 F.2d, the -- if there is a reversal on the other point, the rulings of this Court in Hartford-Empire and in the directions for Shawkee would clearly cover us and permit the recovery of the attorney's fees as justified on the final outcome of the case.", "start": 1015.817, "stop": 1045.115, "duration": 29.3, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "you", "do", "the", "discretion", "although", "i", "think", "that", "in", "view", "of", "the", "shawkee", "case", "the", "fd", "the", "if", "there", "be", "a", "reversal", "on", "the", "other", "point", "the", "ruling", "of", "this", "court", "in", "hartford", "empire", "and", "in", "the", "direction", "for", "shawkee", "would", "clearly", "cover", "us", "and", "permit", "the", "recovery", "of", "the", "attorney", "s", "fee", "as", "justify", "on", "the", "final", "outcome", "of", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "So when I say that while this is an extraordinary case, I don't know of any other fraud of this nature that was not reimbursed by attorney's fees.", "start": 1045.115, "stop": 1054.104, "duration": 8.99, "cleanText": [["so", "when", "i", "say", "that", "while", "this", "be", "an", "extraordinary", "case", "i", "do", "not", "know", "of", "any", "other", "fraud", "of", "this", "nature", "that", "be", "not", "reimburse", "by", "attorney", "s", "fee"]]}, {"text": "This may or may not be moot depending on what happens to the other issue.", "start": 1054.104, "stop": 1066.898, "duration": 12.79, "cleanText": [["this", "may", "or", "may", "not", "be", "moot", "depend", "on", "what", "happen", "to", "the", "other", "issue"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Friedman.", "start": 1066.898, "stop": 1068.11, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["mr", "friedman"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.", "start": 1068.11, "stop": 1071.541, "duration": 3.43, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "The United States is participating in this case as an amicus because of its disagreement with the ruling below, that a charge of monopolization and violation of Section 2 of the Sherman Act cannot be predicated upon the enforcement of a patent that was procured by fraud on the Patent Office.", "start": 1071.541, "stop": 1091.481, "duration": 19.94, "cleanText": [["the", "united", "state", "be", "participate", "in", "this", "case", "as", "an", "amicus", "because", "of", "its", "disagreement", "with", "the", "ruling", "below", "that", "a", "charge", "of", "monopolization", "and", "violation", "of", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "can", "not", "be", "predicate", "upon", "the", "enforcement", "of", "a", "patent", "that", "be", "procure", "by", "fraud", "on", "the", "patent", "office"]]}, {"text": "And I want to emphasize that the outset as my colleague has done, that as the case comes here -- it comes on the dismissal of the counterclaim.", "start": 1091.481, "stop": 1100.057, "duration": 8.58, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "want", "to", "emphasize", "that", "the", "outset", "as", "my", "colleague", "have", "do", "that", "as", "the", "case", "come", "here", "it", "come", "on", "the", "dismissal", "of", "the", "counterclaim"]]}, {"text": "So we must assume for the purposes of argument that the petitioner can prove what he alleges, there are some suggestion by our opponents that in fact this doesn't amount to fraud.", "start": 1100.057, "stop": 1112.029, "duration": 11.97, "cleanText": [["so", "we", "must", "assume", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "argument", "that", "the", "petitioner", "can", "prove", "what", "he", "allege", "there", "be", "some", "suggestion", "by", "our", "opponent", "that", "in", "fact", "this", "do", "not", "amount", "to", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "I think that's a question that's not in the case at this point.", "start": 1112.029, "stop": 1115.424, "duration": 3.39, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "a", "question", "that", "be", "not", "in", "the", "case", "at", "this", "point"]]}, {"text": "We take two positions here and I might just mention in passing, we take no position on the propriety of the denial of the award of attorney's fees, we take two positions here.", "start": 1115.424, "stop": 1125.479, "duration": 10.06, "cleanText": [["we", "take", "two", "position", "here", "and", "i", "might", "just", "mention", "in", "passing", "we", "take", "no", "position", "on", "the", "propriety", "of", "the", "denial", "of", "the", "award", "of", "attorney", "s", "fee", "we", "take", "two", "position", "here"]]}, {"text": "First, we think that the stated basis upon which the Court of Appeals and the District Court dismissed this counterclaim, that the maintenance of this suit would amount to an illegal attempt to annul a patent, not permissible because only the United States may bring such as suit, is plainly an untenable basis for its decision.", "start": 1125.479, "stop": 1145.983, "duration": 20.5, "cleanText": [["first", "we", "think", "that", "the", "stated", "basis", "upon", "which", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "and", "the", "district", "court", "dismiss", "this", "counterclaim", "that", "the", "maintenance", "of", "this", "suit", "would", "amount", "to", "an", "illegal", "attempt", "to", "annul", "a", "patent", "not", "permissible", "because", "only", "the", "united", "state", "may", "bring", "such", "as", "suit", "be", "plainly", "an", "untenable", "basis", "for", "its", "decision"]]}, {"text": "And indeed, as far as we can read the respondent's brief, they no longer really seek to defend that ground.", "start": 1145.983, "stop": 1152.434, "duration": 6.45, "cleanText": [["and", "indeed", "as", "far", "as", "we", "can", "read", "the", "respondent", "s", "brief", "they", "no", "longer", "really", "seek", "to", "defend", "that", "ground"]]}, {"text": "And secondly, we shall argue that passing that point for the moment, the complaint in this case does state a violation of Section 2 of the Sherman Act and that the petitioner therefore should have been permitted to go to trial on that issue.", "start": 1152.434, "stop": 1169.489, "duration": 17.06, "cleanText": [["and", "secondly", "we", "shall", "argue", "that", "pass", "that", "point", "for", "the", "moment", "the", "complaint", "in", "this", "case", "do", "state", "a", "violation", "of", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "and", "that", "the", "petitioner", "therefore", "should", "have", "be", "permit", "to", "go", "to", "trial", "on", "that", "issue"]]}, {"text": "Now I'd like first to discuss the grounds given by the Court of Appeals, that is, they said is a well-settled rule that only the United States may bring an action to annul or cancel a patent.", "start": 1169.489, "stop": 1182.137, "duration": 12.65, "cleanText": [["now", "I", "would", "like", "first", "to", "discuss", "the", "ground", "give", "by", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "that", "be", "they", "say", "be", "a", "well", "settle", "rule", "that", "only", "the", "united", "state", "may", "bring", "an", "action", "to", "annul", "or", "cancel", "a", "patent"]]}, {"text": "And they said that to permit this action to go forward where the claim is, that the patent was illegally procured would do violence to that rule.", "start": 1182.137, "stop": 1191.704, "duration": 9.57, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "say", "that", "to", "permit", "this", "action", "to", "go", "forward", "where", "the", "claim", "be", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "illegally", "procure", "would", "do", "violence", "to", "that", "rule"]]}, {"text": "We think the short answer to that is that no relief that would be given in this case would in effect annul the patent.", "start": 1191.704, "stop": 1199.15, "duration": 7.45, "cleanText": [["we", "think", "the", "short", "answer", "to", "that", "be", "that", "no", "relief", "that", "would", "be", "give", "in", "this", "case", "would", "in", "effect", "annul", "the", "patent"]]}, {"text": "And we have set forth in our brief the various authorities in favor of that proposition and all I would like to do here is to invite the Court's attention to another case which unfortunately we did not cite which we think is virtually dispositive in this point.", "start": 1199.15, "stop": 1214.958, "duration": 15.81, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "have", "set", "forth", "in", "our", "brief", "the", "various", "authority", "in", "favor", "of", "that", "proposition", "and", "all", "i", "would", "like", "to", "do", "here", "be", "to", "invite", "the", "court", "s", "attention", "to", "another", "case", "which", "unfortunately", "we", "do", "not", "cite", "which", "we", "think", "be", "virtually", "dispositive", "in", "this", "point"]]}, {"text": "And that as this Court's opinion in the first Gypsum case, United States v. United States Gypsum Company in 333 U.S. 364.", "start": 1214.958, "stop": 1226.238, "duration": 11.28, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "as", "this", "court", "s", "opinion", "in", "the", "first", "gypsum", "case", "united", "state", "v", "united", "state", "gypsum", "company", "in", "us"]]}, {"text": "That was a civil antitrust case brought by the Government alleging violations of Section 1 and 2 of the Sherman Act and the claim was an illegal combination in conspiracy to restrain and monopolize, accomplished through various patent licensing practices.", "start": 1226.238, "stop": 1244.802, "duration": 18.56, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "a", "civil", "antitrust", "case", "bring", "by", "the", "government", "allege", "violation", "of", "section", "and", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "and", "the", "claim", "be", "an", "illegal", "combination", "in", "conspiracy", "to", "restrain", "and", "monopolize", "accomplish", "through", "various", "patent", "licensing", "practice"]]}, {"text": "During the course of the proceedings in the District Court, the defendants conceded that if they didn't have the protection of the patents, their practices would be illegal.", "start": 1244.802, "stop": 1257.072, "duration": 12.27, "cleanText": [["during", "the", "course", "of", "the", "proceeding", "in", "the", "district", "court", "the", "defendant", "concede", "that", "if", "they", "do", "not", "have", "the", "protection", "of", "the", "patent", "their", "practice", "would", "be", "illegal"]]}, {"text": "But they claim the patents gave them a full defense.", "start": 1257.072, "stop": 1260.082, "duration": 3.01, "cleanText": [["but", "they", "claim", "the", "patent", "give", "them", "a", "full", "defense"]]}, {"text": "At this point, the Government move to amend its complaint to add another paragraph alleging that the patents themselves were invalid for a large number of grounds, seven or eight grounds.", "start": 1260.082, "stop": 1271.029, "duration": 10.95, "cleanText": [["at", "this", "point", "the", "government", "move", "to", "amend", "its", "complaint", "to", "add", "another", "paragraph", "allege", "that", "the", "patent", "themselves", "we", "be", "invalid", "for", "a", "large", "number", "of", "ground", "seven", "or", "eight", "ground"]]}, {"text": "The District Court refused to permit that amendment.", "start": 1271.029, "stop": 1273.838, "duration": 2.81, "cleanText": [["the", "district", "court", "refuse", "to", "permit", "that", "amendment"]]}, {"text": "The District Court thought that allowing such a claim in the suit wouldn't effect amount to a prohibited attempt by the United States in that case to challenge the patent and to secure its annulment.", "start": 1273.838, "stop": 1286.622, "duration": 12.78, "cleanText": [["the", "district", "court", "think", "that", "allow", "such", "a", "claim", "in", "the", "suit", "would", "not", "effect", "amount", "to", "a", "prohibit", "attempt", "by", "the", "united", "state", "in", "that", "case", "to", "challenge", "the", "patent", "and", "to", "secure", "its", "annulment"]]}, {"text": "Now, this Court in its decision in the Gypsum case, although recognizing that that issue was not crucial as the way the case came out, nevertheless went out of its way, specifically to reject that ruling, pointing out it would be most unfortunate to leave as a precedent.", "start": 1286.622, "stop": 1302.877, "duration": 16.25, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "court", "in", "its", "decision", "in", "the", "gypsum", "case", "although", "recognize", "that", "that", "issue", "be", "not", "crucial", "as", "the", "way", "the", "case", "come", "out", "nevertheless", "go", "out", "of", "its", "way", "specifically", "to", "reject", "that", "ruling", "point", "out", "it", "would", "be", "most", "unfortunate", "to", "leave", "as", "a", "precedent"]]}, {"text": "And I'd like to read to the Court two sentences from its decision on this point which is at page 387, at 333 United States and the Court stated.", "start": 1302.877, "stop": 1313.243, "duration": 10.37, "cleanText": [["and", "I", "would", "like", "to", "read", "to", "the", "court", "two", "sentence", "from", "its", "decision", "on", "this", "point", "which", "be", "at", "page", "at", "united", "state", "and", "the", "court", "state"]]}, {"text": "The United States does not claim that the patents are invalid because they have been employed in violation of the Sherman Act, and that a decree should issue canceling the patents; rather, the Government charges that the defendants have violated the Sherman Act because they granted licenses under patents which in fact were invalid.", "start": 1313.243, "stop": 1331.765, "duration": 18.52, "cleanText": [["the", "united", "state", "do", "not", "claim", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "invalid", "because", "they", "have", "be", "employ", "in", "violation", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "and", "that", "a", "decree", "should", "issue", "cancel", "the", "patent", "rather", "the", "government", "charge", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "violate", "the", "sherman", "act", "because", "they", "grant", "license", "under", "patent", "which", "in", "fact", "we", "be", "invalid"]]}, {"text": "Now I come particularly emphasize the second sentence.", "start": 1331.765, "stop": 1334.945, "duration": 3.18, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "come", "particularly", "emphasize", "the", "second", "sentence"]]}, {"text": "If the Government were to succeed in showing that the patents were in fact invalid, such a finding would not itself result in a judgment for cancellation of the patents.", "start": 1334.945, "stop": 1346.179, "duration": 11.23, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "government", "we", "be", "to", "succeed", "in", "show", "that", "the", "patent", "we", "be", "in", "fact", "invalid", "such", "a", "finding", "would", "not", "itself", "result", "in", "a", "judgment", "for", "cancellation", "of", "the", "patent"]]}, {"text": "And we think this same reasoning is fully applicable in this case.", "start": 1346.179, "stop": 1350.611, "duration": 4.43, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "think", "this", "same", "reasoning", "be", "fully", "applicable", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "Here, the petitioner is not claiming that the patent is invalid because it was illegally used to monopolize or seeking cancellation of the patent, rather the charge is that there was a violation of the Sherman Act because the conduct was based on a patent that was invalid.", "start": 1350.611, "stop": 1368.233, "duration": 17.62, "cleanText": [["here", "the", "petitioner", "be", "not", "claim", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "invalid", "because", "it", "be", "illegally", "use", "to", "monopolize", "or", "seek", "cancellation", "of", "the", "patent", "rather", "the", "charge", "be", "that", "there", "be", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "because", "the", "conduct", "be", "base", "on", "a", "patent", "that", "be", "invalid"]]}, {"text": "And just as in the Gypsum case, we think it quite clear here that if the ultimate result in this case is a finding of monopolization based on a finding that the patent was obtained by fraud, such a finding and the words of Gypsum would not itself result in a judgment for cancellation of the patent.", "start": 1368.233, "stop": 1389.097, "duration": 20.86, "cleanText": [["and", "just", "as", "in", "the", "gypsum", "case", "we", "think", "it", "quite", "clear", "here", "that", "if", "the", "ultimate", "result", "in", "this", "case", "be", "a", "finding", "of", "monopolization", "base", "on", "a", "finding", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "obtain", "by", "fraud", "such", "a", "finding", "and", "the", "word", "of", "gypsum", "would", "not", "itself", "result", "in", "a", "judgment", "for", "cancellation", "of", "the", "patent"]]}, {"text": "So we think the stated basis for the decision is plainly untenable.", "start": 1389.097, "stop": 1393.26, "duration": 4.16, "cleanText": [["so", "we", "think", "the", "stated", "basis", "for", "the", "decision", "be", "plainly", "untenable"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because there is a difference for what it's worth, the -- in Gypsum, the United States once was the party and that --", "start": 1393.26, "stop": 1399.004, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["because", "there", "be", "a", "difference", "for", "what", "it", "be", "worth", "the", "in", "gypsum", "the", "united", "state", "once", "be", "the", "party", "and", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was the party.", "start": 1399.004, "stop": 1399.866, "duration": 0.86, "cleanText": [["be", "the", "party"]]}, {"text": "That's correct Mr. Justice --", "start": 1399.866, "stop": 1400.905, "duration": 1.04, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "mr", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "And that would --", "start": 1400.905, "stop": 1401.163, "duration": 0.26, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "would"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- but the -- the rationale it seems to us is equally applicable because in Gypsum, the Court said that the United States could not bring the suit because the District Court erroneously believe that that was not --", "start": 1401.163, "stop": 1412.829, "duration": 11.67, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "the", "rationale", "it", "seem", "to", "us", "be", "equally", "applicable", "because", "in", "gypsum", "the", "court", "say", "that", "the", "united", "state", "could", "not", "bring", "the", "suit", "because", "the", "district", "court", "erroneously", "believe", "that", "that", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1412.829, "stop": 1412.852, "duration": 0.02, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- permitted even to the United States and this Court rejected that --", "start": 1412.852, "stop": 1416.347, "duration": 3.49, "cleanText": [["permit", "even", "to", "the", "united", "state", "and", "this", "court", "reject", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1416.347, "stop": 1416.429, "duration": 0.08, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- and said, No, this is not an attempt to annul or cancel a patent.", "start": 1416.429, "stop": 1419.911, "duration": 3.48, "cleanText": [["and", "say", "no", "this", "be", "not", "an", "attempt", "to", "annul", "or", "cancel", "a", "patent"]]}, {"text": "Now, in --", "start": 1419.911, "stop": 1421.87, "duration": 1.96, "cleanText": [["now", "in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "May I ask Mr. Friedman --", "start": 1421.87, "stop": 1422.709, "duration": 0.84, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "ask", "mr", "friedman"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1422.709, "stop": 1422.761, "duration": 0.05, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- before you can issue -- would you mind briefly stating what you think will have to be tried if you prevail on the statement of fact.", "start": 1422.761, "stop": 1430.553, "duration": 7.79, "cleanText": [["before", "you", "can", "issue", "would", "you", "mind", "briefly", "state", "what", "you", "think", "will", "have", "to", "be", "try", "if", "you", "prevail", "on", "the", "statement", "of", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, I'd like --", "start": 1430.553, "stop": 1431.567, "duration": 1.01, "cleanText": [["yes", "I", "would", "like"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "Don't bother now, before you finish.", "start": 1431.567, "stop": 1433.135, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["do", "not", "bother", "now", "before", "you", "finish"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I'll tell you right now Mr. Justice.", "start": 1433.135, "stop": 1434.999, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "will", "tell", "you", "right", "now", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "I think what will have to be shown are the following -- one, the allegation of the complaint that the patent was obtained by knowingly misrepresenting to the Patent Office that there was in fact no prior invention more than a year of the date of filing, that's the first allegation.", "start": 1434.999, "stop": 1452.706, "duration": 17.71, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "what", "will", "have", "to", "be", "show", "be", "the", "follow", "one", "the", "allegation", "of", "the", "complaint", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "obtain", "by", "knowingly", "misrepresent", "to", "the", "patent", "office", "that", "there", "be", "in", "fact", "no", "prior", "invention", "more", "than", "a", "year", "of", "the", "date", "of", "filing", "that", "be", "the", "first", "allegation"]]}, {"text": "Secondly, they will have to be show not only that they had the patent but that they enforced it against the petitioner in this case.", "start": 1452.706, "stop": 1459.933, "duration": 7.23, "cleanText": [["secondly", "they", "will", "have", "to", "be", "show", "not", "only", "that", "they", "have", "the", "patent", "but", "that", "they", "enforce", "it", "against", "the", "petitioner", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "No, that's not merely the possession of the patent but the allegations that they make, that they lost a great deal of business.", "start": 1459.933, "stop": 1465.382, "duration": 5.45, "cleanText": [["no", "that", "be", "not", "merely", "the", "possession", "of", "the", "patent", "but", "the", "allegation", "that", "they", "make", "that", "they", "lose", "a", "great", "deal", "of", "business"]]}, {"text": "In fact, they were actually excluded from the markets for the (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 1465.382, "stop": 1468.891, "duration": 3.51, "cleanText": [["in", "fact", "they", "we", "be", "actually", "exclude", "from", "the", "market", "for", "the", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Won't they just come to prove the Section 2 case?", "start": 1468.891, "stop": 1471.529, "duration": 2.64, "cleanText": [["will", "not", "they", "just", "come", "to", "prove", "the", "section", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1471.529, "stop": 1472.743, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Whatever the elements are in the Section 2 case --", "start": 1472.743, "stop": 1474.119, "duration": 1.38, "cleanText": [["whatever", "the", "element", "be", "in", "the", "section", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right, yes.", "start": 1474.119, "stop": 1474.823, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- and have to prove it.", "start": 1474.823, "stop": 1476.083, "duration": 1.26, "cleanText": [["and", "have", "to", "prove", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "William J. Brennan, Jr.", "textObjs": [{"text": "What about relevant market?", "start": 1476.083, "stop": 1477.666, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["what", "about", "relevant", "market"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, on the relevant market Mr. Justice -- we have an alternative argument.", "start": 1477.666, "stop": 1483.931, "duration": 6.27, "cleanText": [["well", "on", "the", "relevant", "market", "mr", "justice", "we", "have", "an", "alternative", "argument"]]}, {"text": "The first argument we have is that at least in this kind of a case, the allegations here is sufficient to allow them to go to try, that's our first argument.", "start": 1483.931, "stop": 1493.649, "duration": 9.72, "cleanText": [["the", "first", "argument", "we", "have", "be", "that", "at", "least", "in", "this", "kind", "of", "a", "case", "the", "allegation", "here", "be", "sufficient", "to", "allow", "them", "to", "go", "to", "try", "that", "be", "our", "first", "argument"]]}, {"text": "This was not the basis, relevant market on which the lower court decided the case.", "start": 1493.649, "stop": 1498.362, "duration": 4.71, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "not", "the", "basis", "relevant", "market", "on", "which", "the", "low", "court", "decide", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "The complaint charges monopolization -- if it felt necessary to define the relevant market in this type of a case, it seems to me that's a matter that properly can be developed at further pretrial proceedings, possibly in other amendment of the complaint.", "start": 1498.362, "stop": 1514.068, "duration": 15.71, "cleanText": [["the", "complaint", "charge", "monopolization", "if", "it", "felt", "necessary", "to", "define", "the", "relevant", "market", "in", "this", "type", "of", "a", "case", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "be", "a", "matter", "that", "properly", "can", "be", "develop", "at", "further", "pretrial", "proceeding", "possibly", "in", "other", "amendment", "of", "the", "complaint"]]}, {"text": "Now that's our first position.", "start": 1514.068, "stop": 1515.763, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "be", "our", "first", "position"]]}, {"text": "If we -- I also plan to discuss briefly our argument that we think in this kind of a case, there is no need to define the relevant market.", "start": 1515.763, "stop": 1524.14, "duration": 8.38, "cleanText": [["if", "we", "i", "also", "plan", "to", "discuss", "briefly", "our", "argument", "that", "we", "think", "in", "this", "kind", "of", "a", "case", "there", "be", "no", "need", "to", "define", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "And may I say, to be clear on this, when I say this kind of a case, I learned it myself specifically to the situation, where a claim of illegal monopolization rest on the enforcement of a patent procured by fraud.", "start": 1524.14, "stop": 1538.138, "duration": 14, "cleanText": [["and", "may", "i", "say", "to", "be", "clear", "on", "this", "when", "i", "say", "this", "kind", "of", "a", "case", "i", "learn", "it", "myself", "specifically", "to", "the", "situation", "where", "a", "claim", "of", "illegal", "monopolization", "rest", "on", "the", "enforcement", "of", "a", "patent", "procure", "by", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "Now I'm planning to come to that in a few minutes and to develop the latter point of them --", "start": 1538.138, "stop": 1542.124, "duration": 3.99, "cleanText": [["now", "I", "be", "plan", "to", "come", "to", "that", "in", "a", "few", "minute", "and", "to", "develop", "the", "latter", "point", "of", "them"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Let's assume relevant market is required, how about the necessity of the pleadings?", "start": 1542.124, "stop": 1547.616, "duration": 5.49, "cleanText": [["let", "us", "assume", "relevant", "market", "be", "require", "how", "about", "the", "necessity", "of", "the", "pleading"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that -- that's the question Mr. Justice on which really the Government doesn't take any position whether this pleading is sufficient as a matter of pleading.", "start": 1547.616, "stop": 1555.746, "duration": 8.13, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "that", "be", "the", "question", "mr", "justice", "on", "which", "really", "the", "government", "do", "not", "take", "any", "position", "whether", "this", "pleading", "be", "sufficient", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "plead"]]}, {"text": "I mean, I think that would -- that's again --", "start": 1555.746, "stop": 1557.305, "duration": 1.56, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "i", "think", "that", "would", "that", "be", "again"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "This issue has never been raised anywhere in the this (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 1557.305, "stop": 1559.189, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["this", "issue", "have", "never", "be", "raise", "anywhere", "in", "the", "this", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "This has never been raised, that's correct.", "start": 1559.189, "stop": 1561.138, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["this", "have", "never", "be", "raise", "that", "have", "correct"]]}, {"text": "And it seems to me that again would be a matter properly to be considered by the trial court in the first instance --", "start": 1561.138, "stop": 1566.07, "duration": 4.93, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "again", "would", "be", "a", "matter", "properly", "to", "be", "consider", "by", "the", "trial", "court", "in", "the", "first", "instance"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But you're suggesting you have an alternative argument which would dispense with this trial, is that it?", "start": 1566.07, "stop": 1572.77, "duration": 6.7, "cleanText": [["but", "you", "be", "suggest", "you", "have", "an", "alternative", "argument", "which", "would", "dispense", "with", "this", "trial", "be", "that", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the alternative argument, we would say that there's no need for relevant market at all.", "start": 1572.77, "stop": 1577.076, "duration": 4.31, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "alternative", "argument", "we", "would", "say", "that", "there", "be", "no", "need", "for", "relevant", "market", "at", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, that's (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 1577.076, "stop": 1577.485, "duration": 0.41, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "be", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "But if there is a need for a relevant market, it seems to me that is not a matter that has to be disposed at this point.", "start": 1577.485, "stop": 1583.227, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "there", "be", "a", "need", "for", "a", "relevant", "market", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "be", "not", "a", "matter", "that", "have", "to", "be", "dispose", "at", "this", "point"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Right.", "start": 1583.227, "stop": 1584.22, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "That would be in all cases of this fact, where there's a fraud on Patent Office --", "start": 1584.22, "stop": 1588.335, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "in", "all", "case", "of", "this", "fact", "where", "there", "be", "a", "fraud", "on", "patent", "office"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that's right.", "start": 1588.335, "stop": 1589.389, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "Whether claim of illegal monopolization rests on the enforcement of the patent procured by fraud and I -- as I will come to develop why we think this is an appropriate rule here.", "start": 1589.389, "stop": 1599.988, "duration": 10.6, "cleanText": [["whether", "claim", "of", "illegal", "monopolization", "rest", "on", "the", "enforcement", "of", "the", "patent", "procure", "by", "fraud", "and", "i", "as", "i", "will", "come", "to", "develop", "why", "we", "think", "this", "be", "an", "appropriate", "rule", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 1599.988, "stop": 1617.655, "duration": 17.67, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "It means, for example, that it had not -- did not sufficiently provide any novelty invention -- yes, I think that would -- wouldn't make a difference.", "start": 1617.655, "stop": 1626.276, "duration": 8.62, "cleanText": [["it", "mean", "for", "example", "that", "it", "have", "not", "do", "not", "sufficiently", "provide", "any", "novelty", "invention", "yes", "i", "think", "that", "would", "would", "not", "make", "a", "difference"]]}, {"text": "Well, again Mr. Justice, we recognized that if a patent has been obtained in good faith -- in good faith, where the patentee has attempted in good faith to get the monopoly which the patent laws provide, that is not the kind -- the exercise of that power is not the kind of thing against which the Sherman Act is directed.", "start": 1626.276, "stop": 1648.402, "duration": 22.13, "cleanText": [["well", "again", "mr", "justice", "we", "recognize", "that", "if", "a", "patent", "have", "be", "obtain", "in", "good", "faith", "in", "good", "faith", "where", "the", "patentee", "have", "attempt", "in", "good", "faith", "to", "get", "the", "monopoly", "which", "the", "patent", "law", "provide", "that", "be", "not", "the", "kind", "the", "exercise", "of", "that", "power", "be", "not", "the", "kind", "of", "thing", "against", "which", "the", "sherman", "act", "be", "direct"]]}, {"text": "But we're --", "start": 1648.402, "stop": 1649.312, "duration": 0.91, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 1649.312, "stop": 1705.525, "duration": 56.21, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, we think it would certainly make a difference.", "start": 1705.525, "stop": 1708.718, "duration": 3.19, "cleanText": [["yes", "we", "think", "it", "would", "certainly", "make", "a", "difference"]]}, {"text": "Invalid -- if I may suggest Mr. Justice, the words invalidly obtained patent -- I put in the word knowingly.", "start": 1708.718, "stop": 1714.764, "duration": 6.05, "cleanText": [["invalid", "if", "i", "may", "suggest", "mr", "justice", "the", "word", "invalidly", "obtain", "patent", "i", "put", "in", "the", "word", "knowingly"]]}, {"text": "We think the essential element of this case is the knowing aspect of it, that they intentionally obtain this power by knowingly misrepresenting the facts for the patent.", "start": 1714.764, "stop": 1726.336, "duration": 11.57, "cleanText": [["we", "think", "the", "essential", "element", "of", "this", "case", "be", "the", "know", "aspect", "of", "it", "that", "they", "intentionally", "obtain", "this", "power", "by", "knowingly", "misrepresent", "the", "fact", "for", "the", "patent"]]}, {"text": "That we think is the essence.", "start": 1726.336, "stop": 1728.434, "duration": 2.1, "cleanText": [["that", "we", "think", "be", "the", "essence"]]}, {"text": "Because in the normal case where someone has a patent, he is merely exercising the power which Congress has given, it means he's getting a reward for his invention.", "start": 1728.434, "stop": 1739.491, "duration": 11.06, "cleanText": [["because", "in", "the", "normal", "case", "where", "someone", "have", "a", "patent", "he", "be", "merely", "exercise", "the", "power", "which", "congress", "have", "give", "it", "mean", "he", "be", "get", "a", "reward", "for", "his", "invention"]]}, {"text": "And if it should late to turn out that the rewards for the invention was improperly granted because, let's say it wasn't a true invention, in that situation, as long as he was attempting to exercise the power which he, in good faith, had sought to obtain, it seems to me this is fully what is contemplated by the patent laws.", "start": 1739.491, "stop": 1759.055, "duration": 19.56, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "it", "should", "late", "to", "turn", "out", "that", "the", "reward", "for", "the", "invention", "be", "improperly", "grant", "because", "let", "us", "say", "it", "be", "not", "a", "true", "invention", "in", "that", "situation", "as", "long", "as", "he", "be", "attempt", "to", "exercise", "the", "power", "which", "he", "in", "good", "faith", "have", "seek", "to", "obtain", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "this", "be", "fully", "what", "be", "contemplate", "by", "the", "patent", "law"]]}, {"text": "But we think this is a quite different case.", "start": 1759.055, "stop": 1761.006, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "think", "this", "be", "a", "quite", "different", "case"]]}, {"text": "This is the unusual case where the claim is that he obtained the power initially improperly.", "start": 1761.006, "stop": 1768.005, "duration": 7, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "the", "unusual", "case", "where", "the", "claim", "be", "that", "he", "obtain", "the", "power", "initially", "improperly"]]}, {"text": "Now, this Court in a large number of decisions, has recognized that where a patentee sues for infringement, the alleged infringer is permitted to raise the defense that the patent had been obtained by fraud.", "start": 1768.005, "stop": 1786.356, "duration": 18.35, "cleanText": [["now", "this", "court", "in", "a", "large", "number", "of", "decision", "have", "recognize", "that", "where", "a", "patentee", "sue", "for", "infringement", "the", "allege", "infringer", "be", "permit", "to", "raise", "the", "defense", "that", "the", "patent", "have", "be", "obtain", "by", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "And those decisions rest basically as we read them.", "start": 1786.356, "stop": 1791.435, "duration": 5.08, "cleanText": [["and", "those", "decision", "rest", "basically", "as", "we", "read", "them"]]}, {"text": "On the fact that because a patent does give a natural monopoly, that it gives the absolute right to exclude, is a very strong public interest in making sure that this power is not obtained from the Government through deceptive practice.", "start": 1791.435, "stop": 1808.775, "duration": 17.34, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "fact", "that", "because", "a", "patent", "do", "give", "a", "natural", "monopoly", "that", "it", "give", "the", "absolute", "right", "to", "exclude", "be", "a", "very", "strong", "public", "interest", "in", "make", "sure", "that", "this", "power", "be", "not", "obtain", "from", "the", "government", "through", "deceptive", "practice"]]}, {"text": "Now, it seems to us the same considerations apply the importance of opening up to the public of permitting the public to be protected against monopolies that were obtained improperly where the alleged illegal procurement of the patent is the affirmative case.", "start": 1808.775, "stop": 1826.435, "duration": 17.66, "cleanText": [["now", "it", "seem", "to", "us", "the", "same", "consideration", "apply", "the", "importance", "of", "open", "up", "to", "the", "public", "of", "permit", "the", "public", "to", "be", "protect", "against", "monopoly", "that", "we", "be", "obtain", "improperly", "where", "the", "allege", "illegal", "procurement", "of", "the", "patent", "be", "the", "affirmative", "case"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't seem to us that it should make any difference whether it's offered as a defense to an infringement suit, whether it's the basis upon which the alleged infringer suit succeeds declaratory relief, or whether as in this case, it's the basis of a charge under the Sherman Act, because in all situation, the basic policy upon which this rule permitting the attack on fraud in the procurement of a patent rests, it seems to us, would be served in all of these cases.", "start": 1826.435, "stop": 1857.764, "duration": 31.33, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "seem", "to", "us", "that", "it", "should", "make", "any", "difference", "whether", "it", "be", "offer", "as", "a", "defense", "to", "an", "infringement", "suit", "whether", "it", "be", "the", "basis", "upon", "which", "the", "alleged", "infringer", "suit", "succeed", "declaratory", "relief", "or", "whether", "as", "in", "this", "case", "it", "be", "the", "basis", "of", "a", "charge", "under", "the", "sherman", "act", "because", "in", "all", "situation", "the", "basic", "policy", "upon", "which", "this", "rule", "permit", "the", "attack", "on", "fraud", "in", "the", "procurement", "of", "a", "patent", "rest", "it", "seem", "to", "us", "would", "be", "serve", "in", "all", "of", "these", "case"]]}, {"text": "Now, with this as a background, I would now liked to come to the more specific question whether what is alleged here is enough to establish a violation of Section 2, that is the charge of monopolization based upon the enforcement of a patent procured by a fraud.", "start": 1857.764, "stop": 1879.6, "duration": 21.84, "cleanText": [["now", "with", "this", "as", "a", "background", "i", "would", "now", "like", "to", "come", "to", "the", "more", "specific", "question", "whether", "what", "be", "allege", "here", "be", "enough", "to", "establish", "a", "violation", "of", "section", "that", "be", "the", "charge", "of", "monopolization", "base", "upon", "the", "enforcement", "of", "a", "patent", "procure", "by", "a", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "Monopoly power of course is instated again and again as the power either to raise prices or to exclude competitors.", "start": 1879.6, "stop": 1887.394, "duration": 7.79, "cleanText": [["monopoly", "power", "of", "course", "be", "instated", "again", "and", "again", "as", "the", "power", "either", "to", "raise", "price", "or", "to", "exclude", "competitor"]]}, {"text": "As far as the patent is concerned, there's no question that -- at least for the claims covered by the patent, that's exactly what the patentee has, so that's what a patent is.", "start": 1887.394, "stop": 1897.21, "duration": 9.82, "cleanText": [["as", "far", "as", "the", "patent", "be", "concern", "there", "be", "no", "question", "that", "at", "least", "for", "the", "claim", "cover", "by", "the", "patent", "that", "be", "exactly", "what", "the", "patentee", "have", "so", "that", "be", "what", "a", "patent", "be"]]}, {"text": "The patent gives you the right to exclude from the subject matter of the patented invention.", "start": 1897.21, "stop": 1903.197, "duration": 5.99, "cleanText": [["the", "patent", "give", "you", "the", "right", "to", "exclude", "from", "the", "subject", "matter", "of", "the", "patented", "invention"]]}, {"text": "And in addition, it seems fair to say that when a patentee obtains from the Patent Office, the right to exclude others from practicing this invention, by definition, it has to be something new and novel, some advancement in the -- in the art of what he's doing before, he obviously thinks, he's getting something a benefit to him.", "start": 1903.197, "stop": 1925.65, "duration": 22.45, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "addition", "it", "seem", "fair", "to", "say", "that", "when", "a", "patentee", "obtain", "from", "the", "patent", "office", "the", "right", "to", "exclude", "others", "from", "practice", "this", "invention", "by", "definition", "it", "have", "to", "be", "something", "new", "and", "novel", "some", "advancement", "in", "the", "in", "the", "art", "of", "what", "he", "have", "do", "before", "he", "obviously", "think", "he", "be", "get", "something", "a", "benefit", "to", "him"]]}, {"text": "Now, we therefore think that if the respondent in this case, Food Machinery and Chemical, does have monopoly power by virtue of the patent, the fact that such power rests on a fraudulently procured patent would be enough to show a violation of Section 2.", "start": 1925.65, "stop": 1946.969, "duration": 21.32, "cleanText": [["now", "we", "therefore", "think", "that", "if", "the", "respondent", "in", "this", "case", "food", "machinery", "and", "chemical", "do", "have", "monopoly", "power", "by", "virtue", "of", "the", "patent", "the", "fact", "that", "such", "power", "rest", "on", "a", "fraudulently", "procure", "patent", "would", "be", "enough", "to", "show", "a", "violation", "of", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Per se inherently -- inevitably in every case?", "start": 1946.969, "stop": 1950.621, "duration": 3.65, "cleanText": [["per", "se", "inherently", "inevitably", "in", "every", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "If he -- if I'm just -- that passing Mr. Justice, the question of whether there is monopoly power, assuming there were no question that a particular firm had monopoly power in the relevant market, it seems to me if -- whenever you could show that that power rest on a patent that was procured by fraud, that would be enough to show illegal monopoly power.", "start": 1950.621, "stop": 1970.928, "duration": 20.31, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "if", "I", "be", "just", "that", "pass", "mr", "justice", "the", "question", "of", "whether", "there", "be", "monopoly", "power", "assume", "there", "we", "be", "no", "question", "that", "a", "particular", "firm", "have", "monopoly", "power", "in", "the", "relevant", "market", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "if", "whenever", "you", "could", "show", "that", "that", "power", "rest", "on", "a", "patent", "that", "be", "procure", "by", "fraud", "that", "would", "be", "enough", "to", "show", "illegal", "monopoly", "power"]]}, {"text": "In other words this is a --", "start": 1970.928, "stop": 1971.773, "duration": 0.84, "cleanText": [["in", "other", "word", "this", "be", "a"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1971.773, "stop": 1972.041, "duration": 0.27, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- clear grasping for the power, this is not the thrust upon the alleged monopoly.", "start": 1972.041, "stop": 1976.323, "duration": 4.28, "cleanText": [["clear", "grasping", "for", "the", "power", "this", "be", "not", "the", "thrust", "upon", "the", "allege", "monopoly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "You first, by definition I -- as it shown, the exercise of the monopoly power within the meaning of that -- of that (Voice Overlap).", "start": 1976.323, "stop": 1982.295, "duration": 5.97, "cleanText": [["you", "first", "by", "definition", "i", "as", "it", "show", "the", "exercise", "of", "the", "monopoly", "power", "within", "the", "meaning", "of", "that", "of", "that", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Within -- where there -- which outcome to those -- once you have the existence of monopoly power, we don't think it could seriously be said that that power if it rest on a fraudulent procured patent is illegal.", "start": 1982.295, "stop": 1993.172, "duration": 10.88, "cleanText": [["within", "where", "there", "which", "outcome", "to", "those", "once", "you", "have", "the", "existence", "of", "monopoly", "power", "we", "do", "not", "think", "it", "could", "seriously", "be", "say", "that", "that", "power", "if", "it", "rest", "on", "a", "fraudulent", "procured", "patent", "be", "illegal"]]}, {"text": "So the case really comes down to the question whether here, what has been alleged is enough.", "start": 1993.172, "stop": 1999.425, "duration": 6.25, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "case", "really", "come", "down", "to", "the", "question", "whether", "here", "what", "have", "be", "allege", "be", "enough"]]}, {"text": "In other words, is there a necessity in this case of proving in addition to all of these facts the relevant market?", "start": 1999.425, "stop": 2007.516, "duration": 8.09, "cleanText": [["in", "other", "word", "be", "there", "a", "necessity", "in", "this", "case", "of", "prove", "in", "addition", "to", "all", "of", "these", "fact", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "Now --", "start": 2007.516, "stop": 2008.193, "duration": 0.68, "cleanText": [["now"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But what if there -- are we going to have to decide that aim?", "start": 2008.193, "stop": 2012.353, "duration": 4.16, "cleanText": [["but", "what", "if", "there", "be", "we", "go", "to", "have", "to", "decide", "that", "aim"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I don't think so Mr. Justice.", "start": 2012.353, "stop": 2013.836, "duration": 1.48, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "do", "not", "think", "so", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "As I say, I think -- it think it's enough that the Court can dispose of this case merely saying that whether or not a relevant market has to be proved, is a question that can be disposed within the lower court.", "start": 2013.836, "stop": 2026.731, "duration": 12.89, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "say", "i", "think", "it", "think", "it", "be", "enough", "that", "the", "court", "can", "dispose", "of", "this", "case", "merely", "say", "that", "whether", "or", "not", "a", "relevant", "market", "have", "to", "be", "prove", "be", "a", "question", "that", "can", "be", "dispose", "within", "the", "low", "court"]]}, {"text": "The reason I'm arguing this point is because the respondent says with great vigor that this suit does not lie because there has been no attempt to just indicate what the relevant market is.", "start": 2026.731, "stop": 2040.816, "duration": 14.09, "cleanText": [["the", "reason", "I", "be", "argue", "this", "point", "be", "because", "the", "respondent", "say", "with", "great", "vigor", "that", "this", "suit", "do", "not", "lie", "because", "there", "have", "be", "no", "attempt", "to", "just", "indicate", "what", "the", "relevant", "market", "be"]]}, {"text": "And that's the reason I'm arguing.", "start": 2040.816, "stop": 2041.843, "duration": 1.03, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "the", "reason", "I", "be", "argue"]]}, {"text": "As I say, our first argument is that, at least in this kind of a case, there's enough said forth.", "start": 2041.843, "stop": 2050.356, "duration": 8.51, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "say", "our", "first", "argument", "be", "that", "at", "least", "in", "this", "kind", "of", "a", "case", "there", "be", "enough", "say", "forth"]]}, {"text": "And the reason for that is, it seems to us again, if a relevant market has to be defined, conceding that not every patent necessarily would give complete power to exclude from what might be the relevant market, at least where someone has obtained a patent and enforced it in the allegation that is done by, that would be in a prima facie at least to show that in this kind of a case, the patent is co-extensive with the relevant market.", "start": 2050.356, "stop": 2077.32, "duration": 26.96, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "reason", "for", "that", "be", "it", "seem", "to", "us", "again", "if", "a", "relevant", "market", "have", "to", "be", "define", "concede", "that", "not", "every", "patent", "necessarily", "would", "give", "complete", "power", "to", "exclude", "from", "what", "might", "be", "the", "relevant", "market", "at", "least", "where", "someone", "have", "obtain", "a", "patent", "and", "enforce", "it", "in", "the", "allegation", "that", "be", "do", "by", "that", "would", "be", "in", "a", "prima", "facie", "at", "least", "to", "show", "that", "in", "this", "kind", "of", "a", "case", "the", "patent", "be", "co", "extensive", "with", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "You know, let's just assume there's a competing product, as stiff and as good as yours, the only the thing is that it doesn't infringe, and there's a patent of device that does this job very well and there's an unpatented device, the competing device, or another patent device for that matter, two patents of device do this job very well in the relevant market.", "start": 2077.32, "stop": 2099.837, "duration": 22.52, "cleanText": [["you", "know", "let", "us", "just", "assume", "there", "be", "a", "compete", "product", "as", "stiff", "and", "as", "good", "as", "yours", "the", "only", "the", "thing", "be", "that", "it", "do", "not", "infringe", "and", "there", "be", "a", "patent", "of", "device", "that", "do", "this", "job", "very", "well", "and", "there", "be", "an", "unpatented", "device", "the", "compete", "device", "or", "another", "patent", "device", "for", "that", "matter", "two", "patent", "of", "device", "do", "this", "job", "very", "well", "in", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, first, as I say --", "start": 2099.837, "stop": 2100.91, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["well", "first", "as", "i", "say"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you say that the one -- that the fellow -- the fellow who exercises his right in this market under a fraudulently obtained patent violates the antitrust law?", "start": 2100.91, "stop": 2109.573, "duration": 8.66, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "say", "that", "the", "one", "that", "the", "fellow", "the", "fellow", "who", "exercise", "his", "right", "in", "this", "market", "under", "a", "fraudulently", "obtain", "patent", "violate", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "We would think so, Mr. Justice.", "start": 2109.573, "stop": 2111.278, "duration": 1.7, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "think", "so", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "And as I say, if I may, I'd like to come --", "start": 2111.278, "stop": 2113.581, "duration": 2.3, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "i", "say", "if", "i", "may", "I", "would", "like", "to", "come"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why would that be?", "start": 2113.581, "stop": 2114.256, "duration": 0.67, "cleanText": [["why", "would", "that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I'd like to -- taking you back --", "start": 2114.256, "stop": 2116.77, "duration": 2.51, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "have", "like", "to", "take", "you", "back"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Let's assume there's either -- that neither product were patented.", "start": 2116.77, "stop": 2119.922, "duration": 3.15, "cleanText": [["let", "us", "assume", "there", "be", "either", "that", "neither", "product", "we", "be", "patent"]]}, {"text": "You wouldn't think that either one of them violated -- would be violating Section 2, would you?", "start": 2119.922, "stop": 2123.939, "duration": 4.02, "cleanText": [["you", "would", "not", "think", "that", "either", "one", "of", "them", "violate", "would", "be", "violate", "section", "would", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no.", "start": 2123.939, "stop": 2124.147, "duration": 0.21, "cleanText": [["no", "no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "And just by telling their product?", "start": 2124.147, "stop": 2125.357, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["and", "just", "by", "tell", "their", "product"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, because of the different situation there.", "start": 2125.357, "stop": 2127.902, "duration": 2.55, "cleanText": [["no", "because", "of", "the", "different", "situation", "there"]]}, {"text": "In the latter hypothetical -- in the latter hypothetical, the man has -- did not have the absolute power stemming from the patent to exclude some scope of the patented invention.", "start": 2127.902, "stop": 2139.828, "duration": 11.93, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "latter", "hypothetical", "in", "the", "latter", "hypothetical", "the", "man", "have", "do", "not", "have", "the", "absolute", "power", "stem", "from", "the", "patent", "to", "exclude", "some", "scope", "of", "the", "patented", "invention"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that's all he's got though.", "start": 2139.828, "stop": 2140.963, "duration": 1.14, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "all", "he", "be", "get", "though"]]}, {"text": "But he hasn't had the power to exclude the market.", "start": 2140.963, "stop": 2143.362, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["but", "he", "have", "not", "have", "the", "power", "to", "exclude", "the", "market"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, he may or may not have.", "start": 2143.362, "stop": 2144.632, "duration": 1.27, "cleanText": [["well", "he", "may", "or", "may", "not", "have"]]}, {"text": "He may or may not have Mr. Justice.", "start": 2144.632, "stop": 2145.634, "duration": 1, "cleanText": [["he", "may", "or", "may", "not", "have", "mr", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what I thought was that -- that he didn't have because of another product that could do just as well.", "start": 2145.634, "stop": 2150.502, "duration": 4.87, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "i", "thought", "be", "that", "that", "he", "do", "not", "have", "because", "of", "another", "product", "that", "could", "do", "just", "as", "well"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I've just say first -- first, that that again it seems to me is a matter that should be explored at the trial court.", "start": 2150.502, "stop": 2158.698, "duration": 8.2, "cleanText": [["well", "I", "have", "just", "say", "first", "first", "that", "that", "again", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "be", "a", "matter", "that", "should", "be", "explore", "at", "the", "trial", "court"]]}, {"text": "But secondly, I'd like to suggest to you why we think that doesn't really make any difference with this case.", "start": 2158.698, "stop": 2163.402, "duration": 4.7, "cleanText": [["but", "secondly", "I", "would", "like", "to", "suggest", "to", "you", "why", "we", "think", "that", "do", "not", "really", "make", "any", "difference", "with", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "And we think -- we think that basically this inquires a little analysis as to why in the antitrust field, we look to the relevant market, when it necessary and when it isn't.", "start": 2163.402, "stop": 2177.878, "duration": 14.48, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "think", "we", "think", "that", "basically", "this", "inquire", "a", "little", "analysis", "as", "to", "why", "in", "the", "antitrust", "field", "we", "look", "to", "the", "relevant", "market", "when", "it", "necessary", "and", "when", "it", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "And there are some situations in the antitrust field where we don't look to the relevant market.", "start": 2177.878, "stop": 2183.313, "duration": 5.43, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "be", "some", "situation", "in", "the", "antitrust", "field", "where", "we", "do", "not", "look", "to", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "There are other situations in which we do.", "start": 2183.313, "stop": 2185.388, "duration": 2.07, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "other", "situation", "in", "which", "we", "do"]]}, {"text": "Price fixing is a common example of a situation where there has never been any need to define the relevant market, it's enough to prove an agreement between people to fix prices.", "start": 2185.388, "stop": 2194.922, "duration": 9.53, "cleanText": [["price", "fixing", "be", "a", "common", "example", "of", "a", "situation", "where", "there", "have", "never", "be", "any", "need", "to", "define", "the", "relevant", "market", "it", "be", "enough", "to", "prove", "an", "agreement", "between", "people", "to", "fix", "price"]]}, {"text": "And once that is established, as long as something more than a de minimis amount of commerce is involved, that's the end of it.", "start": 2194.922, "stop": 2203.165, "duration": 8.24, "cleanText": [["and", "once", "that", "be", "establish", "as", "long", "as", "something", "more", "than", "a", "de", "minimis", "amount", "of", "commerce", "be", "involve", "that", "be", "the", "end", "of", "it"]]}, {"text": "In the merger field on the other hand, we always have to define the relevant market and the reason we say, we have to define the relevant market is we have to find out what the effect of the merger is on competition, and the way you find out that is to see where they're competing.", "start": 2203.165, "stop": 2217.267, "duration": 14.1, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "merger", "field", "on", "the", "other", "hand", "we", "always", "have", "to", "define", "the", "relevant", "market", "and", "the", "reason", "we", "say", "we", "have", "to", "define", "the", "relevant", "market", "be", "we", "have", "to", "find", "out", "what", "the", "effect", "of", "the", "merger", "be", "on", "competition", "and", "the", "way", "you", "find", "out", "that", "be", "to", "see", "where", "they", "be", "compete"]]}, {"text": "You see where they compete by defining the relevant market.", "start": 2217.267, "stop": 2221.128, "duration": 3.86, "cleanText": [["you", "see", "where", "they", "compete", "by", "define", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "But I'd like to come back to the price fixing situation for a minute, because I suppose one could conceive of a situation, the particular industry where there are two people out of enlarged number of firms who agree to fix prices.", "start": 2221.128, "stop": 2235.819, "duration": 14.69, "cleanText": [["but", "I", "would", "like", "to", "come", "back", "to", "the", "price", "fix", "situation", "for", "a", "minute", "because", "i", "suppose", "one", "could", "conceive", "of", "a", "situation", "the", "particular", "industry", "where", "there", "be", "two", "people", "out", "of", "enlarged", "number", "of", "firm", "who", "agree", "to", "fix", "price"]]}, {"text": "Now, as long as something more than de minimis commerce is involved, that would be a violation of the antitrust law.", "start": 2235.819, "stop": 2243.843, "duration": 8.02, "cleanText": [["now", "as", "long", "as", "something", "more", "than", "de", "minimis", "commerce", "be", "involve", "that", "would", "be", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "Yet, it might well be in a particular industry that the industry was so structured, that the elimination of price competition between these two people would not realistically have any substantial effect on competition in the line of commerce involved.", "start": 2243.843, "stop": 2261.543, "duration": 17.7, "cleanText": [["yet", "it", "might", "well", "be", "in", "a", "particular", "industry", "that", "the", "industry", "be", "so", "structured", "that", "the", "elimination", "of", "price", "competition", "between", "these", "two", "people", "would", "not", "realistically", "have", "any", "substantial", "effect", "on", "competition", "in", "the", "line", "of", "commerce", "involve"]]}, {"text": "And I would like to offer this suggestion for why there seems to be this dichotomy in the antitrust laws, why it is -- in some types of cases, we find it necessary to analyze the relevant market and others not.", "start": 2261.543, "stop": 2276.473, "duration": 14.93, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "would", "like", "to", "offer", "this", "suggestion", "for", "why", "there", "seem", "to", "be", "this", "dichotomy", "in", "the", "antitrust", "law", "why", "it", "be", "in", "some", "type", "of", "case", "we", "find", "it", "necessary", "to", "analyze", "the", "relevant", "market", "and", "others", "not"]]}, {"text": "And I think the explanation to those has not been articulated in the case.", "start": 2276.473, "stop": 2280.654, "duration": 4.18, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "think", "the", "explanation", "to", "those", "have", "not", "be", "articulate", "in", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "It's basically this -- when you have practices with anti-competitive effect, the credible question there is whether there are any compensating factors, any things that might offset the anti-competitive effects, and therefore unbalance, lead to the conclusion that this is not the kind of practice which the Sherman Act condemns.", "start": 2280.654, "stop": 2303.205, "duration": 22.55, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "basically", "this", "when", "you", "have", "practice", "with", "anti", "competitive", "effect", "the", "credible", "question", "there", "be", "whether", "there", "be", "any", "compensating", "factor", "any", "thing", "that", "might", "offset", "the", "anti", "competitive", "effect", "and", "therefore", "unbalance", "lead", "to", "the", "conclusion", "that", "this", "be", "not", "the", "kind", "of", "practice", "which", "the", "sherman", "act", "condemns"]]}, {"text": "And this of course, has been the -- in the per se case that this Court has pointed out most noticeably in the Northern Pacific case, that in that type of situation, the certain types of practices have presumed to have such a pernicious effect and then this -- as this Court said in Northern Pacific that they are illegal, without a labyrinth inquiry as to the precise harm they may have caused or the business excuse for their use.", "start": 2303.205, "stop": 2329.058, "duration": 25.85, "cleanText": [["and", "this", "of", "course", "have", "be", "the", "in", "the", "per", "se", "case", "that", "this", "court", "have", "point", "out", "most", "noticeably", "in", "the", "northern", "pacific", "case", "that", "in", "that", "type", "of", "situation", "the", "certain", "type", "of", "practice", "have", "presume", "to", "have", "such", "a", "pernicious", "effect", "and", "then", "this", "as", "this", "court", "say", "in", "northern", "pacific", "that", "they", "be", "illegal", "without", "a", "labyrinth", "inquiry", "as", "to", "the", "precise", "harm", "they", "may", "have", "cause", "or", "the", "business", "excuse", "for", "their", "use"]]}, {"text": "I think this is pointed out very dramatically when we contrast the way in which exclusive dealing agreements and tying clauses are treated under the antitrust laws.", "start": 2329.058, "stop": 2339.105, "duration": 10.05, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "this", "be", "point", "out", "very", "dramatically", "when", "we", "contrast", "the", "way", "in", "which", "exclusive", "dealing", "agreement", "and", "tie", "clause", "be", "treat", "under", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "Tying clauses are generally considered to be one of those practices that have no other effect other than the suppression of competition.", "start": 2339.105, "stop": 2346.767, "duration": 7.66, "cleanText": [["tie", "clause", "be", "generally", "consider", "to", "be", "one", "of", "those", "practice", "that", "have", "no", "other", "effect", "other", "than", "the", "suppression", "of", "competition"]]}, {"text": "A market inquiry therefore is not required.", "start": 2346.767, "stop": 2349.246, "duration": 2.48, "cleanText": [["a", "market", "inquiry", "therefore", "be", "not", "require"]]}, {"text": "Those are per se illegal as long as there's a substantial effect was shown.", "start": 2349.246, "stop": 2353.396, "duration": 4.15, "cleanText": [["those", "be", "per", "se", "illegal", "as", "long", "as", "there", "be", "a", "substantial", "effect", "be", "show"]]}, {"text": "On the other hand, exclusive dealing of contracts may or may not have a desirable effect.", "start": 2353.396, "stop": 2359.905, "duration": 6.51, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "other", "hand", "exclusive", "dealing", "of", "contract", "may", "or", "may", "not", "have", "a", "desirable", "effect"]]}, {"text": "And therefore, in that situation, we have to go beyond this inquiry and look to the relevant market to see whether in fact they do have a basically bad effect in the market.", "start": 2359.905, "stop": 2371.724, "duration": 11.82, "cleanText": [["and", "therefore", "in", "that", "situation", "we", "have", "to", "go", "beyond", "this", "inquiry", "and", "look", "to", "the", "relevant", "market", "to", "see", "whether", "in", "fact", "they", "do", "have", "a", "basically", "bad", "effect", "in", "the", "market"]]}, {"text": "Now, with this as the background, I would like to come to the monopoly situation.", "start": 2371.724, "stop": 2375.858, "duration": 4.13, "cleanText": [["now", "with", "this", "as", "the", "background", "i", "would", "like", "to", "come", "to", "the", "monopoly", "situation"]]}, {"text": "In a monopoly case, the fact that a particular firm has a stated percentage of the market for a particular product, doesn't itself tell us whether the possession of that share will or will not harm competition.", "start": 2375.858, "stop": 2391.213, "duration": 15.36, "cleanText": [["in", "a", "monopoly", "case", "the", "fact", "that", "a", "particular", "firm", "have", "a", "state", "percentage", "of", "the", "market", "for", "a", "particular", "product", "do", "not", "itself", "tell", "us", "whether", "the", "possession", "of", "that", "share", "will", "or", "will", "not", "harm", "competition"]]}, {"text": "And therefore, in that situation, what we have to do is first to define the relevant market.", "start": 2391.213, "stop": 2397.305, "duration": 6.09, "cleanText": [["and", "therefore", "in", "that", "situation", "what", "we", "have", "to", "do", "be", "first", "to", "define", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "And then, look to that market to see what the effect on competition is to ascertain whether the firm's share of the particular product where it has, for example, where DuPont had 75% of cellophane, whether that kind of economic power is the kind of power that the antitrust laws condemn.", "start": 2397.305, "stop": 2419.309, "duration": 22, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "look", "to", "that", "market", "to", "see", "what", "the", "effect", "on", "competition", "be", "to", "ascertain", "whether", "the", "firm", "s", "share", "of", "the", "particular", "product", "where", "it", "have", "for", "example", "where", "dupont", "have", "of", "cellophane", "whether", "that", "kind", "of", "economic", "power", "be", "the", "kind", "of", "power", "that", "the", "antitrust", "law", "condemn"]]}, {"text": "Because in that situation, the particular practice -- in this case, it's not a practice I suppose, that the status, the market situation, may or may not be a bad thing.", "start": 2419.309, "stop": 2431.987, "duration": 12.68, "cleanText": [["because", "in", "that", "situation", "the", "particular", "practice", "in", "this", "case", "it", "be", "not", "a", "practice", "i", "suppose", "that", "the", "status", "the", "market", "situation", "may", "or", "may", "not", "be", "a", "bad", "thing"]]}, {"text": "But when we come to the case of a patent that is procured by fraud and which is specifically -- admittedly gives the power to exclude from the particular item covered by the invention and where the patent is obtained for that very purpose, it seems to us that there can be no question that this is precisely the type of economic misuse of power that the antitrust laws are intended to condemn.", "start": 2431.987, "stop": 2456.976, "duration": 24.99, "cleanText": [["but", "when", "we", "come", "to", "the", "case", "of", "a", "patent", "that", "be", "procure", "by", "fraud", "and", "which", "be", "specifically", "admittedly", "give", "the", "power", "to", "exclude", "from", "the", "particular", "item", "cover", "by", "the", "invention", "and", "where", "the", "patent", "be", "obtain", "for", "that", "very", "purpose", "it", "seem", "to", "us", "that", "there", "can", "be", "no", "question", "that", "this", "be", "precisely", "the", "type", "of", "economic", "misuse", "of", "power", "that", "the", "antitrust", "law", "be", "intend", "to", "condemn"]]}, {"text": "And it certainly, the enforcement of the patent for that purpose is injurious to competition, where it's obtained by misleading the Patent Office.", "start": 2456.976, "stop": 2466.894, "duration": 9.92, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "certainly", "the", "enforcement", "of", "the", "patent", "for", "that", "purpose", "be", "injurious", "to", "competition", "where", "it", "be", "obtain", "by", "mislead", "the", "patent", "office"]]}, {"text": "And we therefore think, in that kind of a case, it would be fully consistent with the decisions of this Court to say that there, there is no need for the elaborate analysis of the market to ascertain what needs and bounds of the relevant market are, that -- it's enough in that situation we think that there is a patent, that it has been procured by fraud in the Patent Office, and that it's being used to exclude competition.", "start": 2466.894, "stop": 2492.004, "duration": 25.11, "cleanText": [["and", "we", "therefore", "think", "in", "that", "kind", "of", "a", "case", "it", "would", "be", "fully", "consistent", "with", "the", "decision", "of", "this", "court", "to", "say", "that", "there", "there", "be", "no", "need", "for", "the", "elaborate", "analysis", "of", "the", "market", "to", "ascertain", "what", "need", "and", "bound", "of", "the", "relevant", "market", "be", "that", "it", "be", "enough", "in", "that", "situation", "we", "think", "that", "there", "be", "a", "patent", "that", "it", "have", "be", "procure", "by", "fraud", "in", "the", "patent", "office", "and", "that", "it", "be", "be", "use", "to", "exclude", "competition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you -- it's not only a prima facie case then if I would understand the -- you would say, but a conclusive case?", "start": 2492.004, "stop": 2498.873, "duration": 6.87, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "it", "be", "not", "only", "a", "prima", "facie", "case", "then", "if", "i", "would", "understand", "the", "you", "would", "say", "but", "a", "conclusive", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "On this aspect of it, yes.", "start": 2498.873, "stop": 2500.441, "duration": 1.57, "cleanText": [["on", "this", "aspect", "of", "it", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of a -- of monopolization?", "start": 2500.441, "stop": 2503.047, "duration": 2.61, "cleanText": [["of", "a", "of", "monopolization"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct.", "start": 2503.047, "stop": 2503.21, "duration": 0.16, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "You proved that as conclusive?", "start": 2503.21, "stop": 2505.209, "duration": 2, "cleanText": [["you", "prove", "that", "as", "conclusive"]]}, {"text": "There's no need for -- there's no defense, is there?", "start": 2505.209, "stop": 2510.07, "duration": 4.86, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "need", "for", "there", "be", "no", "defense", "be", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there's no defense except the defenses as to whether they have in fact the same patent (Voice Overlap) by fraud and whether they enforced it against.", "start": 2510.07, "stop": 2517.674, "duration": 7.6, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "be", "no", "defense", "except", "the", "defense", "as", "to", "whether", "they", "have", "in", "fact", "the", "same", "patent", "voice", "overlap", "by", "fraud", "and", "whether", "they", "enforce", "it", "against"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes --", "start": 2517.674, "stop": 2519.112, "duration": 1.44, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "And the damages, of course, yes.", "start": 2519.112, "stop": 2520.812, "duration": 1.7, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "damage", "of", "course", "yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Suppose we didn't agree with you though, this case have to be affirmed or --", "start": 2520.812, "stop": 2525.127, "duration": 4.32, "cleanText": [["suppose", "we", "do", "not", "agree", "with", "you", "though", "this", "case", "have", "to", "be", "affirm", "or"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Mr. Justice.", "start": 2525.127, "stop": 2526.09, "duration": 0.96, "cleanText": [["no", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "If the Court does not agree with us on that, there is still -- I think it should go back to develop and -- at the District Court level what the relevant market is against --", "start": 2526.09, "stop": 2534.012, "duration": 7.92, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "court", "do", "not", "agree", "with", "us", "on", "that", "there", "be", "still", "i", "think", "it", "should", "go", "back", "to", "develop", "and", "at", "the", "district", "court", "level", "what", "the", "relevant", "market", "be", "against"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Although you didn't allege that other kind of alleged?", "start": 2534.012, "stop": 2536.566, "duration": 2.55, "cleanText": [["although", "you", "do", "not", "allege", "that", "other", "kind", "of", "allege"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think again, this is a question -- we don't take -- the Government doesn't take any position as to whether if relevant market has to be shown whether this complaint sufficiently alleged.", "start": 2536.566, "stop": 2546.523, "duration": 9.96, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "again", "this", "be", "a", "question", "we", "do", "not", "take", "the", "government", "do", "not", "take", "any", "position", "as", "to", "whether", "if", "relevant", "market", "have", "to", "be", "show", "whether", "this", "complaint", "sufficiently", "allege"]]}, {"text": "I think again, this would be a matter for the District Court, the District Court did attempt to decide the case on that basis, and it seems to me in the first instance that the trial court should now be given an opportunity to see whether this complaint is deficient and in further whether an amendment might be appropriate.", "start": 2546.523, "stop": 2562.259, "duration": 15.74, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "again", "this", "would", "be", "a", "matter", "for", "the", "district", "court", "the", "district", "court", "do", "attempt", "to", "decide", "the", "case", "on", "that", "basis", "and", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "in", "the", "first", "instance", "that", "the", "trial", "court", "should", "now", "be", "give", "an", "opportunity", "to", "see", "whether", "this", "complaint", "be", "deficient", "and", "in", "further", "whether", "an", "amendment", "might", "be", "appropriate"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, assuming that that is irrelevant to the case, why is that -- why does that rise above anything except an amendable defense?", "start": 2562.259, "stop": 2572.105, "duration": 9.85, "cleanText": [["well", "assume", "that", "that", "be", "irrelevant", "to", "the", "case", "why", "be", "that", "why", "do", "that", "rise", "above", "anything", "except", "an", "amendable", "defense"]]}, {"text": "Why should the lawsuit be thrown out of court on that?", "start": 2572.105, "stop": 2575.023, "duration": 2.92, "cleanText": [["why", "should", "the", "lawsuit", "be", "throw", "out", "of", "court", "on", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, we don't think it should Mr. Justice --", "start": 2575.023, "stop": 2576.626, "duration": 1.6, "cleanText": [["well", "we", "do", "not", "think", "it", "should", "mr", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "So why do we have to decide it here one way or the other?", "start": 2576.626, "stop": 2579.391, "duration": 2.76, "cleanText": [["so", "why", "do", "we", "have", "to", "decide", "it", "here", "one", "way", "or", "the", "other"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I don't think so.", "start": 2579.391, "stop": 2580.292, "duration": 0.9, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "do", "not", "think", "so"]]}, {"text": "I don't believe, as I suggested earlier, I don't think the Court has to pass on that.", "start": 2580.292, "stop": 2593.039, "duration": 12.75, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "believe", "as", "i", "suggest", "earlier", "i", "do", "not", "think", "the", "court", "have", "to", "pass", "on", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Collen.", "start": 2593.039, "stop": 2607.721, "duration": 14.68, "cleanText": [["mr", "collen"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, if the Court please.", "start": 2607.721, "stop": 2613.115, "duration": 5.39, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}, {"text": "I think what is really necessary for the Court to understand why this particular case is here, is for us to review briefly the pleadings because the simple fact of the matter is, and during the course of three pleadings, there isn't any question -- I think the Court will agree that Walker Process Equipment Company is submitting to the Court the sole and simple question of whether the fraudulent procurement in maintenance of a patent is illegal per se.", "start": 2613.115, "stop": 2643.796, "duration": 30.68, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "what", "be", "really", "necessary", "for", "the", "court", "to", "understand", "why", "this", "particular", "case", "be", "here", "be", "for", "us", "to", "review", "briefly", "the", "pleading", "because", "the", "simple", "fact", "of", "the", "matter", "be", "and", "during", "the", "course", "of", "three", "pleading", "there", "be", "not", "any", "question", "i", "think", "the", "court", "will", "agree", "that", "walker", "process", "equipment", "company", "be", "submit", "to", "the", "court", "the", "sole", "and", "simple", "question", "of", "whether", "the", "fraudulent", "procurement", "in", "maintenance", "of", "a", "patent", "be", "illegal", "per", "se"]]}, {"text": "That is the only question that they are attempting to submit to this Court.", "start": 2643.796, "stop": 2648.196, "duration": 4.4, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "only", "question", "that", "they", "be", "attempt", "to", "submit", "to", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "It is perfectly clear from their pleadings, it's perfectly clear from the confession of the parties.", "start": 2648.196, "stop": 2654.598, "duration": 6.4, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "perfectly", "clear", "from", "their", "pleading", "it", "be", "perfectly", "clear", "from", "the", "confession", "of", "the", "party"]]}, {"text": "And the reason they arrived at that question and what their position is based in, is the simple equation that any patent necessarily grants a monopoly or monopolies are illegal under the Sherman Antitrust Act and if you remove the protection of the patent laws from the patent, or go ipso facto mechanically, universally, you are left with an unlawful monopoly.", "start": 2654.598, "stop": 2683.76, "duration": 29.16, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "reason", "they", "arrive", "at", "that", "question", "and", "what", "their", "position", "be", "base", "in", "be", "the", "simple", "equation", "that", "any", "patent", "necessarily", "grant", "a", "monopoly", "or", "monopoly", "be", "illegal", "under", "the", "sherman", "antitrust", "act", "and", "if", "you", "remove", "the", "protection", "of", "the", "patent", "law", "from", "the", "patent", "or", "go", "ipso", "facto", "mechanically", "universally", "you", "be", "leave", "with", "an", "unlawful", "monopoly"]]}, {"text": "That is all they have ever attempted to say in this case, if the Court please.", "start": 2683.76, "stop": 2689.07, "duration": 5.31, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "all", "they", "have", "ever", "attempt", "to", "say", "in", "this", "case", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}, {"text": "Their original pleading was filed in response to plaintiff suit for infringement.", "start": 2689.07, "stop": 2694.768, "duration": 5.7, "cleanText": [["their", "original", "pleading", "be", "file", "in", "response", "to", "plaintiff", "suit", "for", "infringement"]]}, {"text": "They defend it on the ground -- so they said that the patent was obtained from the Patent Office by misrepresentations and that this constitutes unclean hands.", "start": 2694.768, "stop": 2706.055, "duration": 11.29, "cleanText": [["they", "defend", "it", "on", "the", "ground", "so", "they", "say", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "obtain", "from", "the", "patent", "office", "by", "misrepresentation", "and", "that", "this", "constitute", "unclean", "hand"]]}, {"text": "And they added, this constitutes a violation of the antitrust laws.", "start": 2706.055, "stop": 2711.478, "duration": 5.42, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "add", "this", "constitute", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "In their first pleading then, that's all they said in violation of the antitrust laws.", "start": 2711.478, "stop": 2716.954, "duration": 5.48, "cleanText": [["in", "their", "first", "pleading", "then", "that", "be", "all", "they", "say", "in", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "It was perfectly clear that in their view, there was a universal exchangeability and interchange of conversion between the defense of unenforceability based on so-called fraudulent procurement in violation of the antitrust laws.", "start": 2716.954, "stop": 2733.633, "duration": 16.68, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "perfectly", "clear", "that", "in", "their", "view", "there", "be", "a", "universal", "exchangeability", "and", "interchange", "of", "conversion", "between", "the", "defense", "of", "unenforceability", "base", "on", "so", "call", "fraudulent", "procurement", "in", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "That's the most -- that's all that they claim.", "start": 2733.633, "stop": 2736.616, "duration": 2.98, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "most", "that", "be", "all", "that", "they", "claim"]]}, {"text": "Now subsequently, they've got leads to amend because with nothing more than their pleading, I don't think they would want to proceed very far in the case.", "start": 2736.616, "stop": 2746.625, "duration": 10.01, "cleanText": [["now", "subsequently", "they", "have", "get", "lead", "to", "amend", "because", "with", "nothing", "more", "than", "their", "pleading", "i", "do", "not", "think", "they", "would", "want", "to", "proceed", "very", "far", "in", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "With their amended counterclaim, they entered a new dimension to the case.", "start": 2746.625, "stop": 2751.629, "duration": 5, "cleanText": [["with", "their", "amended", "counterclaim", "they", "enter", "a", "new", "dimension", "to", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "They contended that there was some kind of illegal tie-ins involved in the case.", "start": 2751.629, "stop": 2756.519, "duration": 4.89, "cleanText": [["they", "contend", "that", "there", "be", "some", "kind", "of", "illegal", "tie", "in", "involve", "in", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "Then FMC, in connection with the sale of its swing diffuser units were somehow packaging or forcing other equipment for plaintiff's buyers.", "start": 2756.519, "stop": 2767.744, "duration": 11.23, "cleanText": [["then", "fmc", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "sale", "of", "its", "swing", "diffuse", "unit", "we", "be", "somehow", "packaging", "or", "force", "other", "equipment", "for", "plaintiff", "s", "buyer"]]}, {"text": "They did not however in their amended complaint change their views or plead anything different in connection with this equation between fraudulent procurement of the patent in violation of the antitrust laws.", "start": 2767.744, "stop": 2783.065, "duration": 15.32, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "however", "in", "their", "amended", "complaint", "change", "their", "view", "or", "plead", "anything", "different", "in", "connection", "with", "this", "equation", "between", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "the", "patent", "in", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "Once again, in their amended complaint, they simply said after reciting the alleged fraudulent procurement that this constitutes a violation of the antitrust laws.", "start": 2783.065, "stop": 2794.206, "duration": 11.14, "cleanText": [["once", "again", "in", "their", "amended", "complaint", "they", "simply", "say", "after", "recite", "the", "allege", "fraudulent", "procurement", "that", "this", "constitute", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "They also told us that their point that it constituted a claim for unjust enrichment, it constituted some claim -- a claim for unfair competition, and they spelled out in frolics detail, if the Court please, an unintelligible detail what they were trying to accomplish.", "start": 2794.206, "stop": 2812.052, "duration": 17.85, "cleanText": [["they", "also", "tell", "us", "that", "their", "point", "that", "it", "constitute", "a", "claim", "for", "unjust", "enrichment", "it", "constitute", "some", "claim", "a", "claim", "for", "unfair", "competition", "and", "they", "spell", "out", "in", "frolic", "detail", "if", "the", "court", "please", "an", "unintelligible", "detail", "what", "they", "we", "be", "try", "to", "accomplish"]]}, {"text": "We moved in the District Court to strike their complaint on the grounds that it was not clear, it was not readable under Rule 8, and also for its failure to state a claim in which relief could be granted.", "start": 2812.052, "stop": 2823.925, "duration": 11.87, "cleanText": [["we", "move", "in", "the", "district", "court", "to", "strike", "their", "complaint", "on", "the", "ground", "that", "it", "be", "not", "clear", "it", "be", "not", "readable", "under", "rule", "and", "also", "for", "its", "failure", "to", "state", "a", "claim", "in", "which", "relief", "could", "be", "grant"]]}, {"text": "Now contrary, if the Court please, to what Mr. Merriam has said this morning, Mr. Merriam did not participate in the case at that stage.", "start": 2823.925, "stop": 2833.319, "duration": 9.39, "cleanText": [["now", "contrary", "if", "the", "court", "please", "to", "what", "mr", "merriam", "have", "say", "this", "morning", "mr", "merriam", "do", "not", "participate", "in", "the", "case", "at", "that", "stage"]]}, {"text": "From the very beginning in our first brief in the District Court, we took two positions.", "start": 2833.319, "stop": 2837.697, "duration": 4.38, "cleanText": [["from", "the", "very", "begin", "in", "our", "first", "brief", "in", "the", "district", "court", "we", "take", "two", "position"]]}, {"text": "We took substantially the technical position that the Court of Appeals relied on, and I'll advert further to that later, but we also took the position, a great link as I'm saying to the Court right now that they are trying to plead an automatic equation between fraudulent procurement of a patent and Sherman Act monopolization.", "start": 2837.697, "stop": 2861.263, "duration": 23.57, "cleanText": [["we", "take", "substantially", "the", "technical", "position", "that", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "rely", "on", "and", "I", "will", "advert", "far", "to", "that", "later", "but", "we", "also", "take", "the", "position", "a", "great", "link", "as", "I", "be", "say", "to", "the", "court", "right", "now", "that", "they", "be", "try", "to", "plead", "an", "automatic", "equation", "between", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "a", "patent", "and", "sherman", "act", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "So, the original motion to strike in our original brief, we at length pointed out from the very beginning that these people were not pleading a claim of monopolization under Section 2, that the concept of monopolization under Section 2 includes a relevant market, it's not a question that to some cases we need a relevant market, in some cases we don't, in any monopolization case under Section 2, the very idea of monopolization means irrelevant market.", "start": 2861.263, "stop": 2893.313, "duration": 32.05, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "original", "motion", "to", "strike", "in", "our", "original", "brief", "we", "at", "length", "point", "out", "from", "the", "very", "begin", "that", "these", "people", "we", "be", "not", "plead", "a", "claim", "of", "monopolization", "under", "section", "that", "the", "concept", "of", "monopolization", "under", "section", "include", "a", "relevant", "market", "it", "be", "not", "a", "question", "that", "to", "some", "case", "we", "need", "a", "relevant", "market", "in", "some", "case", "we", "do", "not", "in", "any", "monopolization", "case", "under", "section", "the", "very", "idea", "of", "monopolization", "mean", "irrelevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "The power to exclude competition or the fix prices in a relevant market is a criteria or at least a basic mode of examination into the ascertainment of whether there is monopolization.", "start": 2893.313, "stop": 2907.458, "duration": 14.14, "cleanText": [["the", "power", "to", "exclude", "competition", "or", "the", "fix", "price", "in", "a", "relevant", "market", "be", "a", "criterion", "or", "at", "least", "a", "basic", "mode", "of", "examination", "into", "the", "ascertainment", "of", "whether", "there", "be", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "In that of any counterclaim, despite all of these allegations about antitrust violations, there was no suggestion whether they were pleading of monopolization case, whether they were pleading of Section 1 case out the Sherman Act or whether they were pleading a tie-in case under Section 3 of the Clayton Act or Section 1 of the Sherman Act, all they talked about was antitrust laws.", "start": 2907.458, "stop": 2931.19, "duration": 23.73, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "of", "any", "counterclaim", "despite", "all", "of", "these", "allegation", "about", "antitrust", "violation", "there", "be", "no", "suggestion", "whether", "they", "we", "be", "plead", "of", "monopolization", "case", "whether", "they", "we", "be", "plead", "of", "section", "case", "out", "the", "sherman", "act", "or", "whether", "they", "we", "be", "plead", "a", "tie", "in", "case", "under", "section", "of", "the", "clayton", "act", "or", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "all", "they", "talk", "about", "be", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "And it was for that reason -- and besides antitrust laws, of course, they were talking about some kind of additional or common law relief for unjust enrichment.", "start": 2931.19, "stop": 2941.028, "duration": 9.84, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "be", "for", "that", "reason", "and", "besides", "antitrust", "law", "of", "course", "they", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "some", "kind", "of", "additional", "or", "common", "law", "relief", "for", "unjust", "enrichment"]]}, {"text": "It was for that reason that we adopted the two-fold approach if that (Inaudible) for the case.", "start": 2941.028, "stop": 2946.446, "duration": 5.42, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "for", "that", "reason", "that", "we", "adopt", "the", "two", "fold", "approach", "if", "that", "inaudible", "for", "the", "case"]]}, {"text": "The theory, again, as I say that the Court of Appeals finally adopted in which I would advert to, that somehow, what they were trying to do is collaterally eject the validity of the patent and that that would not like.", "start": 2946.446, "stop": 2957.693, "duration": 11.25, "cleanText": [["the", "theory", "again", "as", "i", "say", "that", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "finally", "adopt", "in", "which", "i", "would", "advert", "to", "that", "somehow", "what", "they", "we", "be", "try", "to", "do", "be", "collaterally", "eject", "the", "validity", "of", "the", "patent", "and", "that", "that", "would", "not", "like"]]}, {"text": "And at the same time, that if they were talking about a monopolization case, they were not pleading the case of monopolization.", "start": 2957.693, "stop": 2965.886, "duration": 8.19, "cleanText": [["and", "at", "the", "same", "time", "that", "if", "they", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "a", "monopolization", "case", "they", "we", "be", "not", "plead", "the", "case", "of", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "Now, I suggest to the Court and I think it is crucial here for purposes of the ultimate termination of this litigation, they haven't pleaded a monopolization case.", "start": 2965.886, "stop": 2975.529, "duration": 9.64, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "and", "i", "think", "it", "be", "crucial", "here", "for", "purpose", "of", "the", "ultimate", "termination", "of", "this", "litigation", "they", "have", "not", "plead", "a", "monopolization", "case"]]}, {"text": "They don't intend to plead a monopolization case.", "start": 2975.529, "stop": 2978.096, "duration": 2.57, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "intend", "to", "plead", "a", "monopolization", "case"]]}, {"text": "They're pleading a per se case.", "start": 2978.096, "stop": 2980.034, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "plead", "a", "per", "se", "case"]]}, {"text": "They have three chances to make the monopolization case established and under no circumstances is the appropriate for the case to go back to the District Court for determination of what might have been monopolized or what the relevant market might have been.", "start": 2980.034, "stop": 2994.212, "duration": 14.18, "cleanText": [["they", "have", "three", "chance", "to", "make", "the", "monopolization", "case", "establish", "and", "under", "no", "circumstance", "be", "the", "appropriate", "for", "the", "case", "to", "go", "back", "to", "the", "district", "court", "for", "determination", "of", "what", "might", "have", "be", "monopolize", "or", "what", "the", "relevant", "market", "might", "have", "be"]]}, {"text": "That isn't their case.", "start": 2994.212, "stop": 2995.675, "duration": 1.46, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "their", "case"]]}, {"text": "That is not the issue that they are presenting to this Court.", "start": 2995.675, "stop": 2998.88, "duration": 3.2, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "the", "issue", "that", "they", "be", "present", "to", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "They're presenting to the Court -- it's quite apparent from the language of question two presented by Walkers, from the language of the question presented by the Government, that they are only asking for this per se determination.", "start": 2998.88, "stop": 3012.967, "duration": 14.09, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "present", "to", "the", "court", "it", "be", "quite", "apparent", "from", "the", "language", "of", "question", "two", "present", "by", "walker", "from", "the", "language", "of", "the", "question", "present", "by", "the", "government", "that", "they", "be", "only", "ask", "for", "this", "per", "se", "determination"]]}, {"text": "And I want to suggest to the Court, as I have this from the very beginning, that's all they wanted to say.", "start": 3012.967, "stop": 3022.238, "duration": 9.27, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "want", "to", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "as", "i", "have", "this", "from", "the", "very", "beginning", "that", "be", "all", "they", "want", "to", "say"]]}, {"text": "That's all they are saying now.", "start": 3022.238, "stop": 3024.151, "duration": 1.91, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "all", "they", "be", "say", "now"]]}, {"text": "They're talking as even as late as their replied brief, that the relevant market maybe some kind of formality that maybe could be supplied later.", "start": 3024.151, "stop": 3033.576, "duration": 9.43, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "talk", "as", "even", "as", "late", "as", "their", "replied", "brief", "that", "the", "relevant", "market", "maybe", "some", "kind", "of", "formality", "that", "maybe", "could", "be", "supply", "later"]]}, {"text": "But they are totally lacking in any appreciation of the relationship between the relevant market as a dimension of monopolization, there cannot be any such thing as monopolization without reference to a relevant market.", "start": 3033.576, "stop": 3047.704, "duration": 14.13, "cleanText": [["but", "they", "be", "totally", "lack", "in", "any", "appreciation", "of", "the", "relationship", "between", "the", "relevant", "market", "as", "a", "dimension", "of", "monopolization", "there", "can", "not", "be", "any", "such", "thing", "as", "monopolization", "without", "reference", "to", "a", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "Now, if the Court please in response to our first pleas in the District Court, their response was -- and I'm quoting from their District Court brief, The patent monopoly is a monopoly without considering line of commerce or the like.", "start": 3047.704, "stop": 3062.835, "duration": 15.13, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "the", "court", "please", "in", "response", "to", "our", "first", "plea", "in", "the", "district", "court", "their", "response", "be", "and", "I", "be", "quote", "from", "their", "district", "court", "brief", "the", "patent", "monopoly", "be", "a", "monopoly", "without", "consider", "line", "of", "commerce", "or", "the", "like"]]}, {"text": "That's where they started, that the patent grants monopoly.", "start": 3062.835, "stop": 3066.043, "duration": 3.21, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "where", "they", "start", "that", "the", "patent", "grant", "monopoly"]]}, {"text": "Now, the District Court stretched the -- the amended complaint, because it simply was frolics and unreadable.", "start": 3066.043, "stop": 3075.644, "duration": 9.6, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "district", "court", "stretch", "the", "the", "amended", "complaint", "because", "it", "simply", "be", "frolic", "and", "unreadable"]]}, {"text": "The same thing we had already suggested in our brief that they must -- if they are going to plea a monopolization case, plead, and establish relevant market, otherwise they're not talking about monopolization.", "start": 3075.644, "stop": 3087.697, "duration": 12.05, "cleanText": [["the", "same", "thing", "we", "have", "already", "suggest", "in", "our", "brief", "that", "they", "must", "if", "they", "be", "go", "to", "plea", "a", "monopolization", "case", "plead", "and", "establish", "relevant", "market", "otherwise", "they", "be", "not", "talk", "about", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "Maybe they are talking about some kind of unfair competition which however is not available to them.", "start": 3087.697, "stop": 3101.365, "duration": 13.67, "cleanText": [["maybe", "they", "be", "talk", "about", "some", "kind", "of", "unfair", "competition", "which", "however", "be", "not", "available", "to", "them"]]}, {"text": "Once again, in response to our briefs, that supported our motion to dismiss their second amended counterclaim which is the stricken pleading that is here before the Court, they take the position then and I insist that, if the Court please, they still sustain their position, they take no other position.", "start": 3101.365, "stop": 3119.803, "duration": 18.44, "cleanText": [["once", "again", "in", "response", "to", "our", "brief", "that", "support", "our", "motion", "to", "dismiss", "their", "second", "amend", "counterclaim", "which", "be", "the", "stricken", "pleading", "that", "be", "here", "before", "the", "court", "they", "take", "the", "position", "then", "and", "i", "insist", "that", "if", "the", "court", "please", "they", "still", "sustain", "their", "position", "they", "take", "no", "other", "position"]]}, {"text": "They say a patent is unquestionably monopolistic.", "start": 3119.803, "stop": 3123.449, "duration": 3.65, "cleanText": [["they", "say", "a", "patent", "be", "unquestionably", "monopolistic"]]}, {"text": "Although the patent statutes are inferential exemptions, there are limits to this inferential exemption.", "start": 3123.449, "stop": 3130.001, "duration": 6.55, "cleanText": [["although", "the", "patent", "statute", "be", "inferential", "exemption", "there", "be", "limit", "to", "this", "inferential", "exemption"]]}, {"text": "One who obtains a patent which he has no basis whatever than a fraudulent basis or who maintains it in spite of having only a false basis, is beyond those limits.", "start": 3130.001, "stop": 3141.025, "duration": 11.02, "cleanText": [["one", "who", "obtain", "a", "patent", "which", "he", "have", "no", "basis", "whatever", "than", "a", "fraudulent", "basis", "or", "who", "maintain", "it", "in", "spite", "of", "have", "only", "a", "false", "basis", "be", "beyond", "those", "limit"]]}, {"text": "And therefore, let it expose to the antitrust laws, and as accordingly adjoin a monopoly in violation of them, and is liable to those damage.", "start": 3141.025, "stop": 3152.263, "duration": 11.24, "cleanText": [["and", "therefore", "let", "it", "expose", "to", "the", "antitrust", "law", "and", "as", "accordingly", "adjoin", "a", "monopoly", "in", "violation", "of", "them", "and", "be", "liable", "to", "those", "damage"]]}, {"text": "Then, as their case, if the Court please, they are not pleading a case of monopolization from a sense of monopolization under Sherman Act Section 2.", "start": 3152.263, "stop": 3161.048, "duration": 8.78, "cleanText": [["then", "as", "their", "case", "if", "the", "court", "please", "they", "be", "not", "plead", "a", "case", "of", "monopolization", "from", "a", "sense", "of", "monopolization", "under", "sherman", "act", "section"]]}, {"text": "They don't want to, they don't intend to, they did not tendered such a case to the Court and they have had now three opportunities with two briefs below, indicating to them that if that's what they wanted to plead, that's the way they should do it.", "start": 3161.048, "stop": 3175.446, "duration": 14.4, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "want", "to", "they", "do", "not", "intend", "to", "they", "do", "not", "tender", "such", "a", "case", "to", "the", "court", "and", "they", "have", "have", "now", "three", "opportunity", "with", "two", "brief", "below", "indicate", "to", "them", "that", "if", "that", "be", "what", "they", "want", "to", "plead", "that", "be", "the", "way", "they", "should", "do", "it"]]}, {"text": "It should not be opened to them, it should -- it be opened to the Government to suggest that in the event, the claim that they pleaded could be extended into a claim under Sherman Act Section 2, that they can go back into the District Court to start out, to examine it to the relevant market.", "start": 3175.446, "stop": 3196.295, "duration": 20.85, "cleanText": [["it", "should", "not", "be", "open", "to", "them", "it", "should", "it", "be", "open", "to", "the", "government", "to", "suggest", "that", "in", "the", "event", "the", "claim", "that", "they", "plead", "could", "be", "extend", "into", "a", "claim", "under", "sherman", "act", "section", "that", "they", "can", "go", "back", "into", "the", "district", "court", "to", "start", "out", "to", "examine", "it", "to", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "I'll continue, if the Court please, tomorrow on that point.", "start": 3196.295, "stop": 3198.888, "duration": 2.59, "cleanText": [["I", "will", "continue", "if", "the", "court", "please", "tomorrow", "on", "that", "point"]]}]}]}, {"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - October 13, 1965", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren13/oral_argument_audio/23723", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Number 13, Walker Process Equipment Incorporated, Petitioner, versus Food Machinery & Chemical Corporation.", "start": 0, "stop": 10.722, "duration": 10.72, "cleanText": [["number", "walker", "process", "equipment", "incorporate", "petitioner", "versus", "food", "machinery", "chemical", "corporation"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Collen you may continue with your argument.", "start": 10.722, "stop": 13.761, "duration": 3.04, "cleanText": [["mr", "collen", "you", "may", "continue", "with", "your", "argument"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, may it please the Court.", "start": 13.761, "stop": 19.914, "duration": 6.15, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "In the time available yesterday I undertook to demonstrate to the Court that the only claim Walker really asserts is the claim of monopolization per se so to say.", "start": 19.914, "stop": 32.662, "duration": 12.75, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "time", "available", "yesterday", "i", "undertook", "to", "demonstrate", "to", "the", "court", "that", "the", "only", "claim", "walker", "really", "assert", "be", "the", "claim", "of", "monopolization", "per", "se", "so", "to", "say"]]}, {"text": "In Walker's view, recourse to the relevant market is unnecessary to establish -- excuse me, to establish monopolization.", "start": 32.662, "stop": 44.878, "duration": 12.22, "cleanText": [["in", "walker", "s", "view", "recourse", "to", "the", "relevant", "market", "be", "unnecessary", "to", "establish", "excuse", "me", "to", "establish", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "Moreover, even if at this late date they should take the position that it is open to them to now establish a relevant market in support of a definition of monopolization.", "start": 44.878, "stop": 57.688, "duration": 12.81, "cleanText": [["moreover", "even", "if", "at", "this", "late", "date", "they", "should", "take", "the", "position", "that", "it", "be", "open", "to", "them", "to", "now", "establish", "a", "relevant", "market", "in", "support", "of", "a", "definition", "of", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "Our position is, as I indicated yesterday, that after three counterclaims it would come too late.", "start": 57.688, "stop": 66.418, "duration": 8.73, "cleanText": [["our", "position", "be", "as", "i", "indicate", "yesterday", "that", "after", "three", "counterclaim", "it", "would", "come", "too", "late"]]}, {"text": "I would like, as a point of departure this morning, to review very briefly the stricken pleading so that we will have it in front of us and so that it will be clear to everyone if the Court please that they claim nothing other than monopolization because there -- our points in our brief which suggests some kind of analogy to illegal tying arrangements which are proscribed of course by Section 3 of the Clayton Act or by Section 1 of the Sherman Act.", "start": 66.418, "stop": 98.977, "duration": 32.56, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "as", "a", "point", "of", "departure", "this", "morning", "to", "review", "very", "briefly", "the", "stricken", "pleading", "so", "that", "we", "will", "have", "it", "in", "front", "of", "us", "and", "so", "that", "it", "will", "be", "clear", "to", "everyone", "if", "the", "court", "please", "that", "they", "claim", "nothing", "other", "than", "monopolization", "because", "there", "our", "point", "in", "our", "brief", "which", "suggest", "some", "kind", "of", "analogy", "to", "illegal", "tie", "arrangement", "which", "be", "proscribe", "of", "course", "by", "section", "of", "the", "clayton", "act", "or", "by", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act"]]}, {"text": "There is nothing to support any such claim in their pleading.", "start": 98.977, "stop": 104.085, "duration": 5.11, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "nothing", "to", "support", "any", "such", "claim", "in", "their", "pleading"]]}, {"text": "Now, if the Court please, the stricken pleading appears on page 60 of the record.", "start": 104.085, "stop": 109.97, "duration": 5.89, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "the", "court", "please", "the", "stricken", "pleading", "appear", "on", "page", "of", "the", "record"]]}, {"text": "They state in paragraph 15 that plaintiff including its predecessor illegally monopolized interstate and foreign commerce, that is their initial point of departure.", "start": 109.97, "stop": 123.392, "duration": 13.42, "cleanText": [["they", "state", "in", "paragraph", "that", "plaintiff", "include", "its", "predecessor", "illegally", "monopolize", "interstate", "and", "foreign", "commerce", "that", "be", "their", "initial", "point", "of", "departure"]]}, {"text": "They then say that the plaintiff used its patent to restrict and impede competition in interstate and foreign commerce in the sale of equipment not covered by the patent in suit thereby monopolizing trade in the said commerce.", "start": 123.392, "stop": 140.04, "duration": 16.65, "cleanText": [["they", "then", "say", "that", "the", "plaintiff", "use", "its", "patent", "to", "restrict", "and", "impede", "competition", "in", "interstate", "and", "foreign", "commerce", "in", "the", "sale", "of", "equipment", "not", "cover", "by", "the", "patent", "in", "suit", "thereby", "monopolize", "trade", "in", "the", "say", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "I might say parenthetically that to the extent of that paragraph which is paragraph 20 of the complaint appearing at page 62 of the record, may purport to set forth some kind of claim of illegal tie-ins.", "start": 140.04, "stop": 153.209, "duration": 13.17, "cleanText": [["i", "might", "say", "parenthetically", "that", "to", "the", "extent", "of", "that", "paragraph", "which", "be", "paragraph", "of", "the", "complaint", "appear", "at", "page", "of", "the", "record", "may", "purport", "to", "set", "forth", "some", "kind", "of", "claim", "of", "illegal", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "They have abandoned any such claim.", "start": 153.209, "stop": 155.612, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["they", "have", "abandon", "any", "such", "claim"]]}, {"text": "That is not before the Court.", "start": 155.612, "stop": 156.939, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "before", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "There is no question presented to the Court of illegal tie-ins.", "start": 156.939, "stop": 160.789, "duration": 3.85, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "question", "present", "to", "the", "court", "of", "illegal", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "I quoted that paragraph only to indicate that the -- the final bottom line of it is that the assertion is FMC is monopolizing.", "start": 160.789, "stop": 171.045, "duration": 10.26, "cleanText": [["i", "quote", "that", "paragraph", "only", "to", "indicate", "that", "the", "the", "final", "bottom", "line", "of", "it", "be", "that", "the", "assertion", "be", "fmc", "be", "monopolize"]]}, {"text": "Finally, in paragraph 2, they talk about plaintiff's unlawful monopoly.", "start": 171.045, "stop": 177.189, "duration": 6.14, "cleanText": [["finally", "in", "paragraph", "they", "talk", "about", "plaintiff", "s", "unlawful", "monopoly"]]}, {"text": "And the proper relief, if the Court please, is that this constitutes a fraud, that is the unclean hands that they're asserting, that this constitutes a fraud in the Patent Office and on this Court, a violation of antitrust laws and unjust enrichment of plaintiff.", "start": 177.189, "stop": 198.686, "duration": 21.5, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "proper", "relief", "if", "the", "court", "please", "be", "that", "this", "constitute", "a", "fraud", "that", "be", "the", "unclean", "hand", "that", "they", "be", "assert", "that", "this", "constitute", "a", "fraud", "in", "the", "patent", "office", "and", "on", "this", "court", "a", "violation", "of", "antitrust", "law", "and", "unjust", "enrichment", "of", "plaintiff"]]}, {"text": "Finally, in their brief at page 2 they say and I quote, A lawful patent monopoly is a recognized exception to the monopolies prohibited by Section 2 of the Sherman Act.", "start": 198.686, "stop": 216.022, "duration": 17.34, "cleanText": [["finally", "in", "their", "brief", "at", "page", "they", "say", "and", "i", "quote", "a", "lawful", "patent", "monopoly", "be", "a", "recognize", "exception", "to", "the", "monopoly", "prohibit", "by", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act"]]}, {"text": "I suggest, if the Court please, as Mr. Justice Fortas proceeded yesterday, that the Walker argument proves much too much.", "start": 216.022, "stop": 225.745, "duration": 9.72, "cleanText": [["i", "suggest", "if", "the", "court", "please", "as", "mr", "justice", "fortas", "proceed", "yesterday", "that", "the", "walker", "argument", "prove", "much", "too", "much"]]}, {"text": "The argument is based on the proposition that a patent affords a monopoly and that upon removal of the protection of the patent was we are left with an illegal monopoly within the scope of Section 2 of the Sherman Act, then I suggest would mean that any patent invalid for any reason whether it's by reason or fraudulent procurement or whether its by reasonable act of invention, or by reason of any other defect would have exactly the same consequence that Walker suggest in this case.", "start": 225.745, "stop": 261.593, "duration": 35.85, "cleanText": [["the", "argument", "be", "base", "on", "the", "proposition", "that", "a", "patent", "affords", "a", "monopoly", "and", "that", "upon", "removal", "of", "the", "protection", "of", "the", "patent", "be", "we", "be", "leave", "with", "an", "illegal", "monopoly", "within", "the", "scope", "of", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "then", "i", "suggest", "would", "mean", "that", "any", "patent", "invalid", "for", "any", "reason", "whether", "it", "be", "by", "reason", "or", "fraudulent", "procurement", "or", "whether", "its", "by", "reasonable", "act", "of", "invention", "or", "by", "reason", "of", "any", "other", "defect", "would", "have", "exactly", "the", "same", "consequence", "that", "walker", "suggest", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "So the entire premise that the fraudulent procurement of patent amounts without more, prima facie or per se to monopolization under Section 2 really attempts to prove much more than they begin to find necessary to prove.", "start": 261.593, "stop": 281.478, "duration": 19.88, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "entire", "premise", "that", "the", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "patent", "amount", "without", "more", "prima", "facie", "or", "per", "se", "to", "monopolization", "under", "section", "really", "attempt", "to", "prove", "much", "more", "than", "they", "begin", "to", "find", "necessary", "to", "prove"]]}, {"text": "And because it proves much more than as necessary it shows I think the essential insufficiency of the concept.", "start": 281.478, "stop": 289.881, "duration": 8.4, "cleanText": [["and", "because", "it", "prove", "much", "more", "than", "as", "necessary", "it", "show", "i", "think", "the", "essential", "insufficiency", "of", "the", "concept"]]}, {"text": "Now, the Government however comes to their aid in a sense by producing a more discriminating argument.", "start": 289.881, "stop": 299.052, "duration": 9.17, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "government", "however", "come", "to", "their", "aid", "in", "a", "sense", "by", "produce", "a", "more", "discriminating", "argument"]]}, {"text": "The Government really directly defines the offensive monopolization.", "start": 299.052, "stop": 306.092, "duration": 7.04, "cleanText": [["the", "government", "really", "directly", "define", "the", "offensive", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "At the Government's brief at page 12, they say that the offensive monopolization under Section 2 is established by proof, one that the defendant possess the power to exclude competitors from the relevant market and that the powers deliberately obtained or maintained.", "start": 306.092, "stop": 325.046, "duration": 18.95, "cleanText": [["at", "the", "government", "s", "brief", "at", "page", "they", "say", "that", "the", "offensive", "monopolization", "under", "section", "be", "establish", "by", "proof", "one", "that", "the", "defendant", "possess", "the", "power", "to", "exclude", "competitor", "from", "the", "relevant", "market", "and", "that", "the", "power", "deliberately", "obtain", "or", "maintain"]]}, {"text": "However, the Government rather than showing out its definition and applying it to the situation and asking where is the relevant market with respect to the patent which is suppose to constitute illegal monopolization under Section 2, takes the position for purposes of this case or I take it for purposes of any attack on the patent based on fraudulent procurement that the very scope of the patent's claims somehow presumes market control.", "start": 325.046, "stop": 359.23, "duration": 34.18, "cleanText": [["however", "the", "government", "rather", "than", "show", "out", "its", "definition", "and", "apply", "it", "to", "the", "situation", "and", "ask", "where", "be", "the", "relevant", "market", "with", "respect", "to", "the", "patent", "which", "be", "suppose", "to", "constitute", "illegal", "monopolization", "under", "section", "take", "the", "position", "for", "purpose", "of", "this", "case", "or", "i", "take", "it", "for", "purpose", "of", "any", "attack", "on", "the", "patent", "base", "on", "fraudulent", "procurement", "that", "the", "very", "scope", "of", "the", "patent", "s", "claim", "somehow", "presumes", "market", "control"]]}, {"text": "So the Government by that kind of prestidigitation, by that kind of presumption with one fell swoop as it were eliminates the necessity of looking to the relevant market.", "start": 359.23, "stop": 370.663, "duration": 11.43, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "government", "by", "that", "kind", "of", "prestidigitation", "by", "that", "kind", "of", "presumption", "with", "one", "fell", "swoop", "as", "it", "we", "be", "eliminate", "the", "necessity", "of", "look", "to", "the", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "Whereas the Court has in case after case after case, in the various Government agencies in case after case have carefully examined in monopolization cases a question of what constitutes the relevant market because the talk of monopolization or a controllable market without talking about the prescribed market is really to talk about one side of a point without the other.", "start": 370.663, "stop": 394.541, "duration": 23.88, "cleanText": [["whereas", "the", "court", "have", "in", "case", "after", "case", "after", "case", "in", "the", "various", "government", "agency", "in", "case", "after", "case", "have", "carefully", "examine", "in", "monopolization", "case", "a", "question", "of", "what", "constitute", "the", "relevant", "market", "because", "the", "talk", "of", "monopolization", "or", "a", "controllable", "market", "without", "talk", "about", "the", "prescribed", "market", "be", "really", "to", "talk", "about", "one", "side", "of", "a", "point", "without", "the", "other"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is this the first case in which a claim of this kind, antitrust claim of this kind has been asserted in the lower courts?", "start": 394.541, "stop": 402.677, "duration": 8.14, "cleanText": [["be", "this", "the", "first", "case", "in", "which", "a", "claim", "of", "this", "kind", "antitrust", "claim", "of", "this", "kind", "have", "be", "assert", "in", "the", "low", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh yes, Your Honor.", "start": 402.677, "stop": 404.012, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["oh", "yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "If --", "start": 404.012, "stop": 404.547, "duration": 0.54, "cleanText": [["if"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "There are no cases in the lower courts where this claim has been --", "start": 404.547, "stop": 408.364, "duration": 3.82, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "case", "in", "the", "low", "court", "where", "this", "claim", "have", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "There are certain --", "start": 408.364, "stop": 408.581, "duration": 0.22, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "certain"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- either passed upon or commented upon?", "start": 408.581, "stop": 411.129, "duration": 2.55, "cleanText": [["either", "pass", "upon", "or", "comment", "upon"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, there are not Your Honor.", "start": 411.129, "stop": 412.45, "duration": 1.32, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "not", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "There are no cases where the claim is that the fraudulent procurement of a patent is such.", "start": 412.45, "stop": 418.955, "duration": 6.5, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "case", "where", "the", "claim", "be", "that", "the", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "a", "patent", "be", "such"]]}, {"text": "The only attempted enforcement leaves you with the violation of Section 2 of the Sherman Act as illegal monopolization per se.", "start": 418.955, "stop": 427.207, "duration": 8.25, "cleanText": [["the", "only", "attempted", "enforcement", "leave", "you", "with", "the", "violation", "of", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "as", "illegal", "monopolization", "per", "se"]]}, {"text": "There is no case of that kind.", "start": 427.207, "stop": 429.017, "duration": 1.81, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "case", "of", "that", "kind"]]}, {"text": "Now, there are cases if the Court please which is -- are to be expected, where some kind of fraudulent procurement of a patent has been involved in a whole scheme or conspiracy or an attempted monopoly under Section 1 and Section 2 where like anything else, the fraudulent procurement of the patent comprises part of an overall plan to monopolize or part of an overall restraint of trade under Section 1.", "start": 429.017, "stop": 457.403, "duration": 28.39, "cleanText": [["now", "there", "be", "case", "if", "the", "court", "please", "which", "be", "be", "to", "be", "expect", "where", "some", "kind", "of", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "a", "patent", "have", "be", "involve", "in", "a", "whole", "scheme", "or", "conspiracy", "or", "an", "attempted", "monopoly", "under", "section", "and", "section", "where", "like", "anything", "else", "the", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "the", "patent", "comprise", "part", "of", "an", "overall", "plan", "to", "monopolize", "or", "part", "of", "an", "overall", "restraint", "of", "trade", "under", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that what you read the dictum of the Gypsum case to suggest?", "start": 457.403, "stop": 462.653, "duration": 5.25, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "what", "you", "read", "the", "dictum", "of", "the", "gypsum", "case", "to", "suggest"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the Gypsum case, if the Court please --", "start": 462.653, "stop": 464.137, "duration": 1.48, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "gypsum", "case", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Those are -- you refer to that, doesn't it?", "start": 464.137, "stop": 466.53, "duration": 2.39, "cleanText": [["those", "be", "you", "refer", "to", "that", "do", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I would say the Gypsum case -- although the Court acknowledged and I believe it was Mr. Justice Reed who wrote the opinion that the decision at that point was not necessary for a decision of the case.", "start": 466.53, "stop": 477.307, "duration": 10.78, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "would", "say", "the", "gypsum", "case", "although", "the", "court", "acknowledge", "and", "i", "believe", "it", "be", "mr", "justice", "reed", "who", "write", "the", "opinion", "that", "the", "decision", "at", "that", "point", "be", "not", "necessary", "for", "a", "decision", "of", "the", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, its dictum -- the Government admits that?", "start": 477.307, "stop": 479.483, "duration": 2.18, "cleanText": [["well", "its", "dictum", "the", "government", "admit", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, I would say that.", "start": 479.483, "stop": 481.046, "duration": 1.56, "cleanText": [["yes", "i", "would", "say", "that"]]}, {"text": "And likewise of course it's a suit by the Government.", "start": 481.046, "stop": 483.948, "duration": 2.9, "cleanText": [["and", "likewise", "of", "course", "it", "be", "a", "suit", "by", "the", "government"]]}, {"text": "It isn't a private suit where an individual is alleging injury.", "start": 483.948, "stop": 489.417, "duration": 5.47, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "a", "private", "suit", "where", "an", "individual", "be", "allege", "injury"]]}, {"text": "However there is nothing in their case Your Honor which would suggest that the procurement of the patent by fraudulent means would ergo without more or constitute illegal monopolization under Section 2.", "start": 489.417, "stop": 502.496, "duration": 13.08, "cleanText": [["however", "there", "be", "nothing", "in", "their", "case", "your", "honor", "which", "would", "suggest", "that", "the", "procurement", "of", "the", "patent", "by", "fraudulent", "mean", "would", "ergo", "without", "more", "or", "constitute", "illegal", "monopolization", "under", "section"]]}, {"text": "There we have a scheme of concert, a plan of action.", "start": 502.496, "stop": 509.812, "duration": 7.32, "cleanText": [["there", "we", "have", "a", "scheme", "of", "concert", "a", "plan", "of", "action"]]}, {"text": "Now, the Government yesterday made no real efforts to support the proposition that a patent somehow is prima facie support for or evidence of market control.", "start": 509.812, "stop": 523.695, "duration": 13.88, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "government", "yesterday", "make", "no", "real", "effort", "to", "support", "the", "proposition", "that", "a", "patent", "somehow", "be", "prima", "facie", "support", "for", "or", "evidence", "of", "market", "control"]]}, {"text": "I would like to suggest to the Court and I think there is no question about it that the case which they rely on, the Standard Stations case and the subsequent cases where the Court has in passing talked about a patent evidencing market control are strictly cases of tie-in agreements.", "start": 523.695, "stop": 543.9, "duration": 20.2, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "and", "i", "think", "there", "be", "no", "question", "about", "it", "that", "the", "case", "which", "they", "rely", "on", "the", "standard", "station", "case", "and", "the", "subsequent", "case", "where", "the", "court", "have", "in", "pass", "talk", "about", "a", "patent", "evidence", "market", "control", "be", "strictly", "case", "of", "tie", "in", "agreement"]]}, {"text": "These are cases either under Section 3 of the Clayton Act or under Section 1 of the Sherman Act.", "start": 543.9, "stop": 551.011, "duration": 7.11, "cleanText": [["these", "be", "case", "either", "under", "section", "of", "the", "clayton", "act", "or", "under", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act"]]}, {"text": "The question in those cases with respect to the patent is simply how much leverage is available to the patent holder as a means to accomplish his illegal tie-in.", "start": 551.011, "stop": 564.845, "duration": 13.83, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "in", "those", "case", "with", "respect", "to", "the", "patent", "be", "simply", "how", "much", "leverage", "be", "available", "to", "the", "patent", "holder", "as", "a", "mean", "to", "accomplish", "his", "illegal", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "For example, the inquiry really under Section 3 and that was the inquiry, in the Standard Stations case where the Court was comparing the perniciousness of requirements contracts to tying agreements.", "start": 564.845, "stop": 583.469, "duration": 18.62, "cleanText": [["for", "example", "the", "inquiry", "really", "under", "section", "and", "that", "be", "the", "inquiry", "in", "the", "standard", "station", "case", "where", "the", "court", "be", "compare", "the", "perniciousness", "of", "requirement", "contract", "to", "tie", "agreement"]]}, {"text": "The inquiry really is whether there is sufficient dominance over the tie-in product to have the leverage to be able to force the sale of the other products.", "start": 583.469, "stop": 594.772, "duration": 11.3, "cleanText": [["the", "inquiry", "really", "be", "whether", "there", "be", "sufficient", "dominance", "over", "the", "tie", "in", "product", "to", "have", "the", "leverage", "to", "be", "able", "to", "force", "the", "sale", "of", "the", "other", "product"]]}, {"text": "Now in that context, in the context of a tying arrangement where the question is really whether in fact there is actual power to accomplish a tying arrangement whether there's actual power to force the customer to take something besides the tying product.", "start": 594.772, "stop": 617.143, "duration": 22.37, "cleanText": [["now", "in", "that", "context", "in", "the", "context", "of", "a", "tying", "arrangement", "where", "the", "question", "be", "really", "whether", "in", "fact", "there", "be", "actual", "power", "to", "accomplish", "a", "tying", "arrangement", "whether", "there", "be", "actual", "power", "to", "force", "the", "customer", "to", "take", "something", "besides", "the", "tie", "product"]]}, {"text": "It -- for illustrative purposes was said in the Standard Stations case and subsequently in Times-Picayune, that yes, for that purpose a patent may be prima facie evidence of market control.", "start": 617.143, "stop": 632.03, "duration": 14.89, "cleanText": [["it", "for", "illustrative", "purpose", "be", "say", "in", "the", "standard", "station", "case", "and", "subsequently", "in", "time", "picayune", "that", "yes", "for", "that", "purpose", "a", "patent", "may", "be", "prima", "facie", "evidence", "of", "market", "control"]]}, {"text": "But I suggest to the Court that although for that purpose, a patent may suggest some kind of market control or dominance, that does not mean that for purposes of Section 2 of the Sherman Act that a patent all by itself completely defines a relevant market and constitutes monopolization under Section 2 of the Sherman Act if it should turn out to be an unlawfully obtained patent.", "start": 632.03, "stop": 675.092, "duration": 43.06, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "that", "although", "for", "that", "purpose", "a", "patent", "may", "suggest", "some", "kind", "of", "market", "control", "or", "dominance", "that", "do", "not", "mean", "that", "for", "purpose", "of", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "that", "a", "patent", "all", "by", "itself", "completely", "define", "a", "relevant", "market", "and", "constitute", "monopolization", "under", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "if", "it", "should", "turn", "out", "to", "be", "an", "unlawfully", "obtain", "patent"]]}, {"text": "I would like to quote in that connection and to summarize that suggestion to the Court from Times-Picayune, 345 U.S. at page 611.", "start": 675.092, "stop": 686.419, "duration": 11.33, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "quote", "in", "that", "connection", "and", "to", "summarize", "that", "suggestion", "to", "the", "court", "from", "time", "picayune", "us", "at", "page"]]}, {"text": "There the Court said that Section 2 outlaws monopolization of any appreciable part of interstate commerce and by Section 1 unreasonable restraints are banned irrespective of the amount of commerce involved.", "start": 686.419, "stop": 701.899, "duration": 15.48, "cleanText": [["there", "the", "court", "say", "that", "section", "outlaws", "monopolization", "of", "any", "appreciable", "part", "of", "interstate", "commerce", "and", "by", "section", "unreasonable", "restraint", "be", "ban", "irrespective", "of", "the", "amount", "of", "commerce", "involve"]]}, {"text": "But the essence of illegality in tying agreements is the wielding of monopolistic leverage, a seller exploits his dominant position in one market to expand his empire into the next.", "start": 701.899, "stop": 716.719, "duration": 14.82, "cleanText": [["but", "the", "essence", "of", "illegality", "in", "tie", "agreement", "be", "the", "wielding", "of", "monopolistic", "leverage", "a", "seller", "exploit", "his", "dominant", "position", "in", "one", "market", "to", "expand", "his", "empire", "into", "the", "next"]]}, {"text": "So I suggest to the Court finally that for purposes of understanding the basic nature of a tying agreement and the kind of control that had defended may have been such a situation.", "start": 716.719, "stop": 729.207, "duration": 12.49, "cleanText": [["so", "i", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "finally", "that", "for", "purpose", "of", "understand", "the", "basic", "nature", "of", "a", "tying", "agreement", "and", "the", "kind", "of", "control", "that", "have", "defend", "may", "have", "be", "such", "a", "situation"]]}, {"text": "Yes, for that purpose, control to a patent may suggest the capacity, the ability prima facie to force a tying arrangement.", "start": 729.207, "stop": 740.066, "duration": 10.86, "cleanText": [["yes", "for", "that", "purpose", "control", "to", "a", "patent", "may", "suggest", "the", "capacity", "the", "ability", "prima", "facie", "to", "force", "a", "tying", "arrangement"]]}, {"text": "But again, I suggest that has nothing to do with the definition of monopolization under Section 2 of the Sherman Act.", "start": 740.066, "stop": 748.335, "duration": 8.27, "cleanText": [["but", "again", "i", "suggest", "that", "have", "nothing", "to", "do", "with", "the", "definition", "of", "monopolization", "under", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act"]]}, {"text": "Now, I suggest if the Court please that that approach, that argument that the Government advances to relieve itself from the necessity of making a market investigation and to arrive at the concept of per se illegality is completely specious --", "start": 748.335, "stop": 767.072, "duration": 18.74, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "suggest", "if", "the", "court", "please", "that", "that", "approach", "that", "argument", "that", "the", "government", "advance", "to", "relieve", "itself", "from", "the", "necessity", "of", "make", "a", "market", "investigation", "and", "to", "arrive", "at", "the", "concept", "of", "per", "se", "illegality", "be", "completely", "specious"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Has the patent expired?", "start": 767.072, "stop": 770.329, "duration": 3.26, "cleanText": [["have", "the", "patent", "expire"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, the patent has expired.", "start": 770.329, "stop": 771.891, "duration": 1.56, "cleanText": [["yes", "the", "patent", "have", "expire"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "In what year has it expired?", "start": 771.891, "stop": 773.658, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["in", "what", "year", "have", "it", "expire"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "In 1961 -- 1960, Your Honor.", "start": 773.658, "stop": 778.762, "duration": 5.1, "cleanText": [["in", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "I might say, in response to Miranda's question, the suit was filed about six months before this patent expired.", "start": 778.762, "stop": 784.604, "duration": 5.84, "cleanText": [["i", "might", "say", "in", "response", "to", "miranda", "s", "question", "the", "suit", "be", "file", "about", "six", "month", "before", "this", "patent", "expire"]]}, {"text": "It was the only known infringement by this defendant.", "start": 784.604, "stop": 788.121, "duration": 3.52, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "only", "know", "infringement", "by", "this", "defendant"]]}, {"text": "Now, for purposes of the counterclaim Your Honor and for purposes of the amendments to the counterclaim, under the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure, the amendments relate back to the date of filing of those counterclaims.", "start": 788.121, "stop": 800.982, "duration": 12.86, "cleanText": [["now", "for", "purpose", "of", "the", "counterclaim", "your", "honor", "and", "for", "purpose", "of", "the", "amendment", "to", "the", "counterclaim", "under", "the", "federal", "rule", "of", "civil", "procedure", "the", "amendment", "relate", "back", "to", "the", "date", "of", "filing", "of", "those", "counterclaim"]]}, {"text": "So for purposes of analysis of the case, the counterclaim speaks as of the date it was filed during which time the patent was still enforce in effect.", "start": 800.982, "stop": 817.609, "duration": 16.63, "cleanText": [["so", "for", "purpose", "of", "analysis", "of", "the", "case", "the", "counterclaim", "speak", "as", "of", "the", "date", "it", "be", "file", "during", "which", "time", "the", "patent", "be", "still", "enforce", "in", "effect"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "Counsel, may I ask you a question?", "start": 817.609, "stop": 820.707, "duration": 3.1, "cleanText": [["counsel", "may", "i", "ask", "you", "a", "question"]]}, {"text": "Suppose that paragraph 20 were not abandoned, paragraph 20 in the counterclaims were not abandoned by the petitioner, you claim that it has been abandoned?", "start": 820.707, "stop": 834.471, "duration": 13.76, "cleanText": [["suppose", "that", "paragraph", "we", "be", "not", "abandon", "paragraph", "in", "the", "counterclaim", "we", "be", "not", "abandon", "by", "the", "petitioner", "you", "claim", "that", "it", "have", "be", "abandon"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes sir.", "start": 834.471, "stop": 834.674, "duration": 0.2, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's the allegation of tie-in.", "start": 834.674, "stop": 837.615, "duration": 2.94, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "allegation", "of", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "Is it your position that if that paragraph is still alive and not abandoned, nevertheless this counterclaim does not state a cause of action?", "start": 837.615, "stop": 852.018, "duration": 14.4, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "your", "position", "that", "if", "that", "paragraph", "be", "still", "alive", "and", "not", "abandon", "nevertheless", "this", "counterclaim", "do", "not", "state", "a", "because", "of", "action"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes it is Your Honor.", "start": 852.018, "stop": 852.949, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["yes", "it", "be", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "I think by the terms of paragraph 20, it -- on its face it's not sufficient to state a claims for illegal tie-ins.", "start": 852.949, "stop": 861.882, "duration": 8.93, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "by", "the", "term", "of", "paragraph", "it", "on", "its", "face", "it", "be", "not", "sufficient", "to", "state", "a", "claim", "for", "illegal", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "I would like Your Honor if you please to read paragraph 17 of their previous amended counterclaim.", "start": 861.882, "stop": 870.002, "duration": 8.12, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "your", "honor", "if", "you", "please", "to", "read", "paragraph", "of", "their", "previous", "amend", "counterclaim"]]}, {"text": "In that paragraph which was the father so to say of paragraph 20.", "start": 870.002, "stop": 876.515, "duration": 6.51, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "paragraph", "which", "be", "the", "father", "so", "to", "say", "of", "paragraph"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "What page is that?", "start": 876.515, "stop": 879.036, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["what", "page", "be", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's at page 73, if the Court please.", "start": 879.036, "stop": 889.063, "duration": 10.03, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "at", "page", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}, {"text": "There, on page 73 is the effort in their predecessor counterclaim to set forth some kind of claim of illegal tie-ins.", "start": 889.063, "stop": 899.155, "duration": 10.09, "cleanText": [["there", "on", "page", "be", "the", "effort", "in", "their", "predecessor", "counterclaim", "to", "set", "forth", "some", "kind", "of", "claim", "of", "illegal", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "By their paragraph A and B, I think it will be perfectly apparent to the Court that all they were suggesting was that in connection with it's offer of -- a subject swing, refusal of units, FMC was off also selling a considerable amount of other equipment.", "start": 899.155, "stop": 919.061, "duration": 19.91, "cleanText": [["by", "their", "paragraph", "a", "and", "b", "i", "think", "it", "will", "be", "perfectly", "apparent", "to", "the", "court", "that", "all", "they", "we", "be", "suggest", "be", "that", "in", "connection", "with", "it", "be", "offer", "of", "a", "subject", "swing", "refusal", "of", "unit", "fmc", "be", "off", "also", "sell", "a", "considerable", "amount", "of", "other", "equipment"]]}, {"text": "There was nothing in the predecessor paragraph 17 or those subparagraphs to suggest that they were tying or forcing and indeed they were not Your Honor and that is why when they finally framed it, the new paragraph 20, they eliminated the subparagraphs A and B because under its face, they did not a show a tie-in.", "start": 919.061, "stop": 940.231, "duration": 21.17, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "nothing", "in", "the", "predecessor", "paragraph", "or", "those", "subparagraphs", "to", "suggest", "that", "they", "we", "be", "tie", "or", "force", "and", "indeed", "they", "we", "be", "not", "your", "honor", "and", "that", "be", "why", "when", "they", "finally", "frame", "it", "the", "new", "paragraph", "they", "eliminate", "the", "subparagraphs", "a", "and", "b", "because", "under", "its", "face", "they", "do", "not", "a", "show", "a", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "They did not brief this question in the Court of Appeals even though 20 was still in there.", "start": 940.231, "stop": 944.483, "duration": 4.25, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "brief", "this", "question", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "even", "though", "be", "still", "in", "there"]]}, {"text": "We took the position then that they had abandoned it and there just -- is not any tying situation in this case, if the Court please.", "start": 944.483, "stop": 951.123, "duration": 6.64, "cleanText": [["we", "take", "the", "position", "then", "that", "they", "have", "abandon", "it", "and", "there", "just", "be", "not", "any", "tie", "situation", "in", "this", "case", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that may or may not be premature at this stage.", "start": 951.123, "stop": 956.115, "duration": 4.99, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "may", "or", "may", "not", "be", "premature", "at", "this", "stage"]]}, {"text": "But let me ask you another question, suppose the counterclaim alleged in general terms that the plaintiff had monopolized trade in commerce, proposition one.", "start": 956.115, "stop": 970.484, "duration": 14.37, "cleanText": [["but", "let", "me", "ask", "you", "another", "question", "suppose", "the", "counterclaim", "allege", "in", "general", "term", "that", "the", "plaintiff", "have", "monopolize", "trade", "in", "commerce", "proposition", "one"]]}, {"text": "Proposition 2, that plaintiff had done this by use of a patent.", "start": 970.484, "stop": 978.611, "duration": 8.13, "cleanText": [["proposition", "that", "plaintiff", "have", "do", "this", "by", "use", "of", "a", "patent"]]}, {"text": "Proposition three, that the patent was fraudulently obtained.", "start": 978.611, "stop": 984.123, "duration": 5.51, "cleanText": [["proposition", "three", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "fraudulently", "obtain"]]}, {"text": "Suppose the counterclaim had said that or couldn't be construed to say that, would it still be your position that it would not state a valid cause of action?", "start": 984.123, "stop": 995.027, "duration": 10.9, "cleanText": [["suppose", "the", "counterclaim", "have", "say", "that", "or", "could", "not", "be", "construe", "to", "say", "that", "would", "it", "still", "be", "your", "position", "that", "it", "would", "not", "state", "a", "valid", "because", "of", "action"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I think Your Honor.", "start": 995.027, "stop": 996.102, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "think", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Under no circumstances, it would be open to them to establish monopolization.", "start": 996.102, "stop": 1001.24, "duration": 5.14, "cleanText": [["under", "no", "circumstance", "it", "would", "be", "open", "to", "them", "to", "establish", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "But our position in this case is that they make it perfectly clear that that is not what they intend to do that they --", "start": 1001.24, "stop": 1008.634, "duration": 7.39, "cleanText": [["but", "our", "position", "in", "this", "case", "be", "that", "they", "make", "it", "perfectly", "clear", "that", "that", "be", "not", "what", "they", "intend", "to", "do", "that", "they"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "That would be a rather (Inaudible)", "start": 1008.634, "stop": 1014.159, "duration": 5.52, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "be", "a", "rather", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, thank you Your Honor, I think it would.", "start": 1014.159, "stop": 1017.371, "duration": 3.21, "cleanText": [["yes", "thank", "you", "your", "honor", "i", "think", "it", "would"]]}, {"text": "But as I started out yesterday and as I'll say again in passing and as I will finally conclude, the question they present to this Court, the position they've always asserted is this per se position.", "start": 1017.371, "stop": 1030.131, "duration": 12.76, "cleanText": [["but", "as", "i", "start", "out", "yesterday", "and", "as", "I", "will", "say", "again", "in", "pass", "and", "as", "i", "will", "finally", "conclude", "the", "question", "they", "present", "to", "this", "court", "the", "position", "they", "have", "always", "assert", "be", "this", "per", "se", "position"]]}, {"text": "And there was nothing else --", "start": 1030.131, "stop": 1030.253, "duration": 0.12, "cleanText": [["and", "there", "be", "nothing", "else"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, is that the -- except yesterday, the answer was that they are asserting the other position.", "start": 1030.253, "stop": 1039.744, "duration": 9.49, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "that", "the", "except", "yesterday", "the", "answer", "be", "that", "they", "be", "assert", "the", "other", "position"]]}, {"text": "They may not have before, I don't know about that.", "start": 1039.744, "stop": 1042.876, "duration": 3.13, "cleanText": [["they", "may", "not", "have", "before", "i", "do", "not", "know", "about", "that"]]}, {"text": "But yesterday, the assertion was that if we do not agree with them that this is a per se matter that the -- that they think the case should be remanded for the proceedings in the trial court.", "start": 1042.876, "stop": 1057.952, "duration": 15.08, "cleanText": [["but", "yesterday", "the", "assertion", "be", "that", "if", "we", "do", "not", "agree", "with", "them", "that", "this", "be", "a", "per", "se", "matter", "that", "the", "that", "they", "think", "the", "case", "should", "be", "remand", "for", "the", "proceeding", "in", "the", "trial", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "If Your Honor please, I don't believe counsel for Walker said that.", "start": 1057.952, "stop": 1061.218, "duration": 3.27, "cleanText": [["if", "your", "honor", "please", "i", "do", "not", "believe", "counsel", "for", "walker", "say", "that"]]}, {"text": "I think the Government mind that suggestion gratuitously as you press them to ascertain whether their position was for per se illegality.", "start": 1061.218, "stop": 1071.464, "duration": 10.25, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "government", "mind", "that", "suggestion", "gratuitously", "as", "you", "press", "them", "to", "ascertain", "whether", "their", "position", "be", "for", "per", "se", "illegality"]]}, {"text": "I do acknowledge of course in the reply brief of Walker, they do with a wave of their hand say, Well, if relevant, Walker has anything to do with it, we could always supply that.", "start": 1071.464, "stop": 1082.483, "duration": 11.02, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "acknowledge", "of", "course", "in", "the", "reply", "brief", "of", "walker", "they", "do", "with", "a", "wave", "of", "their", "hand", "say", "well", "if", "relevant", "walker", "have", "anything", "to", "do", "with", "it", "we", "could", "always", "supply", "that"]]}, {"text": "I suggest in that connections Your Honor that -- and I suppose it's only a truism, there must be an end to litigation at some point.", "start": 1082.483, "stop": 1091.331, "duration": 8.85, "cleanText": [["i", "suggest", "in", "that", "connection", "your", "honor", "that", "and", "i", "suppose", "it", "be", "only", "a", "truism", "there", "must", "be", "an", "end", "to", "litigation", "at", "some", "point"]]}, {"text": "These people have taken this position twice in the District Court, once in the Court of Appeals.", "start": 1091.331, "stop": 1097.393, "duration": 6.06, "cleanText": [["these", "people", "have", "take", "this", "position", "twice", "in", "the", "district", "court", "once", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal"]]}, {"text": "They have successfully petitioned this Court to get a determination of the per se question, that they have insisted is what they're asking for.", "start": 1097.393, "stop": 1106.578, "duration": 9.18, "cleanText": [["they", "have", "successfully", "petition", "this", "court", "to", "get", "a", "determination", "of", "the", "per", "se", "question", "that", "they", "have", "insist", "be", "what", "they", "be", "ask", "for"]]}, {"text": "It should not be open to them under any circumstances after the filing of three counterclaims, after putting everybody in the judicial processes to work -- to get an adjudication of that to decide they don't need an adjudication of that.", "start": 1106.578, "stop": 1121.236, "duration": 14.66, "cleanText": [["it", "should", "not", "be", "open", "to", "them", "under", "any", "circumstance", "after", "the", "filing", "of", "three", "counterclaim", "after", "put", "everybody", "in", "the", "judicial", "process", "to", "work", "to", "get", "an", "adjudication", "of", "that", "to", "decide", "they", "do", "not", "need", "an", "adjudication", "of", "that"]]}, {"text": "They can just go back and set off with a new complaint.", "start": 1121.236, "stop": 1124.897, "duration": 3.66, "cleanText": [["they", "can", "just", "go", "back", "and", "set", "off", "with", "a", "new", "complaint"]]}, {"text": "They could have done that after we filed our motion to strike their first counterclaim and to dismiss it.", "start": 1124.897, "stop": 1131.787, "duration": 6.89, "cleanText": [["they", "could", "have", "do", "that", "after", "we", "file", "our", "motion", "to", "strike", "their", "first", "counterclaim", "and", "to", "dismiss", "it"]]}, {"text": "We said then and there, this is not --", "start": 1131.787, "stop": 1133.937, "duration": 2.15, "cleanText": [["we", "say", "then", "and", "there", "this", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That -- they wouldn't have done them any good in the lower courts.", "start": 1133.937, "stop": 1136.048, "duration": 2.11, "cleanText": [["that", "they", "would", "not", "have", "do", "them", "any", "good", "in", "the", "low", "court"]]}, {"text": "In the theory of the lower court, they've applied anything they wanted to and it wouldn't have got them to first pay?", "start": 1136.048, "stop": 1142.059, "duration": 6.01, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "theory", "of", "the", "low", "court", "they", "have", "apply", "anything", "they", "want", "to", "and", "it", "would", "not", "have", "get", "them", "to", "first", "pay"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh no, I don't think that is correct if the Court please.", "start": 1142.059, "stop": 1143.922, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["oh", "no", "i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "be", "correct", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what the -- this Court of Appeals, it seems to me would've have thrown them out no matter what they plead.", "start": 1143.922, "stop": 1148.868, "duration": 4.95, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "the", "this", "court", "of", "appeal", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "would", "have", "have", "throw", "them", "out", "no", "matter", "what", "they", "plead"]]}, {"text": "This was an effort to cancel the patent and only the United States had the right to cancel it.", "start": 1148.868, "stop": 1153.556, "duration": 4.69, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "an", "effort", "to", "cancel", "the", "patent", "and", "only", "the", "united", "state", "have", "the", "right", "to", "cancel", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "They -- that is correct.", "start": 1153.556, "stop": 1154.705, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["they", "that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "I think on that basis, the Court of Appeals would have thrown them out but that is --", "start": 1154.705, "stop": 1158.694, "duration": 3.99, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "on", "that", "basis", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "would", "have", "throw", "them", "out", "but", "that", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, the District Court.", "start": 1158.694, "stop": 1162.216, "duration": 3.52, "cleanText": [["oh", "the", "district", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think on the same basis, the District Court were to throw them out.", "start": 1162.216, "stop": 1165.465, "duration": 3.25, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "on", "the", "same", "basis", "the", "district", "court", "we", "be", "to", "throw", "them", "out"]]}, {"text": "But notwithstanding that that is not the question that they present at this point.", "start": 1165.465, "stop": 1171.125, "duration": 5.66, "cleanText": [["but", "notwithstanding", "that", "that", "be", "not", "the", "question", "that", "they", "present", "at", "this", "point"]]}, {"text": "I would like to say Your Honor too, that when they file their original counterclaims, there was no suggestion of what they were really complaining about.", "start": 1171.125, "stop": 1179.21, "duration": 8.09, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "say", "your", "honor", "too", "that", "when", "they", "file", "their", "original", "counterclaim", "there", "be", "no", "suggestion", "of", "what", "they", "we", "be", "really", "complain", "about"]]}, {"text": "They did not refer to Section 1.", "start": 1179.21, "stop": 1181.727, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "refer", "to", "section"]]}, {"text": "They didn't refer to Section 2.", "start": 1181.727, "stop": 1183.178, "duration": 1.45, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "refer", "to", "section"]]}, {"text": "They didn't refer to Clayton Act Section 3.", "start": 1183.178, "stop": 1185.736, "duration": 2.56, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "refer", "to", "clayton", "act", "section"]]}, {"text": "They just said this violates the antitrust laws, and in addition, as I've suggested to the Court --", "start": 1185.736, "stop": 1191.455, "duration": 5.72, "cleanText": [["they", "just", "say", "this", "violate", "the", "antitrust", "law", "and", "in", "addition", "as", "I", "have", "suggest", "to", "the", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible) position of the District Court and the Court of Appeals.", "start": 1191.455, "stop": 1195.64, "duration": 4.19, "cleanText": [["inaudible", "position", "of", "the", "district", "court", "and", "the", "court", "of", "appeal"]]}, {"text": "It was that this was -- that this couldn't be made an antitrust case at all, wasn't it?", "start": 1195.64, "stop": 1201.738, "duration": 6.1, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "that", "this", "be", "that", "this", "could", "not", "be", "make", "an", "antitrust", "case", "at", "all", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's -- that is correct Your Honor, on the basis of the way --", "start": 1201.738, "stop": 1204.339, "duration": 2.6, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "that", "be", "correct", "your", "honor", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "the", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yours was the same position that the Court took?", "start": 1204.339, "stop": 1206.546, "duration": 2.21, "cleanText": [["yours", "be", "the", "same", "position", "that", "the", "court", "take"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 1206.546, "stop": 1207.768, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "That is correct.", "start": 1207.768, "stop": 1208.377, "duration": 0.61, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}, {"text": "On the basis of the Court of Appeals decision, it could not be made into an antitrust case.", "start": 1208.377, "stop": 1214.051, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "basis", "of", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "decision", "it", "could", "not", "be", "make", "into", "an", "antitrust", "case"]]}, {"text": "I suggest to the Court that that is probably an inaccurate position to take.", "start": 1214.051, "stop": 1219.149, "duration": 5.1, "cleanText": [["i", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "that", "that", "be", "probably", "an", "inaccurate", "position", "to", "take"]]}, {"text": "I think the Court of Appeals opinion is cryptic.", "start": 1219.149, "stop": 1223.115, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "opinion", "be", "cryptic"]]}, {"text": "It's impossible in some ways to determine when the Court is describing the position of the parties and when it's reaching this conclusion.", "start": 1223.115, "stop": 1231.319, "duration": 8.2, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "impossible", "in", "some", "way", "to", "determine", "when", "the", "court", "be", "describe", "the", "position", "of", "the", "party", "and", "when", "it", "be", "reach", "this", "conclusion"]]}, {"text": "But I would like to suggest to the Court that there was --", "start": 1231.319, "stop": 1233.369, "duration": 2.05, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "would", "like", "to", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "that", "there", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 1233.369, "stop": 1256.432, "duration": 23.06, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, that is certainly correct Your Honor.", "start": 1256.432, "stop": 1258.974, "duration": 2.54, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "certainly", "correct", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "That is certainly correct.", "start": 1258.974, "stop": 1259.56, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "certainly", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 1259.56, "stop": 1270.405, "duration": 10.85, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct Your Honor, no.", "start": 1270.405, "stop": 1275.479, "duration": 5.07, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "your", "honor", "no"]]}, {"text": "If the Court please -- in returning to your inquiry Mr. Justice White, besides talking about antitrust violation they talked about unfair competition, they talked about unjust enrichment.", "start": 1275.479, "stop": 1289.662, "duration": 14.18, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "court", "please", "in", "return", "to", "your", "inquiry", "mr", "justice", "white", "besides", "talk", "about", "antitrust", "violation", "they", "talk", "about", "unfair", "competition", "they", "talk", "about", "unjust", "enrichment"]]}, {"text": "They argued to the Court of Appeals that they did not have the obligation to provide a legal category on the basis on which relief was available, that they were hurt in some way by the so-called fraudulent procurement.", "start": 1289.662, "stop": 1303.02, "duration": 13.36, "cleanText": [["they", "argue", "to", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "that", "they", "do", "not", "have", "the", "obligation", "to", "provide", "a", "legal", "category", "on", "the", "basis", "on", "which", "relief", "be", "available", "that", "they", "we", "be", "hurt", "in", "some", "way", "by", "the", "so", "called", "fraudulent", "procurement"]]}, {"text": "They must have some remedy.", "start": 1303.02, "stop": 1305.328, "duration": 2.31, "cleanText": [["they", "must", "have", "some", "remedy"]]}, {"text": "And the response to the proposition that they must have some remedy was the proposition finally adopted by the Court but not expressed if the Court please, in a very artistic fashion.", "start": 1305.328, "stop": 1317.041, "duration": 11.71, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "response", "to", "the", "proposition", "that", "they", "must", "have", "some", "remedy", "be", "the", "proposition", "finally", "adopt", "by", "the", "court", "but", "not", "express", "if", "the", "court", "please", "in", "a", "very", "artistic", "fashion"]]}, {"text": "That there was no automatic conversion feature between this defense of unclean hands or fraudulent procurement and the availability of any kind of affirmative relief.", "start": 1317.041, "stop": 1327.657, "duration": 10.62, "cleanText": [["that", "there", "be", "no", "automatic", "conversion", "feature", "between", "this", "defense", "of", "unclean", "hand", "or", "fraudulent", "procurement", "and", "the", "availability", "of", "any", "kind", "of", "affirmative", "relief"]]}, {"text": "Now, that had been the law in the Seventh Circuit and the District Courts had followed that.", "start": 1327.657, "stop": 1333.757, "duration": 6.1, "cleanText": [["now", "that", "have", "be", "the", "law", "in", "the", "seventh", "circuit", "and", "the", "district", "court", "have", "follow", "that"]]}, {"text": "I agree that the problem of the opinion of the Court of Appeals would leave them if the Court of Appeals' opinion stood in a position where under no circumstances they could -- they plead a good and valid monopolization case under Section 2.", "start": 1333.757, "stop": 1353.673, "duration": 19.92, "cleanText": [["i", "agree", "that", "the", "problem", "of", "the", "opinion", "of", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "would", "leave", "them", "if", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "opinion", "stand", "in", "a", "position", "where", "under", "no", "circumstance", "they", "could", "they", "plead", "a", "good", "and", "valid", "monopolization", "case", "under", "section"]]}, {"text": "But I also suggest that the most that's involved in the Court of Appeals' opinion in -- on that basis is a hypothetical question.", "start": 1353.673, "stop": 1363.281, "duration": 9.61, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "also", "suggest", "that", "the", "most", "that", "be", "involve", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "opinion", "in", "on", "that", "basis", "be", "a", "hypothetical", "question"]]}, {"text": "What the Court of Appeals in effect says and what bothers the Government in the Court of Appeals' opinion is that the Gov -- the Court of Appeals suggest that fraud in the Patent Office can never be part of a showing of violation of the antitrust laws.", "start": 1363.281, "stop": 1376.061, "duration": 12.78, "cleanText": [["what", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "in", "effect", "say", "and", "what", "bother", "the", "government", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "opinion", "be", "that", "the", "gov", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "suggest", "that", "fraud", "in", "the", "patent", "office", "can", "never", "be", "part", "of", "a", "showing", "of", "violation", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "Now if all that this Court were concerned with were the opinion of the Court of Appeals, then this Court would say, I suggest, that that is inaccurate.", "start": 1376.061, "stop": 1384.734, "duration": 8.67, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "all", "that", "this", "court", "we", "be", "concern", "with", "we", "be", "the", "opinion", "of", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "then", "this", "court", "would", "say", "i", "suggest", "that", "that", "be", "inaccurate"]]}, {"text": "That certainly, under appropriate circumstances, fraud on the Patent Office could be a violation of Section 1 or of Section 2.", "start": 1384.734, "stop": 1393.668, "duration": 8.93, "cleanText": [["that", "certainly", "under", "appropriate", "circumstance", "fraud", "on", "the", "patent", "office", "could", "be", "a", "violation", "of", "section", "or", "of", "section"]]}, {"text": "But if we are left with only that hypothetical consideration, that cannot dispose of the litigation and I suggest very emphatically that that is not the question as they presented to this Court.", "start": 1393.668, "stop": 1405.661, "duration": 11.99, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "we", "be", "leave", "with", "only", "that", "hypothetical", "consideration", "that", "can", "not", "dispose", "of", "the", "litigation", "and", "i", "suggest", "very", "emphatically", "that", "that", "be", "not", "the", "question", "as", "they", "present", "to", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "And what attracted the Government to this case, I suggest, and the reason they came in was an opportunity to find a new area of per se illegality.", "start": 1405.661, "stop": 1415.24, "duration": 9.58, "cleanText": [["and", "what", "attract", "the", "government", "to", "this", "case", "i", "suggest", "and", "the", "reason", "they", "come", "in", "be", "an", "opportunity", "to", "find", "a", "new", "area", "of", "per", "se", "illegality"]]}, {"text": "Here where you have a patent allegedly procured by fraud.", "start": 1415.24, "stop": 1420.992, "duration": 5.75, "cleanText": [["here", "where", "you", "have", "a", "patent", "allegedly", "procure", "by", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "You have Section 2 monopolization without more.", "start": 1420.992, "stop": 1423.923, "duration": 2.93, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "section", "monopolization", "without", "more"]]}, {"text": "The relevant market is presumed and if the Court please, now the Justice Department should go out and get a summary judgment without any market investigation, without any study of the relevant factors.", "start": 1423.923, "stop": 1435.932, "duration": 12.01, "cleanText": [["the", "relevant", "market", "be", "presume", "and", "if", "the", "court", "please", "now", "the", "justice", "department", "should", "go", "out", "and", "get", "a", "summary", "judgment", "without", "any", "market", "investigation", "without", "any", "study", "of", "the", "relevant", "factor"]]}, {"text": "If it can just establish that the patent was procured by fraud and then enforced, I suggest that is why the Justice Department came into this case.", "start": 1435.932, "stop": 1444.962, "duration": 9.03, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "can", "just", "establish", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "procure", "by", "fraud", "and", "then", "enforce", "i", "suggest", "that", "be", "why", "the", "justice", "department", "come", "into", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "If there were only the question of the correctness of the Court of Appeals' opinion, the Justice Department would be unable to take the position it does by its question in this case.", "start": 1444.962, "stop": 1456.276, "duration": 11.31, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "we", "be", "only", "the", "question", "of", "the", "correctness", "of", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "opinion", "the", "justice", "department", "would", "be", "unable", "to", "take", "the", "position", "it", "do", "by", "its", "question", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "In question two, which is the question for certiorari presented by Walker, would not really be controlling.", "start": 1456.276, "stop": 1464.674, "duration": 8.4, "cleanText": [["in", "question", "two", "which", "be", "the", "question", "for", "certiorari", "present", "by", "walker", "would", "not", "really", "be", "control"]]}, {"text": "Now the Court, as I understand it, in the exercise of the certiorari jurisdiction is concerning itself with the question presented by the party and it is their question that they presented and we are undertaking as best as we can to show the insufficiency of their solution to the question.", "start": 1464.674, "stop": 1484.319, "duration": 19.64, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "court", "as", "i", "understand", "it", "in", "the", "exercise", "of", "the", "certiorari", "jurisdiction", "be", "concern", "itself", "with", "the", "question", "present", "by", "the", "party", "and", "it", "be", "their", "question", "that", "they", "present", "and", "we", "be", "undertake", "as", "best", "as", "we", "can", "to", "show", "the", "insufficiency", "of", "their", "solution", "to", "the", "question"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 1484.319, "stop": 1498.732, "duration": 14.41, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't believe so Your Honor because they contend that a component of the cause of action or the claim is that FMC undertook to enforce its patent against them.", "start": 1498.732, "stop": 1510.229, "duration": 11.5, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "believe", "so", "your", "honor", "because", "they", "contend", "that", "a", "component", "of", "the", "because", "of", "action", "or", "the", "claim", "be", "that", "fmc", "undertook", "to", "enforce", "its", "patent", "against", "them"]]}, {"text": "So we filed a patent infringement suit back in 1960 while as of today there would be a problem because four years have expired since the last act in connection with the original cause of action.", "start": 1510.229, "stop": 1525.389, "duration": 15.16, "cleanText": [["so", "we", "file", "a", "patent", "infringement", "suit", "back", "in", "while", "as", "of", "today", "there", "would", "be", "a", "problem", "because", "four", "year", "have", "expire", "since", "the", "last", "act", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "original", "because", "of", "action"]]}, {"text": "But at that time they filed their counterclaim, there was no statutory limitations defense available to us.", "start": 1525.389, "stop": 1534.199, "duration": 8.81, "cleanText": [["but", "at", "that", "time", "they", "file", "their", "counterclaim", "there", "be", "no", "statutory", "limitation", "defense", "available", "to", "us"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 1534.199, "stop": 1537.75, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "As of today, I believe they would be barred, if the Court please.", "start": 1537.75, "stop": 1546.047, "duration": 8.3, "cleanText": [["as", "of", "today", "i", "believe", "they", "would", "be", "bar", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}, {"text": "Yesterday in response to questions from the bench and so to say the relevance of the relevant market to the concept of monopoly, counsel for the Government took the position that, well, sometimes we need relevant market and sometimes we have situations that are illegal per se and we don't need a relevant market.", "start": 1546.047, "stop": 1567.737, "duration": 21.69, "cleanText": [["yesterday", "in", "response", "to", "question", "from", "the", "bench", "and", "so", "to", "say", "the", "relevance", "of", "the", "relevant", "market", "to", "the", "concept", "of", "monopoly", "counsel", "for", "the", "government", "take", "the", "position", "that", "well", "sometimes", "we", "need", "relevant", "market", "and", "sometimes", "we", "have", "situation", "that", "be", "illegal", "per", "se", "and", "we", "do", "not", "need", "a", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "I would like if I can and if the Court please to try to underscore the situations where relevant market is necessarily and universally a requirement and I think it takes a very little analysis to get to that point.", "start": 1567.737, "stop": 1586.299, "duration": 18.56, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "if", "i", "can", "and", "if", "the", "court", "please", "to", "try", "to", "underscore", "the", "situation", "where", "relevant", "market", "be", "necessarily", "and", "universally", "a", "requirement", "and", "i", "think", "it", "take", "a", "very", "little", "analysis", "to", "get", "to", "that", "point"]]}, {"text": "When we're talking about per se violations ordinarily we are in the realm of Section 1.", "start": 1586.299, "stop": 1591.63, "duration": 5.33, "cleanText": [["when", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "per", "se", "violation", "ordinarily", "we", "be", "in", "the", "realm", "of", "section"]]}, {"text": "Section 1 of course as for its ultimate criterion the question of reasonableness, reasonableness of the restraint and the Court has held in a handful of situations price fixing, through boycotts perhaps unlawful tie-ins and horizontal divisions of market that in those situations the restraint is per se prima facie if it were illegal because it has no justification whatsoever.", "start": 1591.63, "stop": 1619.422, "duration": 27.79, "cleanText": [["section", "of", "course", "as", "for", "its", "ultimate", "criterion", "the", "question", "of", "reasonableness", "reasonableness", "of", "the", "restraint", "and", "the", "court", "have", "hold", "in", "a", "handful", "of", "situation", "price", "fixing", "through", "boycott", "perhaps", "unlawful", "tie", "in", "and", "horizontal", "division", "of", "market", "that", "in", "those", "situation", "the", "restraint", "be", "per", "se", "prima", "facie", "if", "it", "we", "be", "illegal", "because", "it", "have", "no", "justification", "whatsoever"]]}, {"text": "It obviously and patently forecloses competition between competitors.", "start": 1619.422, "stop": 1624.283, "duration": 4.86, "cleanText": [["it", "obviously", "and", "patently", "foreclose", "competition", "between", "competitor"]]}, {"text": "It's only question under Section 1.", "start": 1624.283, "stop": 1626.919, "duration": 2.64, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "only", "question", "under", "section"]]}, {"text": "When we get to Section 2 however, we are not talking about foreclosing the competition of an individual competitor or suppressing the competition of an individual.", "start": 1626.919, "stop": 1636.207, "duration": 9.29, "cleanText": [["when", "we", "get", "to", "section", "however", "we", "be", "not", "talk", "about", "foreclose", "the", "competition", "of", "an", "individual", "competitor", "or", "suppress", "the", "competition", "of", "an", "individual"]]}, {"text": "We are talking about either monopolization, attempted monopolization, or a combination or conspiracy to monopolize.", "start": 1636.207, "stop": 1645.434, "duration": 9.23, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "talk", "about", "either", "monopolization", "attempt", "monopolization", "or", "a", "combination", "or", "conspiracy", "to", "monopolize"]]}, {"text": "Now if the Court please, the act nowhere talks about a monopoly as Mr. Justice Holmes observed many years ago in the Northern Securities case having a monopoly is not the same thing by any means as the offensive monopolization.", "start": 1645.434, "stop": 1661.621, "duration": 16.19, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "the", "court", "please", "the", "act", "nowhere", "talk", "about", "a", "monopoly", "as", "mr", "justice", "holmes", "observe", "many", "year", "ago", "in", "the", "northern", "security", "case", "have", "a", "monopoly", "be", "not", "the", "same", "thing", "by", "any", "mean", "as", "the", "offensive", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "The monopolization that the Court is talking about which for many, many seasons so to speak and in many, many cases, it is carefully defined relevant market.", "start": 1661.621, "stop": 1674.132, "duration": 12.51, "cleanText": [["the", "monopolization", "that", "the", "court", "be", "talk", "about", "which", "for", "many", "many", "season", "so", "to", "speak", "and", "in", "many", "many", "case", "it", "be", "carefully", "define", "relevant", "market"]]}, {"text": "The monopolization under Section 2 that it is talking about relates to some control, some capacity to exclude competition in some kind of a relevant market coupled with either an historical effort and intent to obtain that control or other unlawful conduct in that connection.", "start": 1674.132, "stop": 1696.134, "duration": 22, "cleanText": [["the", "monopolization", "under", "section", "that", "it", "be", "talk", "about", "relates", "to", "some", "control", "some", "capacity", "to", "exclude", "competition", "in", "some", "kind", "of", "a", "relevant", "market", "couple", "with", "either", "an", "historical", "effort", "and", "intent", "to", "obtain", "that", "control", "or", "other", "unlawful", "conduct", "in", "that", "connection"]]}, {"text": "To eliminate from the concept of Section 2 monopolization, the feature of what is monopolized is, if the Court please, I think completely untenable.", "start": 1696.134, "stop": 1710.663, "duration": 14.53, "cleanText": [["to", "eliminate", "from", "the", "concept", "of", "section", "monopolization", "the", "feature", "of", "what", "be", "monopolize", "be", "if", "the", "court", "please", "i", "think", "completely", "untenable"]]}, {"text": "Likewise, when we get into the area of Section 7 of the Clayton Act, again we are talking about the relevant market because we are talking about the possible adverse effect on competition or tendency to create a monopoly.", "start": 1710.663, "stop": 1725.392, "duration": 14.73, "cleanText": [["likewise", "when", "we", "get", "into", "the", "area", "of", "section", "of", "the", "clayton", "act", "again", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "the", "relevant", "market", "because", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "the", "possible", "adverse", "effect", "on", "competition", "or", "tendency", "to", "create", "a", "monopoly"]]}, {"text": "So when we look at a merger case as the Court did in Brown Shoe and seven rate merger cases since then, or when we look at a monopolization case under Section 1, we are looking to the market effects.", "start": 1725.392, "stop": 1737.286, "duration": 11.89, "cleanText": [["so", "when", "we", "look", "at", "a", "merger", "case", "as", "the", "court", "do", "in", "brown", "shoe", "and", "seven", "rate", "merger", "case", "since", "then", "or", "when", "we", "look", "at", "a", "monopolization", "case", "under", "section", "we", "be", "look", "to", "the", "market", "effect"]]}, {"text": "We are looking to the broad scope of the probability that competition will or will not be affected in some specified and relevant area.", "start": 1737.286, "stop": 1747.282, "duration": 10, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "look", "to", "the", "broad", "scope", "of", "the", "probability", "that", "competition", "will", "or", "will", "not", "be", "affect", "in", "some", "specify", "and", "relevant", "area"]]}, {"text": "That however is not the case under Section 1 where we're just looking for suppression of competition as to an individual competitor.", "start": 1747.282, "stop": 1755.828, "duration": 8.55, "cleanText": [["that", "however", "be", "not", "the", "case", "under", "section", "where", "we", "be", "just", "look", "for", "suppression", "of", "competition", "as", "to", "an", "individual", "competitor"]]}, {"text": "And generally speaking, it is not the case as to Section 3 of the Clayton Act where we were likewise looking to the position of an individual upon whom products have been forced by reason of the control of the seller over some kind of a tie-in product.", "start": 1755.828, "stop": 1774.435, "duration": 18.61, "cleanText": [["and", "generally", "speak", "it", "be", "not", "the", "case", "as", "to", "section", "of", "the", "clayton", "act", "where", "we", "we", "be", "likewise", "look", "to", "the", "position", "of", "an", "individual", "upon", "whom", "product", "have", "be", "force", "by", "reason", "of", "the", "control", "of", "the", "seller", "over", "some", "kind", "of", "a", "tie", "in", "product"]]}, {"text": "So, it is not a question that the Court may sometimes say, Well, we have to look to the relevant market in some other times.", "start": 1774.435, "stop": 1782.192, "duration": 7.76, "cleanText": [["so", "it", "be", "not", "a", "question", "that", "the", "court", "may", "sometimes", "say", "well", "we", "have", "to", "look", "to", "the", "relevant", "market", "in", "some", "other", "time"]]}, {"text": "Say, Well, we won't look to the relevant market, it's purely and simply, if the Court please, a question of understanding the operation of the various provisions of the Sherman Act and of the Clayton Act.", "start": 1782.192, "stop": 1794.427, "duration": 12.23, "cleanText": [["say", "well", "we", "will", "not", "look", "to", "the", "relevant", "market", "it", "be", "purely", "and", "simply", "if", "the", "court", "please", "a", "question", "of", "understand", "the", "operation", "of", "the", "various", "provision", "of", "the", "sherman", "act", "and", "of", "the", "clayton", "act"]]}, {"text": "And once again, I underscore and reemphasize that as far as monopolization under Section 2 is concerned, the result of what I say is that without a relevant market, there can't be any monopolization.", "start": 1794.427, "stop": 1809.747, "duration": 15.32, "cleanText": [["and", "once", "again", "i", "underscore", "and", "reemphasize", "that", "as", "far", "as", "monopolization", "under", "section", "be", "concern", "the", "result", "of", "what", "i", "say", "be", "that", "without", "a", "relevant", "market", "there", "can", "not", "be", "any", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "I suggest too, as a matter of policy if the Court please, that we have in our society very few absolutes.", "start": 1809.747, "stop": 1817.103, "duration": 7.36, "cleanText": [["i", "suggest", "too", "as", "a", "matter", "of", "policy", "if", "the", "court", "please", "that", "we", "have", "in", "our", "society", "very", "few", "absolute"]]}, {"text": "We have, as I have indicated, very few categories of per se liability.", "start": 1817.103, "stop": 1822.423, "duration": 5.32, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "as", "i", "have", "indicate", "very", "few", "category", "of", "per", "se", "liability"]]}, {"text": "In the complexity and the richness of our social and economic fabric, there are always distinctions.", "start": 1822.423, "stop": 1828.693, "duration": 6.27, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "complexity", "and", "the", "richness", "of", "our", "social", "and", "economic", "fabric", "there", "be", "always", "distinction"]]}, {"text": "There are always facts and circumstances.", "start": 1828.693, "stop": 1830.672, "duration": 1.98, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "always", "fact", "and", "circumstance"]]}, {"text": "There are always special situations that have to be considered.", "start": 1830.672, "stop": 1836.629, "duration": 5.96, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "always", "special", "situation", "that", "have", "to", "be", "consider"]]}, {"text": "Every time we establish some new category of per se liability, whether it's under the Sherman Act or under any other provision of law, we are losing something of value because in the final analysis, there is no substitute for concrete investigation of the concrete facts and circumstances of a particular situation.", "start": 1836.629, "stop": 1859.479, "duration": 22.85, "cleanText": [["every", "time", "we", "establish", "some", "new", "category", "of", "per", "se", "liability", "whether", "it", "be", "under", "the", "sherman", "act", "or", "under", "any", "other", "provision", "of", "law", "we", "be", "lose", "something", "of", "value", "because", "in", "the", "final", "analysis", "there", "be", "no", "substitute", "for", "concrete", "investigation", "of", "the", "concrete", "fact", "and", "circumstance", "of", "a", "particular", "situation"]]}, {"text": "Now, if the Court please, I would like to consider, if I may, the apparent inappropriateness of this particular case for the Court to undertake to make any kind of pronouncements that might be construed by the lower court's and the bar to be (Inaudible) or far reaching or constitute the development of a new category of liability under the antitrust laws.", "start": 1859.479, "stop": 1887.59, "duration": 28.11, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "the", "court", "please", "i", "would", "like", "to", "consider", "if", "i", "may", "the", "apparent", "inappropriateness", "of", "this", "particular", "case", "for", "the", "court", "to", "undertake", "to", "make", "any", "kind", "of", "pronouncement", "that", "might", "be", "construe", "by", "the", "low", "court", "s", "and", "the", "bar", "to", "be", "inaudible", "or", "far", "reach", "or", "constitute", "the", "development", "of", "a", "new", "category", "of", "liability", "under", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "Counsel for Walker yesterday elaborated at length and the alleged fraud in this case attempting to tar FMC Corporation with the black brush of bad conduct.", "start": 1887.59, "stop": 1901.011, "duration": 13.42, "cleanText": [["counsel", "for", "walker", "yesterday", "elaborate", "at", "length", "and", "the", "allege", "fraud", "in", "this", "case", "attempt", "to", "tar", "fmc", "corporation", "with", "the", "black", "brush", "of", "bad", "conduct"]]}, {"text": "I would like to suggest to the Court that of course the conclusions of fraud for purposes of testing the sufficiency of the pleading are accepted, that is a necessary point in order to work off of a motion to dismiss.", "start": 1901.011, "stop": 1915.581, "duration": 14.57, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "like", "to", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "that", "of", "course", "the", "conclusion", "of", "fraud", "for", "purpose", "of", "test", "the", "sufficiency", "of", "the", "pleading", "be", "accept", "that", "be", "a", "necessary", "point", "in", "order", "to", "work", "off", "of", "a", "motion", "to", "dismiss"]]}, {"text": "However, I invite the Court's rotation to the way Walker pleaded the question of fraud in its amended counterclaims, the predecessor to the stricken pleading.", "start": 1915.581, "stop": 1926.276, "duration": 10.7, "cleanText": [["however", "i", "invite", "the", "court", "s", "rotation", "to", "the", "way", "walker", "plead", "the", "question", "of", "fraud", "in", "its", "amended", "counterclaim", "the", "predecessor", "to", "the", "stricken", "pleading"]]}, {"text": "There Walker said the plaintiff committed at least a technical fraud on the Patent Office by representing that the patent that not be on sale or in public use for more than a year.", "start": 1926.276, "stop": 1941.237, "duration": 14.96, "cleanText": [["there", "walker", "say", "the", "plaintiff", "commit", "at", "least", "a", "technical", "fraud", "on", "the", "patent", "office", "by", "represent", "that", "the", "patent", "that", "not", "be", "on", "sale", "or", "in", "public", "use", "for", "more", "than", "a", "year"]]}, {"text": "At that time, when Walker was so pleading, it did not regard the fraud as some kind of vicious and horrendous and indefensible situation.", "start": 1941.237, "stop": 1950.842, "duration": 9.61, "cleanText": [["at", "that", "time", "when", "walker", "be", "so", "pleading", "it", "do", "not", "regard", "the", "fraud", "as", "some", "kind", "of", "vicious", "and", "horrendous", "and", "indefensible", "situation"]]}, {"text": "In addition, I would like to suggest to the Court and this is apparent from the record, the plaint -- the original complaint shows that the patent is the Lannert Patent.", "start": 1950.842, "stop": 1966.418, "duration": 15.58, "cleanText": [["in", "addition", "i", "would", "like", "to", "suggest", "to", "the", "court", "and", "this", "be", "apparent", "from", "the", "record", "the", "plaint", "the", "original", "complaint", "show", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "the", "lannert", "patent"]]}, {"text": "And FMC Corporation is a subsequent assignee of that patent.", "start": 1966.418, "stop": 1970.554, "duration": 4.14, "cleanText": [["and", "fmc", "corporation", "be", "a", "subsequent", "assignee", "of", "that", "patent"]]}, {"text": "Lannert was an employee of Chicago Pump Company.", "start": 1970.554, "stop": 1973.772, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["lannert", "be", "an", "employee", "of", "chicago", "pump", "company"]]}, {"text": "The patent was applied for in 1942.", "start": 1973.772, "stop": 1978.216, "duration": 4.44, "cleanText": [["the", "patent", "be", "apply", "for", "in"]]}, {"text": "In 1954, FMC Corporation acquired all the assets of Chicago Pump Company.", "start": 1978.216, "stop": 1986.865, "duration": 8.65, "cleanText": [["in", "fmc", "corporation", "acquire", "all", "the", "asset", "of", "chicago", "pump", "company"]]}, {"text": "Now, I think most likely from the standpoint of the rights of creditors and others, FMC company is of course liable for the acts of its predecessor although we have that situation from the standpoint of attributing to FMC Corporation most of the elements necessary to create the offense of monopolization namely, the monopoly power coupled with the monopolistic intent which is supposed to be evidenced by the fraudulent procurement of the patent.", "start": 1986.865, "stop": 2020.112, "duration": 33.25, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "think", "most", "likely", "from", "the", "standpoint", "of", "the", "right", "of", "creditor", "and", "others", "fmc", "company", "be", "of", "course", "liable", "for", "the", "act", "of", "its", "predecessor", "although", "we", "have", "that", "situation", "from", "the", "standpoint", "of", "attribute", "to", "fmc", "corporation", "most", "of", "the", "element", "necessary", "to", "create", "the", "offense", "of", "monopolization", "namely", "the", "monopoly", "power", "couple", "with", "the", "monopolistic", "intent", "which", "be", "suppose", "to", "be", "evidence", "by", "the", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "the", "patent"]]}, {"text": "From that standpoint, the case presents a peculiar wrinkle because it was a remote individual predecessor of FMC who applied for the patent and it was that individual if there was a fraud committed on the Patent Office who was guilty of that fraud.", "start": 2020.112, "stop": 2035.966, "duration": 15.85, "cleanText": [["from", "that", "standpoint", "the", "case", "present", "a", "peculiar", "wrinkle", "because", "it", "be", "a", "remote", "individual", "predecessor", "of", "fmc", "who", "apply", "for", "the", "patent", "and", "it", "be", "that", "individual", "if", "there", "be", "a", "fraud", "commit", "on", "the", "patent", "office", "who", "be", "guilty", "of", "that", "fraud"]]}, {"text": "Now, to take in a case where the facts have not been tried, where the facts are merely speculative and based on the allegations of the pleader and couple that remote intention with the subsequent activity of FMC Corporation in enforcing the patent and say that those two fit together to subject FMC Corporation to the offensive monopolization, that presents a problem which I think properly, if that were the question in the case, would have to be tried, the defenses would have to be tried out and the facts would have to be ascertained.", "start": 2035.966, "stop": 2074.495, "duration": 38.53, "cleanText": [["now", "to", "take", "in", "a", "case", "where", "the", "fact", "have", "not", "be", "try", "where", "the", "fact", "be", "merely", "speculative", "and", "base", "on", "the", "allegation", "of", "the", "pleader", "and", "couple", "that", "remote", "intention", "with", "the", "subsequent", "activity", "of", "fmc", "corporation", "in", "enforce", "the", "patent", "and", "say", "that", "those", "two", "fit", "together", "to", "subject", "fmc", "corporation", "to", "the", "offensive", "monopolization", "that", "present", "a", "problem", "which", "i", "think", "properly", "if", "that", "we", "be", "the", "question", "in", "the", "case", "would", "have", "to", "be", "try", "the", "defense", "would", "have", "to", "be", "try", "out", "and", "the", "fact", "would", "have", "to", "be", "ascertain"]]}, {"text": "Those difficulties plus the very difficulty of the nature of their pleading and the ultimate confusion that they expressed in their briefs and in their proper relief suggesting really that what their complaining about is analogous to a tying situation which of course it really is not because this is not a leverage situation.", "start": 2074.495, "stop": 2099.167, "duration": 24.67, "cleanText": [["those", "difficulty", "plus", "the", "very", "difficulty", "of", "the", "nature", "of", "their", "pleading", "and", "the", "ultimate", "confusion", "that", "they", "express", "in", "their", "brief", "and", "in", "their", "proper", "relief", "suggest", "really", "that", "what", "their", "complaining", "about", "be", "analogous", "to", "a", "tying", "situation", "which", "of", "course", "it", "really", "be", "not", "because", "this", "be", "not", "a", "leverage", "situation"]]}, {"text": "FMC has not used the patent to force anyone, let alone Walker, to acquire something in addition to the patent and product.", "start": 2099.167, "stop": 2110.136, "duration": 10.97, "cleanText": [["fmc", "have", "not", "use", "the", "patent", "to", "force", "anyone", "let", "alone", "walker", "to", "acquire", "something", "in", "addition", "to", "the", "patent", "and", "product"]]}, {"text": "There is no tie-in.", "start": 2110.136, "stop": 2111.065, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "There is no forcing of any kind.", "start": 2111.065, "stop": 2114.376, "duration": 3.31, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "forcing", "of", "any", "kind"]]}, {"text": "So that the analogy really, if the Court please, simply has no bearing on the situation, couple that with the factor that when they say in their suggestion of damages that they were deprived of the opportunity to compete with Walker -- excuse me, with FMC.", "start": 2114.376, "stop": 2135.612, "duration": 21.24, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "the", "analogy", "really", "if", "the", "court", "please", "simply", "have", "no", "bearing", "on", "the", "situation", "couple", "that", "with", "the", "factor", "that", "when", "they", "say", "in", "their", "suggestion", "of", "damage", "that", "they", "we", "be", "deprive", "of", "the", "opportunity", "to", "compete", "with", "walker", "excuse", "me", "with", "fmc"]]}, {"text": "What they're saying by that really is that if it were a Sherman Act Section 1 case, they had been injured, their competition were suppressed.", "start": 2135.612, "stop": 2145.883, "duration": 10.27, "cleanText": [["what", "they", "be", "say", "by", "that", "really", "be", "that", "if", "it", "we", "be", "a", "sherman", "act", "section", "case", "they", "have", "be", "injure", "their", "competition", "we", "be", "suppress"]]}, {"text": "And accordingly because it looks like a Sherman Section 1 from that standpoint, they ought to have some kind of cause of action under the antitrust laws which of course they cannot allege because there's no element of combination or conspiracy or contract which is requisite to Section 1.", "start": 2145.883, "stop": 2164.361, "duration": 18.48, "cleanText": [["and", "accordingly", "because", "it", "look", "like", "a", "sherman", "section", "from", "that", "standpoint", "they", "ought", "to", "have", "some", "kind", "of", "because", "of", "action", "under", "the", "antitrust", "law", "which", "of", "course", "they", "can", "not", "allege", "because", "there", "be", "no", "element", "of", "combination", "or", "conspiracy", "or", "contract", "which", "be", "requisite", "to", "section"]]}, {"text": "And the finding in their previous pleadings and in their briefs, an effort is set forth some kind of common law fraud claim, some kind of claim of unfair competition.", "start": 2164.361, "stop": 2176.263, "duration": 11.9, "cleanText": [["and", "the", "finding", "in", "their", "previous", "pleading", "and", "in", "their", "brief", "an", "effort", "be", "set", "forth", "some", "kind", "of", "common", "law", "fraud", "claim", "some", "kind", "of", "claim", "of", "unfair", "competition"]]}, {"text": "It was seen really that if an action to a private party were available under Section 5 of the Federal Trade Commission Act, that that is really what their complaining about.", "start": 2176.263, "stop": 2187.106, "duration": 10.84, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "see", "really", "that", "if", "an", "action", "to", "a", "private", "party", "we", "be", "available", "under", "section", "of", "the", "federal", "trade", "commission", "act", "that", "that", "be", "really", "what", "their", "complaining", "about"]]}, {"text": "Some kind of unfair method of competition that Walker -- excuse me, that FMC had this patent an item that they were unable to successfully compete with it.", "start": 2187.106, "stop": 2199.372, "duration": 12.27, "cleanText": [["some", "kind", "of", "unfair", "method", "of", "competition", "that", "walker", "excuse", "me", "that", "fmc", "have", "this", "patent", "an", "item", "that", "they", "we", "be", "unable", "to", "successfully", "compete", "with", "it"]]}, {"text": "And that FMC had fraudulently procured it that might be some method of unfair competition interdicted by Section 5 of the Federal Trade Commission Act.", "start": 2199.372, "stop": 2210.819, "duration": 11.45, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "fmc", "have", "fraudulently", "procure", "it", "that", "might", "be", "some", "method", "of", "unfair", "competition", "interdict", "by", "section", "of", "the", "federal", "trade", "commission", "act"]]}, {"text": "We have all of these difficulties in this case.", "start": 2210.819, "stop": 2214.503, "duration": 3.68, "cleanText": [["we", "have", "all", "of", "these", "difficulty", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "It does not seem to lend itself to a definitive pronouncement by the Court in this state of the facts.", "start": 2214.503, "stop": 2223.493, "duration": 8.99, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "seem", "to", "lend", "itself", "to", "a", "definitive", "pronouncement", "by", "the", "court", "in", "this", "state", "of", "the", "fact"]]}, {"text": "Nonetheless, I would like to make this perfectly clear once again if I may.", "start": 2223.493, "stop": 2229.034, "duration": 5.54, "cleanText": [["nonetheless", "i", "would", "like", "to", "make", "this", "perfectly", "clear", "once", "again", "if", "i", "may"]]}, {"text": "I am not suggesting that this case should go back to the District Court with an opportunity for them to amend this thing once more and to figure out if there is in some way now after having presented this per se question to this Court, isn't there some way now that they can go ahead and state their claims for relief under Section 2 of the Sherman Act.", "start": 2229.034, "stop": 2249.484, "duration": 20.45, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "not", "suggest", "that", "this", "case", "should", "go", "back", "to", "the", "district", "court", "with", "an", "opportunity", "for", "them", "to", "amend", "this", "thing", "once", "more", "and", "to", "figure", "out", "if", "there", "be", "in", "some", "way", "now", "after", "have", "present", "this", "per", "se", "question", "to", "this", "court", "be", "not", "there", "some", "way", "now", "that", "they", "can", "go", "ahead", "and", "state", "their", "claim", "for", "relief", "under", "section", "of", "the", "sherman", "act"]]}, {"text": "I am not suggesting that, if the Court please.", "start": 2249.484, "stop": 2252.163, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "not", "suggest", "that", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}, {"text": "I'm suggesting only in the first instance that on the question presented, they have not stated a claim for relief.", "start": 2252.163, "stop": 2258.529, "duration": 6.37, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "suggest", "only", "in", "the", "first", "instance", "that", "on", "the", "question", "present", "they", "have", "not", "state", "a", "claim", "for", "relief"]]}, {"text": "Their legal theory leaves them up against the blind wall because they cannot simply equate the fraudulent procurement of the patent or a patent monopoly with Sherman Act monopolization.", "start": 2258.529, "stop": 2270.979, "duration": 12.45, "cleanText": [["their", "legal", "theory", "leave", "them", "up", "against", "the", "blind", "wall", "because", "they", "can", "not", "simply", "equate", "the", "fraudulent", "procurement", "of", "the", "patent", "or", "a", "patent", "monopoly", "with", "sherman", "act", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "And secondly, that they have had their day in court.", "start": 2270.979, "stop": 2274.43, "duration": 3.45, "cleanText": [["and", "secondly", "that", "they", "have", "have", "their", "day", "in", "court"]]}, {"text": "If every time a party were to lose on the basis of illegal theory, that it's made three efforts to carry through the District Court and the Court of Appeals, and then up to the Supreme Court, if every time they could do that and start out all over again, we would never finish with the processes of litigation.", "start": 2274.43, "stop": 2294.425, "duration": 20, "cleanText": [["if", "every", "time", "a", "party", "we", "be", "to", "lose", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "illegal", "theory", "that", "it", "be", "make", "three", "effort", "to", "carry", "through", "the", "district", "court", "and", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "and", "then", "up", "to", "the", "supreme", "court", "if", "every", "time", "they", "could", "do", "that", "and", "start", "out", "all", "over", "again", "we", "would", "never", "finish", "with", "the", "process", "of", "litigation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was (Inaudible)", "start": 2294.425, "stop": 2298.378, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "Complaint was filed in 1960, if the Court please.", "start": 2298.378, "stop": 2303.725, "duration": 5.35, "cleanText": [["complaint", "be", "file", "in", "if", "the", "court", "please"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2303.725, "stop": 2307.398, "duration": 3.67, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "There was an original counterclaim, which was twice amended, so they made three efforts to plead this counterclaim.", "start": 2307.398, "stop": 2316.661, "duration": 9.26, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "an", "original", "counterclaim", "which", "be", "twice", "amend", "so", "they", "make", "three", "effort", "to", "plead", "this", "counterclaim"]]}, {"text": "I suggest that the question of the discretion of the District Court not to grant a fourth opportunity to amend is really not something with respect to which this Court on certiorari would be particularly concerned with.", "start": 2316.661, "stop": 2330.444, "duration": 13.78, "cleanText": [["i", "suggest", "that", "the", "question", "of", "the", "discretion", "of", "the", "district", "court", "not", "to", "grant", "a", "fourth", "opportunity", "to", "amend", "be", "really", "not", "something", "with", "respect", "to", "which", "this", "court", "on", "certiorari", "would", "be", "particularly", "concern", "with"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2330.444, "stop": 2332.076, "duration": 1.63, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no, there was not Your Honor.", "start": 2332.076, "stop": 2333.933, "duration": 1.86, "cleanText": [["no", "no", "there", "be", "not", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "It was dismissed with prejudice so that they would have an opportunity to appeal or I think if they wanted to they could have wanted and asked for leave to amend whether it was dismissed with prejudice or not.", "start": 2333.933, "stop": 2344.498, "duration": 10.57, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "dismiss", "with", "prejudice", "so", "that", "they", "would", "have", "an", "opportunity", "to", "appeal", "or", "i", "think", "if", "they", "want", "to", "they", "could", "have", "want", "and", "ask", "for", "leave", "to", "amend", "whether", "it", "be", "dismiss", "with", "prejudice", "or", "not"]]}, {"text": "I think that's just surplus verbiage when a counterclaim is dismissed.", "start": 2344.498, "stop": 2349.612, "duration": 5.11, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "just", "surplus", "verbiage", "when", "a", "counterclaim", "be", "dismiss"]]}, {"text": "It's always open to a pleader to ask the Court for a leave to amend its pleading.", "start": 2349.612, "stop": 2354.158, "duration": 4.55, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "always", "open", "to", "a", "pleader", "to", "ask", "the", "court", "for", "a", "leave", "to", "amend", "its", "pleading"]]}, {"text": "The Court obviously would have denied it because the Court had had several opportunities to review Walker's theory.", "start": 2354.158, "stop": 2364.368, "duration": 10.21, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "obviously", "would", "have", "deny", "it", "because", "the", "court", "have", "have", "several", "opportunity", "to", "review", "walker", "s", "theory"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there a stay or a legal (Inaudible)", "start": 2364.368, "stop": 2369.589, "duration": 5.22, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "a", "stay", "or", "a", "legal", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Sheldon O. Collen", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, there was not Your Honor because as Mr. Justice White has observed the nature of the Court of Appeal's opinion was such that it foreclosed the possibility of relief under early circumstances.", "start": 2369.589, "stop": 2398.952, "duration": 29.36, "cleanText": [["no", "there", "be", "not", "your", "honor", "because", "as", "mr", "justice", "white", "have", "observe", "the", "nature", "of", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "s", "opinion", "be", "such", "that", "it", "foreclose", "the", "possibility", "of", "relief", "under", "early", "circumstance"]]}, {"text": "I think if the Court please whatever remains of the position that we want to take that I have not touched on is adequately touched upon in our briefs and that bring the case I shall conclude.", "start": 2398.952, "stop": 2418.39, "duration": 19.44, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "if", "the", "court", "please", "whatever", "remain", "of", "the", "position", "that", "we", "want", "to", "take", "that", "i", "have", "not", "touch", "on", "be", "adequately", "touch", "upon", "in", "our", "brief", "and", "that", "bring", "the", "case", "i", "shall", "conclude"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Merriam.", "start": 2418.39, "stop": 2419.58, "duration": 1.19, "cleanText": [["mr", "merriam"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Chief Justice, Members of the Court.", "start": 2419.58, "stop": 2423.089, "duration": 3.51, "cleanText": [["mr", "chief", "justice", "member", "of", "the", "court"]]}, {"text": "I'll start out by answering Mr. Justice White's question as to whether we do say that if the Court decides this is not a per se violation we would like to go back and replay it and we would.", "start": 2423.089, "stop": 2435.134, "duration": 12.05, "cleanText": [["I", "will", "start", "out", "by", "answer", "mr", "justice", "white", "s", "question", "as", "to", "whether", "we", "do", "say", "that", "if", "the", "court", "decide", "this", "be", "not", "a", "per", "se", "violation", "we", "would", "like", "to", "go", "back", "and", "replay", "it", "and", "we", "would"]]}, {"text": "I thought I said it before but I'll say it now.", "start": 2435.134, "stop": 2438.954, "duration": 3.82, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "i", "say", "it", "before", "but", "I", "will", "say", "it", "now"]]}, {"text": "Two, I'd like --", "start": 2438.954, "stop": 2439.282, "duration": 0.33, "cleanText": [["two", "I", "would", "like"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "You never say it before?", "start": 2439.282, "stop": 2441.806, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["you", "never", "say", "it", "before"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Alright, you mean in the lower court?", "start": 2441.806, "stop": 2445.018, "duration": 3.21, "cleanText": [["alright", "you", "mean", "in", "the", "low", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Earl Warren", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 2445.018, "stop": 2445.323, "duration": 0.3, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I wasn't in the lower court and I don't know that anybody ever said it through the (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 2445.323, "stop": 2449.733, "duration": 4.41, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "be", "not", "in", "the", "low", "court", "and", "i", "do", "not", "know", "that", "anybody", "ever", "say", "it", "through", "the", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was it ever raised by anybody in the lower court as to the --", "start": 2449.733, "stop": 2451.865, "duration": 2.13, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "ever", "raise", "by", "anybody", "in", "the", "low", "court", "as", "to", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't --", "start": 2451.865, "stop": 2452.551, "duration": 0.69, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- as to whether this pleading was sufficient in terms of the relevant market business.", "start": 2452.551, "stop": 2458.313, "duration": 5.76, "cleanText": [["as", "to", "whether", "this", "pleading", "be", "sufficient", "in", "term", "of", "the", "relevant", "market", "business"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's my understanding that it was not.", "start": 2458.313, "stop": 2459.983, "duration": 1.67, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "my", "understanding", "that", "it", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "The record doesn't show that it was, but as Mr. Collen said, I wasn't there so I can say no more than that.", "start": 2459.983, "stop": 2467.155, "duration": 7.17, "cleanText": [["the", "record", "do", "not", "show", "that", "it", "be", "but", "as", "mr", "collen", "say", "i", "be", "not", "there", "so", "i", "can", "say", "no", "more", "than", "that"]]}, {"text": "I came into this case only after when taken by this Court.", "start": 2467.155, "stop": 2470.787, "duration": 3.63, "cleanText": [["i", "come", "into", "this", "case", "only", "after", "when", "take", "by", "this", "court"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you (Inaudible)", "start": 2470.787, "stop": 2473.446, "duration": 2.66, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "I wouldn't like to.", "start": 2473.446, "stop": 2474.344, "duration": 0.9, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "not", "like", "to"]]}, {"text": "I'd like --", "start": 2474.344, "stop": 2474.748, "duration": 0.4, "cleanText": [["I", "would", "like"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2474.748, "stop": 2478.094, "duration": 3.35, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'd like to amend the pleading.", "start": 2478.094, "stop": 2479.345, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["I", "would", "like", "to", "amend", "the", "pleading"]]}, {"text": "It's not the kind of a --", "start": 2479.345, "stop": 2480.196, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "the", "kind", "of", "a"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2480.196, "stop": 2480.625, "duration": 0.43, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's not the kind of pleading I would have drawn.", "start": 2480.625, "stop": 2482.662, "duration": 2.04, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "the", "kind", "of", "pleading", "i", "would", "have", "draw"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2482.662, "stop": 2486.297, "duration": 3.64, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Second, I don't know of any abandonment of the tie-in clause and I understand that there have been tie-ins.", "start": 2486.297, "stop": 2491.968, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["second", "i", "do", "not", "know", "of", "any", "abandonment", "of", "the", "tie", "in", "clause", "and", "i", "understand", "that", "there", "have", "be", "tie", "in"]]}, {"text": "Now, Mr. Collen says that was done.", "start": 2491.968, "stop": 2493.907, "duration": 1.94, "cleanText": [["now", "mr", "collen", "say", "that", "be", "do"]]}, {"text": "I've talked to our people and they say it was not.", "start": 2493.907, "stop": 2496.283, "duration": 2.38, "cleanText": [["I", "have", "talk", "to", "our", "people", "and", "they", "say", "it", "be", "not"]]}, {"text": "It's not on the record that there was any withdrawal.", "start": 2496.283, "stop": 2499.827, "duration": 3.54, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "on", "the", "record", "that", "there", "be", "any", "withdrawal"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Collen said there are no cases in the lower courts passing on the point which is here.", "start": 2499.827, "stop": 2506.946, "duration": 7.12, "cleanText": [["mr", "collen", "say", "there", "be", "no", "case", "in", "the", "low", "court", "pass", "on", "the", "point", "which", "be", "here"]]}, {"text": "There are in fact two of them cited in our brief which he never answered.", "start": 2506.946, "stop": 2510.768, "duration": 3.82, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "in", "fact", "two", "of", "them", "cite", "in", "our", "brief", "which", "he", "never", "answer"]]}, {"text": "They are the Clinton case and the (Inaudible) case cited on pages 9 and 13 of our brief.", "start": 2510.768, "stop": 2517.13, "duration": 6.36, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "the", "clinton", "case", "and", "the", "inaudible", "case", "cite", "on", "page", "and", "of", "our", "brief"]]}, {"text": "Off of which is squarely implied in which they -- monopolization count was upheld against the motion to strike.", "start": 2517.13, "stop": 2525.435, "duration": 8.3, "cleanText": [["off", "of", "which", "be", "squarely", "imply", "in", "which", "they", "monopolization", "count", "be", "uphold", "against", "the", "motion", "to", "strike"]]}, {"text": "In the Briggs case, it was specifically because there had been an alleged fraud on the Patent Office in connection with the prior use, which is not revealed to it.", "start": 2525.435, "stop": 2536.502, "duration": 11.07, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "briggs", "case", "it", "be", "specifically", "because", "there", "have", "be", "an", "allege", "fraud", "on", "the", "patent", "office", "in", "connection", "with", "the", "prior", "use", "which", "be", "not", "reveal", "to", "it"]]}, {"text": "Those two cases have never been referred to at all by my opponent and they are there.", "start": 2536.502, "stop": 2542.375, "duration": 5.87, "cleanText": [["those", "two", "case", "have", "never", "be", "refer", "to", "at", "all", "by", "my", "opponent", "and", "they", "be", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was the name of the case?", "start": 2542.375, "stop": 2544.138, "duration": 1.76, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "the", "name", "of", "the", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "The Clinton against Briggs & Stratton on page 9 and the (Inaudible) case which I believe is on the same page.", "start": 2544.138, "stop": 2552.067, "duration": 7.93, "cleanText": [["the", "clinton", "against", "briggs", "stratton", "on", "page", "and", "the", "inaudible", "case", "which", "i", "believe", "be", "on", "the", "same", "page"]]}, {"text": "They're also cited on page 13 of our brief.", "start": 2552.067, "stop": 2559.154, "duration": 7.09, "cleanText": [["they", "be", "also", "cite", "on", "page", "of", "our", "brief"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Justice Harlan asked about the effect of the statute's limitations.", "start": 2559.154, "stop": 2563.62, "duration": 4.47, "cleanText": [["mr", "justice", "harlan", "ask", "about", "the", "effect", "of", "the", "statute", "s", "limitation"]]}, {"text": "In that connection, I would like again to refer to the Hartford-Empire against Shawkee which is recited in our brief on the same page 9 and the subsequent case in the District -- in the Court of Appeals where the patent had been set aside by fraud 11 years after the event.", "start": 2563.62, "stop": 2587.134, "duration": 23.51, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "connection", "i", "would", "like", "again", "to", "refer", "to", "the", "hartford", "empire", "against", "shawkee", "which", "be", "recite", "in", "our", "brief", "on", "the", "same", "page", "and", "the", "subsequent", "case", "in", "the", "district", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "where", "the", "patent", "have", "be", "set", "aside", "by", "fraud", "year", "after", "the", "event"]]}, {"text": "And they held that while the statute of limitations was gone, I mean, had passed and expired, a recovery would be allowed simply on the ground of improper use of the patent.", "start": 2587.134, "stop": 2597.752, "duration": 10.62, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "hold", "that", "while", "the", "statute", "of", "limitation", "be", "go", "i", "mean", "have", "pass", "and", "expire", "a", "recovery", "would", "be", "allow", "simply", "on", "the", "ground", "of", "improper", "use", "of", "the", "patent"]]}, {"text": "And among those was attorneys fees, they refused to allow a business recovery not on the ground of statute of limitations but on the ground that it had not been proved properly.", "start": 2597.752, "stop": 2608.205, "duration": 10.45, "cleanText": [["and", "among", "those", "be", "attorney", "fee", "they", "refuse", "to", "allow", "a", "business", "recovery", "not", "on", "the", "ground", "of", "statute", "of", "limitation", "but", "on", "the", "ground", "that", "it", "have", "not", "be", "prove", "properly"]]}, {"text": "The matter of relevant market, it's really -- has come up here for the first time.", "start": 2608.205, "stop": 2614.48, "duration": 6.28, "cleanText": [["the", "matter", "of", "relevant", "market", "it", "be", "really", "have", "come", "up", "here", "for", "the", "first", "time"]]}, {"text": "I think as Mr. Justice Black says doesn't belong here for discussion at all.", "start": 2614.48, "stop": 2618.69, "duration": 4.21, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "as", "mr", "justice", "black", "say", "do", "not", "belong", "here", "for", "discussion", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "As to Mr. Justice Black's question, I wouldn't say however that -- I think that we have a tendency, I'm primarily a patent lawyer and not an antitrust lawyer, we have a tendency to make secondary rules of construction of revenues and then forget that they are secondary such as change or form doesn't amount to invention.", "start": 2618.69, "stop": 2641.598, "duration": 22.91, "cleanText": [["as", "to", "mr", "justice", "black", "s", "question", "i", "would", "not", "say", "however", "that", "i", "think", "that", "we", "have", "a", "tendency", "I", "be", "primarily", "a", "patent", "lawyer", "and", "not", "an", "antitrust", "lawyer", "we", "have", "a", "tendency", "to", "make", "secondary", "rule", "of", "construction", "of", "revenue", "and", "then", "forget", "that", "they", "be", "secondary", "such", "as", "change", "or", "form", "do", "not", "amount", "to", "invention"]]}, {"text": "That's only in its evidence, it isn't, the ultimate fact is whether or not there was invention, there was unobvious.", "start": 2641.598, "stop": 2647.865, "duration": 6.27, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "only", "in", "its", "evidence", "it", "be", "not", "the", "ultimate", "fact", "be", "whether", "or", "not", "there", "be", "invention", "there", "be", "unobvious"]]}, {"text": "So here, the ultimate fact is whether or not the plaintiff had -- was able to control prices in the industry.", "start": 2647.865, "stop": 2656.596, "duration": 8.73, "cleanText": [["so", "here", "the", "ultimate", "fact", "be", "whether", "or", "not", "the", "plaintiff", "have", "be", "able", "to", "control", "price", "in", "the", "industry"]]}, {"text": "If he was able to control prices, relevant market is not of importance at all.", "start": 2656.596, "stop": 2661.006, "duration": 4.41, "cleanText": [["if", "he", "be", "able", "to", "control", "price", "relevant", "market", "be", "not", "of", "importance", "at", "all"]]}, {"text": "It's only important as it was in the Cellophane case to show because controlling prices is not normally an easy thing to do.", "start": 2661.006, "stop": 2670.586, "duration": 9.58, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "only", "important", "as", "it", "be", "in", "the", "cellophane", "case", "to", "show", "because", "control", "price", "be", "not", "normally", "an", "easy", "thing", "to", "do"]]}, {"text": "You have to take the eloquent evidence on it and in that case, there were plenty of other wrapping materials that indicated that there was no ability to control prices even though it had a monopoly, (Inaudible) of monopoly.", "start": 2670.586, "stop": 2682.988, "duration": 12.4, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "to", "take", "the", "eloquent", "evidence", "on", "it", "and", "in", "that", "case", "there", "we", "be", "plenty", "of", "other", "wrap", "material", "that", "indicate", "that", "there", "be", "no", "ability", "to", "control", "price", "even", "though", "it", "have", "a", "monopoly", "inaudible", "of", "monopoly"]]}, {"text": "So here, the -- it was left out of our second counterclaim, I would have put it in, in better form.", "start": 2682.988, "stop": 2691.567, "duration": 8.58, "cleanText": [["so", "here", "the", "it", "be", "leave", "out", "of", "our", "second", "counterclaim", "i", "would", "have", "put", "it", "in", "in", "good", "form"]]}, {"text": "But on page 78 of the record the statement was made in paragraph 24 that before the patent expired, the prices were $150 a lineal foot and sometimes higher possibly and that after the patent expired there were $50 a running foot which certainly shows right off there that there was a controlled price.", "start": 2691.567, "stop": 2714.571, "duration": 23, "cleanText": [["but", "on", "page", "of", "the", "record", "the", "statement", "be", "make", "in", "paragraph", "that", "before", "the", "patent", "expire", "the", "price", "we", "be", "a", "lineal", "foot", "and", "sometimes", "high", "possibly", "and", "that", "after", "the", "patent", "expire", "there", "we", "be", "a", "running", "foot", "which", "certainly", "show", "right", "off", "there", "that", "there", "be", "a", "controlled", "price"]]}, {"text": "Furthermore, Mr. Forrest, their man, said on page 50 that they had to control not only of the action lifter, but they had virtually no computation throughout the life of the patent in swing diffusers.", "start": 2714.571, "stop": 2732.324, "duration": 17.75, "cleanText": [["furthermore", "mr", "forrest", "their", "man", "say", "on", "page", "that", "they", "have", "to", "control", "not", "only", "of", "the", "action", "lifter", "but", "they", "have", "virtually", "no", "computation", "throughout", "the", "life", "of", "the", "patent", "in", "swing", "diffuser"]]}, {"text": "Not just a patent of swing diffusers but any swing diffusers.", "start": 2732.324, "stop": 2735.923, "duration": 3.6, "cleanText": [["not", "just", "a", "patent", "of", "swing", "diffuser", "but", "any", "swing", "diffuser"]]}, {"text": "So that there are facts in this record which show not only there was control of prices and control of competition, but that the relevant -- what the relevant market was.", "start": 2735.923, "stop": 2748.851, "duration": 12.93, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "there", "be", "fact", "in", "this", "record", "which", "show", "not", "only", "there", "be", "control", "of", "price", "and", "control", "of", "competition", "but", "that", "the", "relevant", "what", "the", "relevant", "market", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "What was it, swing diffusion?", "start": 2748.851, "stop": 2751.223, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "it", "swing", "diffusion"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would say diffusion equipment including the swing diffusers.", "start": 2751.223, "stop": 2755.062, "duration": 3.84, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "say", "diffusion", "equipment", "include", "the", "swing", "diffuser"]]}, {"text": "And on page 76 and 77 there's quite a discussion of that a very poor form showing --", "start": 2755.062, "stop": 2760.333, "duration": 5.27, "cleanText": [["and", "on", "page", "and", "there", "be", "quite", "a", "discussion", "of", "that", "a", "very", "poor", "form", "showing"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "There's no evidence.", "start": 2760.333, "stop": 2761.299, "duration": 0.97, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "evidence"]]}, {"text": "There's not -- there's no evidence constructed to show what other things besides swing diffusers could do the job that swing diffusers do.", "start": 2761.299, "stop": 2769.526, "duration": 8.23, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "not", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "construct", "to", "show", "what", "other", "thing", "besides", "swing", "diffuser", "could", "do", "the", "job", "that", "swing", "diffuser", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the record shows that when we bid on diffusers per se, and this is on 77, and got the award that the municipality was persuaded unless we have their swing diffuser, we shouldn't be even allowed to put in our diffusers.", "start": 2769.526, "stop": 2784.932, "duration": 15.41, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "record", "show", "that", "when", "we", "bid", "on", "diffuser", "per", "se", "and", "this", "be", "on", "and", "get", "the", "award", "that", "the", "municipality", "be", "persuade", "unless", "we", "have", "their", "swing", "diffuser", "we", "should", "not", "be", "even", "allow", "to", "put", "in", "our", "diffuser"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it doesn't reach it quite, doesn't it?", "start": 2784.932, "stop": 2786.903, "duration": 1.97, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "do", "not", "reach", "it", "quite", "do", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, the case is not gone to evidence yet.", "start": 2786.903, "stop": 2790.547, "duration": 3.64, "cleanText": [["no", "the", "case", "be", "not", "go", "to", "evidence", "yet"]]}, {"text": "There has been no real evidence taken on the point of the monopolization.", "start": 2790.547, "stop": 2795.061, "duration": 4.51, "cleanText": [["there", "have", "be", "no", "real", "evidence", "take", "on", "the", "point", "of", "the", "monopolization"]]}, {"text": "The evidence was taken on the issue of fraud.", "start": 2795.061, "stop": 2797.127, "duration": 2.07, "cleanText": [["the", "evidence", "be", "take", "on", "the", "issue", "of", "fraud"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Are there licensees of the patentee or --", "start": 2797.127, "stop": 2800.672, "duration": 3.55, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "licensee", "of", "the", "patentee", "or"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "That isn't in the record and I know of none on this patent, of course the patent has expired.", "start": 2800.672, "stop": 2805.35, "duration": 4.68, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "not", "in", "the", "record", "and", "i", "know", "of", "none", "on", "this", "patent", "of", "course", "the", "patent", "have", "expire"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "So the patentee made and sold them all himself?", "start": 2805.35, "stop": 2809.282, "duration": 3.93, "cleanText": [["so", "the", "patentee", "make", "and", "sell", "them", "all", "himself"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's my understanding.", "start": 2809.282, "stop": 2810.384, "duration": 1.1, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "my", "understanding"]]}, {"text": "That would -- the record would so indicate.", "start": 2810.384, "stop": 2813.066, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["that", "would", "the", "record", "would", "so", "indicate"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is this a -- is this kind of fraud a -- if it were proved, is it a criminal, is it a violation of any criminal law?", "start": 2813.066, "stop": 2822.774, "duration": 9.71, "cleanText": [["be", "this", "a", "be", "this", "kind", "of", "fraud", "a", "if", "it", "we", "be", "prove", "be", "it", "a", "criminal", "be", "it", "a", "violation", "of", "any", "criminal", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, I would take it would be.", "start": 2822.774, "stop": 2824.461, "duration": 1.69, "cleanText": [["oh", "i", "would", "take", "it", "would", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But if the general -- is this the general fraudulent misrepresentation?", "start": 2824.461, "stop": 2830.227, "duration": 5.77, "cleanText": [["but", "if", "the", "general", "be", "this", "the", "general", "fraudulent", "misrepresentation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the -- in order to file --", "start": 2830.227, "stop": 2831.408, "duration": 1.18, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "in", "order", "to", "file"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Voice Overlap)", "start": 2831.408, "stop": 2831.764, "duration": 0.36, "cleanText": [["voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- the patent there must be an old file representing that there was no prior public use more than a year before.", "start": 2831.764, "stop": 2837.356, "duration": 5.59, "cleanText": [["the", "patent", "there", "must", "be", "an", "old", "file", "represent", "that", "there", "be", "no", "prior", "public", "use", "more", "than", "a", "year", "before"]]}, {"text": "That oath was filed in accordance with the Patent Office rules and it's my understanding that there is a criminal statute which would apply.", "start": 2837.356, "stop": 2844.621, "duration": 7.26, "cleanText": [["that", "oath", "be", "file", "in", "accordance", "with", "the", "patent", "office", "rule", "and", "it", "be", "my", "understanding", "that", "there", "be", "a", "criminal", "statute", "which", "would", "apply"]]}, {"text": "Of course the statue would be -- the statute limitations has long passed on it.", "start": 2844.621, "stop": 2850.188, "duration": 5.57, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "the", "statue", "would", "be", "the", "statute", "limitation", "have", "long", "pass", "on", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, would that start to run when they opened this file or when somebody learns it was wrong?", "start": 2850.188, "stop": 2854.025, "duration": 3.84, "cleanText": [["well", "would", "that", "start", "to", "run", "when", "they", "open", "this", "file", "or", "when", "somebody", "learn", "it", "be", "wrong"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "I don't know.", "start": 2854.025, "stop": 2854.89, "duration": 0.86, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "know"]]}, {"text": "I should -- there are some cases that I can't held in my fingertips that might -- would indicate it starts when the oath is made.", "start": 2854.89, "stop": 2862.984, "duration": 8.09, "cleanText": [["i", "should", "there", "be", "some", "case", "that", "i", "can", "not", "hold", "in", "my", "fingertip", "that", "might", "would", "indicate", "it", "start", "when", "the", "oath", "be", "make"]]}, {"text": "We didn't find out about it for sure until well into 1962, and our motion for summary judgment was not filed until September of 1962.", "start": 2862.984, "stop": 2872.173, "duration": 9.19, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "find", "out", "about", "it", "for", "sure", "until", "well", "into", "and", "our", "motion", "for", "summary", "judgment", "be", "not", "file", "until", "september", "of"]]}, {"text": "And up to that time, there was no definite proof of it in our opinion.", "start": 2872.173, "stop": 2879.752, "duration": 7.58, "cleanText": [["and", "up", "to", "that", "time", "there", "be", "no", "definite", "proof", "of", "it", "in", "our", "opinion"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2879.752, "stop": 2895.043, "duration": 15.29, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think they would have to show that there was some damage.", "start": 2895.043, "stop": 2896.663, "duration": 1.62, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "they", "would", "have", "to", "show", "that", "there", "be", "some", "damage"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2896.663, "stop": 2900.007, "duration": 3.34, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think they'd have to show that somebody was harmed by reason of it.", "start": 2900.007, "stop": 2903.429, "duration": 3.42, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "they", "would", "have", "to", "show", "that", "somebody", "be", "harm", "by", "reason", "of", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2903.429, "stop": 2904.075, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "In order to recover any damages or to --", "start": 2904.075, "stop": 2906.917, "duration": 2.84, "cleanText": [["in", "order", "to", "recover", "any", "damage", "or", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2906.917, "stop": 2916.64, "duration": 9.72, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Into criminal --", "start": 2916.64, "stop": 2917.241, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["into", "criminal"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 2917.241, "stop": 2938.098, "duration": 20.86, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, I think they could.", "start": 2938.098, "stop": 2940.502, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["yes", "i", "think", "they", "could"]]}, {"text": "I think they could.", "start": 2940.502, "stop": 2941.962, "duration": 1.46, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "they", "could"]]}, {"text": "And if I could answer it in that same connection Mr. Justice Fortas' question to Mr. Friedman as to the matter of whether we claim that this should apply to more than fraud, whether a state should be, justify such an action.", "start": 2941.962, "stop": 2958.018, "duration": 16.06, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "i", "could", "answer", "it", "in", "that", "same", "connection", "mr", "justice", "fortas", "question", "to", "mr", "friedman", "as", "to", "the", "matter", "of", "whether", "we", "claim", "that", "this", "should", "apply", "to", "more", "than", "fraud", "whether", "a", "state", "should", "be", "justify", "such", "an", "action"]]}, {"text": "It's my position that anything that can be shown to be bad faith and that's what some of these cases have held that I cited, should be the basis for such an action.", "start": 2958.018, "stop": 2966.555, "duration": 8.54, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "my", "position", "that", "anything", "that", "can", "be", "show", "to", "be", "bad", "faith", "and", "that", "be", "what", "some", "of", "these", "case", "have", "hold", "that", "i", "cite", "should", "be", "the", "basis", "for", "such", "an", "action"]]}, {"text": "In other words, if the patent have -- if the patent infringement suit is brought in bad faith for the purpose of obtaining monopolization, I think there might be an action.", "start": 2966.555, "stop": 2975.432, "duration": 8.88, "cleanText": [["in", "other", "word", "if", "the", "patent", "have", "if", "the", "patent", "infringement", "suit", "be", "bring", "in", "bad", "faith", "for", "the", "purpose", "of", "obtain", "monopolization", "i", "think", "there", "might", "be", "an", "action"]]}, {"text": "But just on a simple mistake, I do not think so and there's a reason which I don't know that Mr. Friedman would have like to have set forth because the person who issues the patent is the Government.", "start": 2975.432, "stop": 2986.138, "duration": 10.71, "cleanText": [["but", "just", "on", "a", "simple", "mistake", "i", "do", "not", "think", "so", "and", "there", "be", "a", "reason", "which", "i", "do", "not", "know", "that", "mr", "friedman", "would", "have", "like", "to", "have", "set", "forth", "because", "the", "person", "who", "issue", "the", "patent", "be", "the", "government"]]}, {"text": "And if the Government issued the patent period by a mistake, there might be a question of Government liability or sovereign immunity comes in but isn't what it used to be and --", "start": 2986.138, "stop": 2996.573, "duration": 10.43, "cleanText": [["and", "if", "the", "government", "issue", "the", "patent", "period", "by", "a", "mistake", "there", "might", "be", "a", "question", "of", "government", "liability", "or", "sovereign", "immunity", "come", "in", "but", "be", "not", "what", "it", "use", "to", "be", "and"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "But sir, when you look at it from a point of view the antitrust law, does it make any difference why the patent is invalid?", "start": 2996.573, "stop": 3006.105, "duration": 9.53, "cleanText": [["but", "sir", "when", "you", "look", "at", "it", "from", "a", "point", "of", "view", "the", "antitrust", "law", "do", "it", "make", "any", "difference", "why", "the", "patent", "be", "invalid"]]}, {"text": "As I understand you now, you're asserting the proposition that if someone uses a patent and if that patent is invalid because it was fraudulently obtained, there follows automatically a cause of action under the antitrust laws regardless of what the patent is or what it covers, regardless of general market conditions.", "start": 3006.105, "stop": 3037.303, "duration": 31.2, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "understand", "you", "now", "you", "be", "assert", "the", "proposition", "that", "if", "someone", "use", "a", "patent", "and", "if", "that", "patent", "be", "invalid", "because", "it", "be", "fraudulently", "obtain", "there", "follow", "automatically", "a", "because", "of", "action", "under", "the", "antitrust", "law", "regardless", "of", "what", "the", "patent", "be", "or", "what", "it", "cover", "regardless", "of", "general", "market", "condition"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 3037.303, "stop": 3037.739, "duration": 0.44, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's my understanding that that is your position.", "start": 3037.739, "stop": 3039.737, "duration": 2, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "my", "understanding", "that", "that", "be", "your", "position"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "It's my position.", "start": 3039.737, "stop": 3041.317, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "my", "position"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now if that is so, from the point of view of the antitrust laws, what difference does it make whether the invalidity of the patent was due to fraudulent procurement or to some other reason?", "start": 3041.317, "stop": 3055.626, "duration": 14.31, "cleanText": [["now", "if", "that", "be", "so", "from", "the", "point", "of", "view", "of", "the", "antitrust", "law", "what", "difference", "do", "it", "make", "whether", "the", "invalidity", "of", "the", "patent", "be", "due", "to", "fraudulent", "procurement", "or", "to", "some", "other", "reason"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because so long as the patent owner is operating in good faith, under the basis of a Government grant of the patent, I don't think he could possibly commit a wrong.", "start": 3055.626, "stop": 3066.984, "duration": 11.36, "cleanText": [["because", "so", "long", "as", "the", "patent", "owner", "be", "operate", "in", "good", "faith", "under", "the", "basis", "of", "a", "government", "grant", "of", "the", "patent", "i", "do", "not", "think", "he", "could", "possibly", "commit", "a", "wrong"]]}, {"text": "It's only when he's not operating in good faith that I think any wrong could be done.", "start": 3066.984, "stop": 3072.004, "duration": 5.02, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "only", "when", "he", "be", "not", "operate", "in", "good", "faith", "that", "i", "think", "any", "wrong", "could", "be", "do"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 3072.004, "stop": 3072.078, "duration": 0.07, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Abe Fortas", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that in terms of antitrust doctrine, it's my understanding that good faith or bad faith is inconsequential.", "start": 3072.078, "stop": 3083.459, "duration": 11.38, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "in", "term", "of", "antitrust", "doctrine", "it", "be", "my", "understanding", "that", "good", "faith", "or", "bad", "faith", "be", "inconsequential"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Charles J. Merriam", "textObjs": [{"text": "On the question of intent, I would agree.", "start": 3083.459, "stop": 3085.885, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "question", "of", "intent", "i", "would", "agree"]]}, {"text": "But I think that this Court, as well as other courts, I don't have the citations here, has always held that a patent issue is a shield against the antitrust laws and it has been so considerate.", "start": 3085.885, "stop": 3097.414, "duration": 11.53, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "that", "this", "court", "as", "well", "as", "other", "court", "i", "do", "not", "have", "the", "citation", "here", "have", "always", "hold", "that", "a", "patent", "issue", "be", "a", "shield", "against", "the", "antitrust", "law", "and", "it", "have", "be", "so", "considerate"]]}, {"text": "I don't think that shield should be asserted where the thing is a -- where the patent has been obtained in bad faith and that's my position here.", "start": 3097.414, "stop": 3110.559, "duration": 13.14, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "shield", "should", "be", "assert", "where", "the", "thing", "be", "a", "where", "the", "patent", "have", "be", "obtain", "in", "bad", "faith", "and", "that", "be", "my", "position", "here"]]}, {"text": "The matter of the FMC as against Chicago Pump has never been raised before, fraud as a matter will have to prove if we get them when we go back.", "start": 3110.559, "stop": 3121.376, "duration": 10.82, "cleanText": [["the", "matter", "of", "the", "fmc", "as", "against", "chicago", "pump", "have", "never", "be", "raise", "before", "fraud", "as", "a", "matter", "will", "have", "to", "prove", "if", "we", "get", "them", "when", "we", "go", "back"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Collen did not answer my statement earlier what I made in my opening that in 1956, on page 16 of the record, we wrote them a letter saying that it had come to our attention that there was a possible fraud in this connection.", "start": 3121.376, "stop": 3138.877, "duration": 17.5, "cleanText": [["mr", "collen", "do", "not", "answer", "my", "statement", "earlier", "what", "i", "make", "in", "my", "opening", "that", "in", "on", "page", "of", "the", "record", "we", "write", "them", "a", "letter", "say", "that", "it", "have", "come", "to", "our", "attention", "that", "there", "be", "a", "possible", "fraud", "in", "this", "connection"]]}, {"text": "And record 62 shows that they -- while they replied, they denied any duty to look into the matter.", "start": 3138.877, "stop": 3144.888, "duration": 6.01, "cleanText": [["and", "record", "show", "that", "they", "while", "they", "reply", "they", "deny", "any", "duty", "to", "look", "into", "the", "matter"]]}, {"text": "And certainly, from that time on, I think we have no problem that the papers that which showed fraud were all in their possession as it turned out and that's a matter of proof we'll have to face when the time comes but it isn't here.", "start": 3144.888, "stop": 3160.797, "duration": 15.91, "cleanText": [["and", "certainly", "from", "that", "time", "on", "i", "think", "we", "have", "no", "problem", "that", "the", "paper", "that", "which", "show", "fraud", "we", "be", "all", "in", "their", "possession", "as", "it", "turn", "out", "and", "that", "be", "a", "matter", "of", "proof", "we", "will", "have", "to", "face", "when", "the", "time", "come", "but", "it", "be", "not", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "I wonder if I could ask Mr. Friedman a question Mr. Collen.", "start": 3160.797, "stop": 3163.479, "duration": 2.68, "cleanText": [["i", "wonder", "if", "i", "could", "ask", "mr", "friedman", "a", "question", "mr", "collen"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Certainly.", "start": 3163.479, "stop": 3165.555, "duration": 2.08, "cleanText": [["certainly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because -- perhaps I misunderstood it, but if as I understood it, it seemed to me there was some disparity between your brief and your oral argument and I'd like to be straightened out.", "start": 3165.555, "stop": 3179.059, "duration": 13.5, "cleanText": [["because", "perhaps", "i", "misunderstood", "it", "but", "if", "as", "i", "understand", "it", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "there", "be", "some", "disparity", "between", "your", "brief", "and", "your", "oral", "argument", "and", "I", "would", "like", "to", "be", "straighten", "out"]]}, {"text": "As I read that part B of your brief, it's the Government's position that the use of a patent fraudulently procured regardless of the nature of the patent, and without more, constitutes a monopoly under the antitrust laws.", "start": 3179.059, "stop": 3195.064, "duration": 16, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "read", "that", "part", "b", "of", "your", "brief", "it", "be", "the", "government", "s", "position", "that", "the", "use", "of", "a", "patent", "fraudulently", "procure", "regardless", "of", "the", "nature", "of", "the", "patent", "and", "without", "more", "constitute", "a", "monopoly", "under", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}, {"text": "That's what B seems to say to me and is that -- do I understand that position correctly?", "start": 3195.064, "stop": 3201.305, "duration": 6.24, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "b", "seem", "to", "say", "to", "me", "and", "be", "that", "do", "i", "understand", "that", "position", "correctly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes Mr. Justice that is our position that they procure the enforcement of a patent procured by fraud without more is enough to establish the legal monopolization under Section 2.", "start": 3201.305, "stop": 3212.425, "duration": 11.12, "cleanText": [["yes", "mr", "justice", "that", "be", "our", "position", "that", "they", "procure", "the", "enforcement", "of", "a", "patent", "procure", "by", "fraud", "without", "more", "be", "enough", "to", "establish", "the", "legal", "monopolization", "under", "section"]]}, {"text": "As I've tried to indicate yesterday, if the Court is unwilling to accept that argument, we suggest that in any event, in any event, a case maybe grounded upon the enforcement of a patent procured by fraud in the sense that if that patent is deemed to give monopoly power in the relevant market, if the relevant market is a critical consideration, that the obtaining of the power through the procurement of the patent by fraud that is enough to show (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 3212.425, "stop": 3244.615, "duration": 32.19, "cleanText": [["as", "I", "have", "try", "to", "indicate", "yesterday", "if", "the", "court", "be", "unwilling", "to", "accept", "that", "argument", "we", "suggest", "that", "in", "any", "event", "in", "any", "event", "a", "case", "maybe", "ground", "upon", "the", "enforcement", "of", "a", "patent", "procure", "by", "fraud", "in", "the", "sense", "that", "if", "that", "patent", "be", "deem", "to", "give", "monopoly", "power", "in", "the", "relevant", "market", "if", "the", "relevant", "market", "be", "a", "critical", "consideration", "that", "the", "obtaining", "of", "the", "power", "through", "the", "procurement", "of", "the", "patent", "by", "fraud", "that", "be", "enough", "to", "show", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you therefore exactly equate the meaning of the word monopoly as we know it in the patent law even though it's a little gadget with the meaning of the word monopoly under the Sherman Act?", "start": 3244.615, "stop": 3258.619, "duration": 14, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "therefore", "exactly", "equate", "the", "meaning", "of", "the", "word", "monopoly", "as", "we", "know", "it", "in", "the", "patent", "law", "even", "though", "it", "be", "a", "little", "gadget", "with", "the", "meaning", "of", "the", "word", "monopoly", "under", "the", "sherman", "act"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "In --", "start": 3258.619, "stop": 3258.968, "duration": 0.35, "cleanText": [["in"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you exactly equate the two?", "start": 3258.968, "stop": 3260.295, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "exactly", "equate", "the", "two"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, we say this Mr. Justice.", "start": 3260.295, "stop": 3262.148, "duration": 1.85, "cleanText": [["well", "we", "say", "this", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "We do it in limited case for the reasons I have given.", "start": 3262.148, "stop": 3265.207, "duration": 3.06, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "it", "in", "limited", "case", "for", "the", "reason", "i", "have", "give"]]}, {"text": "Now of course we recognize that in terms of the market and as I think this Court is self-recognized in the footnote in the Northern Pacific opinion that not every patent in the classical sense necessarily gives a monopoly and that it has complete power to exclude from all competing substitutes.", "start": 3265.207, "stop": 3285.876, "duration": 20.67, "cleanText": [["now", "of", "course", "we", "recognize", "that", "in", "term", "of", "the", "market", "and", "as", "i", "think", "this", "court", "be", "self", "recognize", "in", "the", "footnote", "in", "the", "northern", "pacific", "opinion", "that", "not", "every", "patent", "in", "the", "classical", "sense", "necessarily", "give", "a", "monopoly", "and", "that", "it", "have", "complete", "power", "to", "exclude", "from", "all", "compete", "substitute"]]}, {"text": "I mean some patents by definition may have a very small increment of advancement over other patents but we suggest basically two things.", "start": 3285.876, "stop": 3295.612, "duration": 9.74, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "some", "patent", "by", "definition", "may", "have", "a", "very", "small", "increment", "of", "advancement", "over", "other", "patent", "but", "we", "suggest", "basically", "two", "thing"]]}, {"text": "I think, one, as I attempted to argue yesterday, when you deal with a special case of a patent that is procured by a fraud, the considerations which normally apply to defining a market don't apply.", "start": 3295.612, "stop": 3308.118, "duration": 12.51, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "one", "as", "i", "attempt", "to", "argue", "yesterday", "when", "you", "deal", "with", "a", "special", "case", "of", "a", "patent", "that", "be", "procure", "by", "a", "fraud", "the", "consideration", "which", "normally", "apply", "to", "define", "a", "market", "do", "not", "apply"]]}, {"text": "And then the second point I tried to make was -- which I just made a moment -- trying to make a moment ago to you, if it was -- if that argument is to be rejected, if in fact even in this case the market need be defined, still the case should go back as we do think that even if the market has to be defined, the market power that rest on a fraudulent procured patent is enough in that situation to ground illegal monopoly if the requisite market position is sustained.", "start": 3308.118, "stop": 3341.771, "duration": 33.65, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "the", "second", "point", "i", "try", "to", "make", "be", "which", "i", "just", "make", "a", "moment", "try", "to", "make", "a", "moment", "ago", "to", "you", "if", "it", "be", "if", "that", "argument", "be", "to", "be", "reject", "if", "in", "fact", "even", "in", "this", "case", "the", "market", "need", "be", "define", "still", "the", "case", "should", "go", "back", "as", "we", "do", "think", "that", "even", "if", "the", "market", "have", "to", "be", "define", "the", "market", "power", "that", "rest", "on", "a", "fraudulent", "procured", "patent", "be", "enough", "in", "that", "situation", "to", "grind", "illegal", "monopoly", "if", "the", "requisite", "market", "position", "be", "sustain"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Going back to Justice Fortas' question (Inaudible)", "start": 3341.771, "stop": 3353.427, "duration": 11.66, "cleanText": [["go", "back", "to", "justice", "fortas", "question", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think Mr. Justice the distinction is that there is nothing fundamentally improper in attempting to assert your rights under a patent that the Government has given you were in good faith, you have obtained it, believing you have an invention.", "start": 3353.427, "stop": 3371.204, "duration": 17.78, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think", "mr", "justice", "the", "distinction", "be", "that", "there", "be", "nothing", "fundamentally", "improper", "in", "attempt", "to", "assert", "your", "right", "under", "a", "patent", "that", "the", "government", "have", "give", "you", "we", "be", "in", "good", "faith", "you", "have", "obtain", "it", "believe", "you", "have", "an", "invention"]]}, {"text": "If it turns out you're wrong later on, if it turns out that contrary to your views, this is not a valid patent, there's nothing odious about that.", "start": 3371.204, "stop": 3379.46, "duration": 8.26, "cleanText": [["if", "it", "turn", "out", "you", "be", "wrong", "later", "on", "if", "it", "turn", "out", "that", "contrary", "to", "your", "view", "this", "be", "not", "a", "valid", "patent", "there", "be", "nothing", "odious", "about", "that"]]}, {"text": "But it seems this is a quite different case where you knowingly obtained from the Government the power to exclude people from the product covered by the patent, it seems --", "start": 3379.46, "stop": 3390.291, "duration": 10.83, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "seem", "this", "be", "a", "quite", "different", "case", "where", "you", "knowingly", "obtain", "from", "the", "government", "the", "power", "to", "exclude", "people", "from", "the", "product", "cover", "by", "the", "patent", "it", "seem"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "The antitrust (Inaudible)", "start": 3390.291, "stop": 3397.067, "duration": 6.78, "cleanText": [["the", "antitrust", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think --", "start": 3397.067, "stop": 3397.871, "duration": 0.8, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 3397.871, "stop": 3399.508, "duration": 1.64, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "But I think that there are areas Mr. Justice where you do look, you do look to the basic intention with which the power was acquired.", "start": 3399.508, "stop": 3409.352, "duration": 9.84, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "think", "that", "there", "be", "area", "mr", "justice", "where", "you", "do", "look", "you", "do", "look", "to", "the", "basic", "intention", "with", "which", "the", "power", "be", "acquire"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's for maybe for attempts to monopolize, but I'm not -- I thought was sort of an -- I agree with Mr. Justice Fortas, that was irrelevant, it was actually monopolization which you say it is.", "start": 3409.352, "stop": 3422.122, "duration": 12.77, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "for", "maybe", "for", "attempt", "to", "monopolize", "but", "I", "be", "not", "i", "thought", "be", "sort", "of", "an", "i", "agree", "with", "mr", "justice", "fortas", "that", "be", "irrelevant", "it", "be", "actually", "monopolization", "which", "you", "say", "it", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3422.122, "stop": 3422.545, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "Now, I would suggest incidentally Mr. Justice.", "start": 3422.545, "stop": 3425.511, "duration": 2.97, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "would", "suggest", "incidentally", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "May I make one suggestion here that I don't know conceivably on the basis of the facts alleged, it might be appropriate in the course of amending the pleading to amend it to suggest and attempt, I suppose if in fact that is what is shown here.", "start": 3425.511, "stop": 3440.008, "duration": 14.5, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "make", "one", "suggestion", "here", "that", "i", "do", "not", "know", "conceivably", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "the", "fact", "allege", "it", "might", "be", "appropriate", "in", "the", "course", "of", "amend", "the", "pleading", "to", "amend", "it", "to", "suggest", "and", "attempt", "i", "suppose", "if", "in", "fact", "that", "be", "what", "be", "show", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible) I was -- could understand that.But your general rule of -- the general question is, why wouldn't this apply for invalidity for lack of invention.", "start": 3440.008, "stop": 3449.951, "duration": 9.94, "cleanText": [["inaudible", "i", "be", "could", "understand", "thatbut", "your", "general", "rule", "of", "the", "general", "question", "be", "why", "would", "not", "this", "apply", "for", "invalidity", "for", "lack", "of", "invention"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "And when we -- we suggest that this is a special case.", "start": 3449.951, "stop": 3452.929, "duration": 2.98, "cleanText": [["and", "when", "we", "we", "suggest", "that", "this", "be", "a", "special", "case"]]}, {"text": "This is a special case.", "start": 3452.929, "stop": 3453.994, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["this", "be", "a", "special", "case"]]}, {"text": "I mean here what you have, here what you have is the monopoly power or the power, the power to exclude which patent gives is procured improperly.", "start": 3453.994, "stop": 3464.715, "duration": 10.72, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "here", "what", "you", "have", "here", "what", "you", "have", "be", "the", "monopoly", "power", "or", "the", "power", "the", "power", "to", "exclude", "which", "patent", "give", "be", "procure", "improperly"]]}, {"text": "It's obtained, the power to exclude whatever it is excluding from, the power to exclude is obtained by virtue of making a (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 3464.715, "stop": 3471.281, "duration": 6.57, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "obtain", "the", "power", "to", "exclude", "whatever", "it", "be", "exclude", "from", "the", "power", "to", "exclude", "be", "obtain", "by", "virtue", "of", "make", "a", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "You feel that the patent is lost through that basis and nothing else?", "start": 3471.281, "stop": 3474.764, "duration": 3.48, "cleanText": [["you", "feel", "that", "the", "patent", "be", "lose", "through", "that", "basis", "and", "nothing", "else"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry I didn't get it.", "start": 3474.764, "stop": 3475.758, "duration": 0.99, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "i", "do", "not", "get", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "The shield that the patent affords you from the antitrust laws is lost for bad faith but nothing else, that's your position.", "start": 3475.758, "stop": 3486.247, "duration": 10.49, "cleanText": [["the", "shield", "that", "the", "patent", "affords", "you", "from", "the", "antitrust", "law", "be", "lose", "for", "bad", "faith", "but", "nothing", "else", "that", "be", "your", "position"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "I think yes, Mr. Justice, where you obtain it.", "start": 3486.247, "stop": 3488.982, "duration": 2.74, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "yes", "mr", "justice", "where", "you", "obtain", "it"]]}, {"text": "Where you obtain it -- where you obtain it to misrepresenting the facts to the Government, you cannot then rely on it as a basis for excluding others.", "start": 3488.982, "stop": 3497.576, "duration": 8.59, "cleanText": [["where", "you", "obtain", "it", "where", "you", "obtain", "it", "to", "misrepresent", "the", "fact", "to", "the", "government", "you", "can", "not", "then", "rely", "on", "it", "as", "a", "basis", "for", "exclude", "others"]]}, {"text": "I think that is our position.", "start": 3497.576, "stop": 3500.141, "duration": 2.57, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "be", "our", "position"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible) on the basis of the knowledge that the man has at the time he gets the patent, that its there whatever it is.", "start": 3500.141, "stop": 3512.719, "duration": 12.58, "cleanText": [["inaudible", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "the", "knowledge", "that", "the", "man", "have", "at", "the", "time", "he", "get", "the", "patent", "that", "its", "there", "whatever", "it", "be"]]}, {"text": "Are you drawing a distinction between an ordinary patent which nobody can tell whether it's valid or not until they try it out and may be then they won't know.", "start": 3512.719, "stop": 3522.027, "duration": 9.31, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "draw", "a", "distinction", "between", "an", "ordinary", "patent", "which", "nobody", "can", "tell", "whether", "it", "be", "valid", "or", "not", "until", "they", "try", "it", "out", "and", "may", "be", "then", "they", "will", "not", "know"]]}, {"text": "And you'd say there that the man can't be held guilty of violating the monopoly law or intending to do it because all he intended to do was to use what he considers to be a valid patent.", "start": 3522.027, "stop": 3536.168, "duration": 14.14, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "would", "say", "there", "that", "the", "man", "can", "not", "be", "hold", "guilty", "of", "violate", "the", "monopoly", "law", "or", "intend", "to", "do", "it", "because", "all", "he", "intend", "to", "do", "be", "to", "use", "what", "he", "consider", "to", "be", "a", "valid", "patent"]]}, {"text": "Are you drawing a distinction between that and when where the man who gets the patent, gets it with knowledge, it's no good, he is getting it in the way that he'd perjure himself in order to get it.", "start": 3536.168, "stop": 3548.529, "duration": 12.36, "cleanText": [["be", "you", "draw", "a", "distinction", "between", "that", "and", "when", "where", "the", "man", "who", "get", "the", "patent", "get", "it", "with", "knowledge", "it", "be", "no", "good", "he", "be", "get", "it", "in", "the", "way", "that", "he", "would", "perjure", "himself", "in", "order", "to", "get", "it"]]}, {"text": "Therefore you say that in that instant, he has gotten the monopoly as the benefits of a monopoly out of the patent, or is trying to and if he is guilty of monopolizing or intending to monopolize?", "start": 3548.529, "stop": 3560.539, "duration": 12.01, "cleanText": [["therefore", "you", "say", "that", "in", "that", "instant", "he", "have", "get", "the", "monopoly", "as", "the", "benefit", "of", "a", "monopoly", "out", "of", "the", "patent", "or", "be", "try", "to", "and", "if", "he", "be", "guilty", "of", "monopolize", "or", "intend", "to", "monopolize"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is precisely --", "start": 3560.539, "stop": 3561.634, "duration": 1.09, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "precisely"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "You do not say that if the patent might later be found to be invalid that necessarily means that a man violates the antitrust laws?", "start": 3561.634, "stop": 3571.09, "duration": 9.46, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "not", "say", "that", "if", "the", "patent", "might", "later", "be", "find", "to", "be", "invalid", "that", "necessarily", "mean", "that", "a", "man", "violate", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 3571.09, "stop": 3572.352, "duration": 1.26, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "But here you claim that -- your basic -- whether right or wrong, as I understand it, on the premise.", "start": 3572.352, "stop": 3578.333, "duration": 5.98, "cleanText": [["but", "here", "you", "claim", "that", "your", "basic", "whether", "right", "or", "wrong", "as", "i", "understand", "it", "on", "the", "premise"]]}, {"text": "This, as you charge, if this man committed perjury to get it, stating it was patentable when he knew it wasn't, that he knew from the very beginning it was not patentable, and he was trying to use it for the purpose that the man can use a legitimate patent, which is to monopolize, fix prices, and fix the term of sale of the commodity?", "start": 3578.333, "stop": 3597.369, "duration": 19.04, "cleanText": [["this", "as", "you", "charge", "if", "this", "man", "commit", "perjury", "to", "get", "it", "state", "it", "be", "patentable", "when", "he", "know", "it", "be", "not", "that", "he", "know", "from", "the", "very", "begin", "it", "be", "not", "patentable", "and", "he", "be", "try", "to", "use", "it", "for", "the", "purpose", "that", "the", "man", "can", "use", "a", "legitimate", "patent", "which", "be", "to", "monopolize", "fix", "price", "and", "fix", "the", "term", "of", "sale", "of", "the", "commodity"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct.", "start": 3597.369, "stop": 3599.422, "duration": 2.05, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what the -- was it the big argument about what a prior use is too, isn't there?", "start": 3599.422, "stop": 3605.66, "duration": 6.24, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "the", "be", "it", "the", "big", "argument", "about", "what", "a", "prior", "use", "be", "too", "be", "not", "there"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "There is, there is certainly Mr. Justice, but it --", "start": 3605.66, "stop": 3608.36, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "there", "be", "certainly", "mr", "justice", "but", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you may -- a fellow might in a very good faith think he had -- there hasn't been a prior use.", "start": 3608.36, "stop": 3613.995, "duration": 5.63, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "may", "a", "fellow", "might", "in", "a", "very", "good", "faith", "think", "he", "have", "there", "have", "not", "be", "a", "prior", "use"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "That is correct, it may well be --", "start": 3613.995, "stop": 3615.047, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "it", "may", "well", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why is that?", "start": 3615.047, "stop": 3616.072, "duration": 1.03, "cleanText": [["why", "be", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "It may well be if this case goes --", "start": 3616.072, "stop": 3617.279, "duration": 1.21, "cleanText": [["it", "may", "well", "be", "if", "this", "case", "go"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Because he may -- you may prove he's wrong too and if there was a fraud' on the Patent Office (Voice Overlap) --", "start": 3617.279, "stop": 3623.595, "duration": 6.32, "cleanText": [["because", "he", "may", "you", "may", "prove", "he", "be", "wrong", "too", "and", "if", "there", "be", "a", "fraud", "on", "the", "patent", "office", "voice", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I think --", "start": 3623.595, "stop": 3624.166, "duration": 0.57, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Byron R. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- to disclose a prior use for this perfectly good faith?", "start": 3624.166, "stop": 3627.278, "duration": 3.11, "cleanText": [["to", "disclose", "a", "prior", "use", "for", "this", "perfectly", "good", "faith"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, if and -- if -- I would suggest Mr. Justice, the allegation here is that they knowingly -- they know it.", "start": 3627.278, "stop": 3633.649, "duration": 6.37, "cleanText": [["well", "if", "and", "if", "i", "would", "suggest", "mr", "justice", "the", "allegation", "here", "be", "that", "they", "knowingly", "they", "know", "it"]]}, {"text": "They obtained this patent knowing there had been a prior use, that they have made a full statement.", "start": 3633.649, "stop": 3637.923, "duration": 4.27, "cleanText": [["they", "obtain", "this", "patent", "know", "there", "have", "be", "a", "prior", "use", "that", "they", "have", "make", "a", "full", "statement"]]}, {"text": "If this particular affidavit turns out not to satisfy those standards, I think there's no case.", "start": 3637.923, "stop": 3643.914, "duration": 5.99, "cleanText": [["if", "this", "particular", "affidavit", "turn", "out", "not", "to", "satisfy", "those", "standard", "i", "think", "there", "be", "no", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, is that to say Mr. Friedman, that all distinction between a so-called legal fraud and equitable fraud, you limit this to legal fraud --", "start": 3643.914, "stop": 3652.409, "duration": 8.49, "cleanText": [["well", "be", "that", "to", "say", "mr", "friedman", "that", "all", "distinction", "between", "a", "so", "called", "legal", "fraud", "and", "equitable", "fraud", "you", "limit", "this", "to", "legal", "fraud"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I --", "start": 3652.409, "stop": 3652.52, "duration": 0.11, "cleanText": [["well", "i"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Potter Stewart", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- the actual knowledge of the --", "start": 3652.52, "stop": 3654.492, "duration": 1.97, "cleanText": [["the", "actual", "knowledge", "of", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "I would suppose -- I just haven't gone in to that extent.", "start": 3654.492, "stop": 3658.609, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "suppose", "i", "just", "have", "not", "go", "in", "to", "that", "extent"]]}, {"text": "I think that there has to be some knowledge, something -- so put it this way Mr. Justice.", "start": 3658.609, "stop": 3665.434, "duration": 6.83, "cleanText": [["i", "think", "that", "there", "have", "to", "be", "some", "knowledge", "something", "so", "put", "it", "this", "way", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "I would say something that would shock the conscience of the Court that would make the Court believe it was improper.", "start": 3665.434, "stop": 3671.519, "duration": 6.08, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "say", "something", "that", "would", "shock", "the", "conscience", "of", "the", "court", "that", "would", "make", "the", "court", "believe", "it", "be", "improper"]]}, {"text": "They had obtained a patent improperly in a sense that they knowingly were getting monopoly, they had no right to get it.", "start": 3671.519, "stop": 3677.306, "duration": 5.79, "cleanText": [["they", "have", "obtain", "a", "patent", "improperly", "in", "a", "sense", "that", "they", "knowingly", "we", "be", "get", "monopoly", "they", "have", "no", "right", "to", "get", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Tom C. Clark", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 3677.306, "stop": 3681.607, "duration": 4.3, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "It did.", "start": 3681.607, "stop": 3682.748, "duration": 1.14, "cleanText": [["it", "do"]]}, {"text": "No, I'm sorry.", "start": 3682.748, "stop": 3683.62, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["no", "I", "be", "sorry"]]}, {"text": "This case did not go off on the pleading Mr. Justice.", "start": 3683.62, "stop": 3686.415, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["this", "case", "do", "not", "go", "off", "on", "the", "plead", "mr", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Tom C. Clark", "textObjs": [{"text": "So the --", "start": 3686.415, "stop": 3687.373, "duration": 0.96, "cleanText": [["so", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "As --", "start": 3687.373, "stop": 3687.613, "duration": 0.24, "cleanText": [["as"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Tom C. Clark", "textObjs": [{"text": "The allegation was that the -- he fraudulently and intentionally (Inaudible)?", "start": 3687.613, "stop": 3693.909, "duration": 6.3, "cleanText": [["the", "allegation", "be", "that", "the", "he", "fraudulently", "and", "intentionally", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3693.909, "stop": 3694.533, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "In that sense it went off on the pleading --", "start": 3694.533, "stop": 3696.355, "duration": 1.82, "cleanText": [["in", "that", "sense", "it", "go", "off", "on", "the", "pleading"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Tom C. Clark", "textObjs": [{"text": "On the pleading --", "start": 3696.355, "stop": 3697.419, "duration": 1.06, "cleanText": [["on", "the", "pleading"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "In the sense that --", "start": 3697.419, "stop": 3697.964, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "sense", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Tom C. Clark", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 3697.964, "stop": 3699.512, "duration": 1.55, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, well that's of course, correct.", "start": 3699.512, "stop": 3701.118, "duration": 1.61, "cleanText": [["yes", "well", "that", "be", "of", "course", "correct"]]}, {"text": "I mean the case went off on the assumption that he could prove what he had alleged, that that didn't allege a violation of the Sherman Act.", "start": 3701.118, "stop": 3708.956, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "the", "case", "go", "off", "on", "the", "assumption", "that", "he", "could", "prove", "what", "he", "have", "allege", "that", "that", "do", "not", "allege", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "sherman", "act"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is that allegation (Inaudible)?", "start": 3708.956, "stop": 3718.293, "duration": 9.34, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "allegation", "inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "I believe the allegation speaks of the plaintiff.", "start": 3718.293, "stop": 3722.72, "duration": 4.43, "cleanText": [["i", "believe", "the", "allegation", "speaks", "of", "the", "plaintiff"]]}, {"text": "It says at page 60 of the record paragraph 15.", "start": 3722.72, "stop": 3726.313, "duration": 3.59, "cleanText": [["it", "say", "at", "page", "of", "the", "record", "paragraph"]]}, {"text": "It says plaintiff including its predecessor.", "start": 3726.313, "stop": 3729.537, "duration": 3.22, "cleanText": [["it", "say", "plaintiff", "include", "its", "predecessor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Including its predecessor?", "start": 3729.537, "stop": 3730.26, "duration": 0.72, "cleanText": [["include", "its", "predecessor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Including its predecessor.", "start": 3730.26, "stop": 3731.919, "duration": 1.66, "cleanText": [["include", "its", "predecessor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible)", "start": 3731.919, "stop": 3772.091, "duration": 40.17, "cleanText": [["inaudible"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "I wouldn't think so Mr. Justice.", "start": 3772.091, "stop": 3773.96, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "not", "think", "so", "mr", "justice"]]}, {"text": "But I do point out this to you that there's again a dispute that it was a letter which was written in 1956 calling the attention of FMC to the fact of prior use, so that it may be that in effect they could be -- I don't know, again, this would be a question for the --", "start": 3773.96, "stop": 3793.549, "duration": 19.59, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "do", "point", "out", "this", "to", "you", "that", "there", "be", "again", "a", "dispute", "that", "it", "be", "a", "letter", "which", "be", "write", "in", "call", "the", "attention", "of", "fmc", "to", "the", "fact", "of", "prior", "use", "so", "that", "it", "may", "be", "that", "in", "effect", "they", "could", "be", "i", "do", "not", "know", "again", "this", "would", "be", "a", "question", "for", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "(Inaudible) a matter of proof?", "start": 3793.549, "stop": 3794.598, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["inaudible", "a", "matter", "of", "proof"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of proof, they might say that in fact having continue to enforce the patent and brought this suit after this knowledge, they are now -- the knowledge of their predecessor may be imputed.", "start": 3794.598, "stop": 3803.877, "duration": 9.28, "cleanText": [["of", "proof", "they", "might", "say", "that", "in", "fact", "have", "continue", "to", "enforce", "the", "patent", "and", "bring", "this", "suit", "after", "this", "knowledge", "they", "be", "now", "the", "knowledge", "of", "their", "predecessor", "may", "be", "impute"]]}, {"text": "And in the comment, I did state in referring at page 60 to the obtaining the patent well knowing that it -- that is the plaintiff had no basis for, this again it seem to -- will be a question of proof.", "start": 3803.877, "stop": 3817.089, "duration": 13.21, "cleanText": [["and", "in", "the", "comment", "i", "do", "state", "in", "refer", "at", "page", "to", "the", "obtain", "the", "patent", "well", "know", "that", "it", "that", "be", "the", "plaintiff", "have", "no", "basis", "for", "this", "again", "it", "seem", "to", "will", "be", "a", "question", "of", "proof"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "I hope I didn't understand you to (Inaudible) in order for us to decide even in whole or in part on your side, we have assume that it's law that when a man gets the patent (Inaudible) conviction of the court, he thereby violates the antitrust law.", "start": 3817.089, "stop": 3832.973, "duration": 15.88, "cleanText": [["i", "hope", "i", "do", "not", "understand", "you", "to", "inaudible", "in", "order", "for", "us", "to", "decide", "even", "in", "whole", "or", "in", "part", "on", "your", "side", "we", "have", "assume", "that", "it", "be", "law", "that", "when", "a", "man", "get", "the", "patent", "inaudible", "conviction", "of", "the", "court", "he", "thereby", "violate", "the", "antitrust", "law"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, no.", "start": 3832.973, "stop": 3833.709, "duration": 0.74, "cleanText": [["no", "no"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's an extension of the (Inaudible) Doctrine --", "start": 3833.709, "stop": 3836.225, "duration": 2.52, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "an", "extension", "of", "the", "inaudible", "doctrine"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 3836.225, "stop": 3836.275, "duration": 0.05, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "-- that I wouldn't want to read.", "start": 3836.275, "stop": 3837.452, "duration": 1.18, "cleanText": [["that", "i", "would", "not", "want", "to", "read"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Daniel M. Friedman", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I did not intend to suggest that Mr. Justice.", "start": 3837.452, "stop": 3840.628, "duration": 3.18, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "do", "not", "intend", "to", "suggest", "that", "mr", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Hugo L. Black", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'm sorry to take (Inaudible)", "start": 3840.628, "stop": 3851.497, "duration": 10.87, "cleanText": [["I", "be", "sorry", "to", "take", "inaudible"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Warren Court", "arguedOn": "Oct  12 - 13, 1965", "petitioner": "Walker Process Equipment, Inc.", "respondent": "Food Machinery & Chemical Corporation", "docket": "13", "citation": "382US172(1965)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/382/172", "lowerCourt": "United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit", "grantedOn": "", "decidedOn": "Dec 6, 1965"}